WEBVTT

cue-1
00:00:00.560 --> 00:00:01.560
The Path of Prayer

cue-2
00:00:02.660 --> 00:00:03.760
by Samuel Chadwick.

cue-3
00:00:04.420 --> 00:00:06.520
Originally published in 1903.

cue-4
00:00:07.820 --> 00:00:11.760
Audiobook produced and copyrighted by
scrollreader.com.

cue-5
00:00:13.380 --> 00:00:14.100
Chapter One:

cue-6
00:00:14.960 --> 00:00:16.120
The Sign of Prayer.

cue-7
00:00:18.940 --> 00:00:20.900
All religions include prayer.

cue-8
00:00:21.600 --> 00:00:23.350
God and prayer belong together.

cue-9
00:00:24.020 --> 00:00:29.000
Belief in God naturally leads to belief in
prayer. These ideas may be rough

cue-10
00:00:29.000 --> 00:00:32.000
or even misguided in some early or pagan
cultures,

cue-11
00:00:32.619 --> 00:00:35.480
but they are part of the shared instincts
of humanity.

cue-12
00:00:36.620 --> 00:00:38.920
The Old Testament speaks often about
prayer.

cue-13
00:00:39.520 --> 00:00:42.240
It gives many commands and encouragements
to pray.

cue-14
00:00:43.360 --> 00:00:48.340
Its stories of rescue, victory,
experience, and vision all

cue-15
00:00:48.340 --> 00:00:53.260
show the power of earnest prayer. In the
life of our Lord, every

cue-16
00:00:53.260 --> 00:00:57.960
major moment was connected with special
times of prayer. His teaching

cue-17
00:00:57.960 --> 00:01:00.300
gives strong promises to those who pray.

cue-18
00:01:01.360 --> 00:01:05.720
He explained how prayer works, but he did
not try to explain its mystery.

cue-19
00:01:06.420 --> 00:01:11.200
For him, prayer was not a problem to
solve. The two parables he told

cue-20
00:01:11.200 --> 00:01:13.120
about prayer can be difficult for some.

cue-21
00:01:13.820 --> 00:01:18.720
It may seem strange to compare God to an
unjust judge or an unwilling

cue-22
00:01:18.720 --> 00:01:19.120
friend,

cue-23
00:01:20.120 --> 00:01:21.540
but God is not like them.

cue-24
00:01:22.380 --> 00:01:27.259
These parables are not meant to describe
God's character, but to show the value of

cue-25
00:01:27.260 --> 00:01:28.640
persistence in prayer.

cue-26
00:01:29.800 --> 00:01:34.660
The foundation of prayer is our
relationship as children of God. Prayer is

cue-27
00:01:34.660 --> 00:01:38.980
possible and reasonable because it is
like a child speaking to a

cue-28
00:01:38.980 --> 00:01:43.520
father. It is natural for a child to ask
and right for a

cue-29
00:01:43.520 --> 00:01:44.700
father to listen.

cue-30
00:01:45.940 --> 00:01:50.880
If human parents, though imperfect, give
good gifts to their children, how

cue-31
00:01:50.880 --> 00:01:54.960
much more will our heavenly Father give
good things to those who ask Him?

cue-32
00:01:57.260 --> 00:02:01.940
There are many questions about prayer, but
they can't be solved by thinking alone.

cue-33
00:02:02.600 --> 00:02:05.240
They are answered through the act of
praying itself.

cue-34
00:02:06.440 --> 00:02:11.400
Prayer is something we experience, and
throughout history, those who have prayed

cue-35
00:02:11.400 --> 00:02:15.040
testify that God hears and answers His
children.

cue-36
00:02:16.900 --> 00:02:19.320
What God thinks about prayer.

cue-37
00:02:20.880 --> 00:02:25.660
God's thoughts are not like human
thoughts, and His ways are not like ours.

cue-38
00:02:26.600 --> 00:02:30.080
His ways are higher, just as the heavens
are higher than the earth.

cue-39
00:02:31.100 --> 00:02:35.900
God has made His thoughts and ways known
through His Word and through His

cue-40
00:02:35.900 --> 00:02:36.240
Son.

cue-41
00:02:37.300 --> 00:02:41.780
He reveals Himself through real
experiences and through events in the

cue-42
00:02:41.780 --> 00:02:46.600
lives of people and in history. He has not
explained His thoughts

cue-43
00:02:46.600 --> 00:02:51.580
in abstract theories, but has shown them
through life and has taught His ways

cue-44
00:02:51.580 --> 00:02:54.640
through commands, principles, and
examples.

cue-45
00:02:55.880 --> 00:03:00.800
There is a clear example that shows what
God thinks about prayer.

cue-46
00:03:00.800 --> 00:03:03.940
His view of prayer is seen in every
command to pray,

cue-47
00:03:04.600 --> 00:03:09.460
every rule about prayer, every promise
connected to prayer, and every

cue-48
00:03:09.460 --> 00:03:11.760
example where prayer is answered.

cue-49
00:03:12.920 --> 00:03:15.300
Each part helps us understand the whole.

cue-50
00:03:16.120 --> 00:03:21.020
Yet in Scripture, each subject is shown
most fully in a particular example.

cue-51
00:03:22.120 --> 00:03:27.080
In the conversion of Saul of Tarsus, we
see a special and clear picture of God's

cue-52
00:03:27.080 --> 00:03:28.180
mind about prayer.

cue-53
00:03:29.820 --> 00:03:34.740
In that event, there are three people
involved: the one who prays, God who

cue-54
00:03:34.740 --> 00:03:37.980
hears, and the person through whom the
answer comes.

cue-55
00:03:39.040 --> 00:03:40.940
God is at the center.

cue-56
00:03:41.000 --> 00:03:45.420
Prayer is made to Him, understood through
Him, and answered by Him.

cue-57
00:03:46.740 --> 00:03:49.260
God speaks of prayer with a sense of
wonder.

cue-58
00:03:50.100 --> 00:03:51.300
Look, he is praying.

cue-59
00:03:52.200 --> 00:03:56.940
This is human language, and though it is
limited, it still points to something

cue-60
00:03:56.940 --> 00:04:01.740
real in God. Does God feel wonder? Can He
experience

cue-61
00:04:01.740 --> 00:04:03.440
surprise or amazement?

cue-62
00:04:04.190 --> 00:04:09.100
Are there things that are wonderful to
Him? This is how God speaks, and

cue-63
00:04:09.100 --> 00:04:11.960
it shows that prayer is deeply precious to
Him.

cue-64
00:04:12.800 --> 00:04:17.459
It seems that one of the greatest things
in God's universe is a person who prays.

cue-65
00:04:18.620 --> 00:04:21.220
There is only one thing more surprising,

cue-66
00:04:21.280 --> 00:04:24.460
that people, knowing this, still do not
pray.

cue-67
00:04:25.660 --> 00:04:25.900
Look,

cue-68
00:04:26.880 --> 00:04:30.120
in that word there is wonder, joy, and
delight.

cue-69
00:04:31.120 --> 00:04:35.760
In God's view, prayer is greater than the
wonders of the heavens, more glorious than

cue-70
00:04:35.760 --> 00:04:40.250
the mysteries of the earth, and more
powerful than all the forces of creation.

cue-71
00:04:42.240 --> 00:04:46.740
God sees prayer as the sign of all that
happened to Saul of Tarsus on the

cue-72
00:04:46.740 --> 00:04:47.700
Damascus Road.

cue-73
00:04:48.680 --> 00:04:51.060
The event can be described in different
ways.

cue-74
00:04:51.780 --> 00:04:56.000
To the churches in Judea, it was a
conversion that turned their greatest

cue-75
00:04:56.000 --> 00:04:57.280
enemy into a preacher.

cue-76
00:04:58.460 --> 00:05:01.920
Paul himself describes it this way when
writing to the Galatians.

cue-77
00:05:02.720 --> 00:05:07.700
He went into the regions of Syria and
Cilicia and was not personally known

cue-78
00:05:07.700 --> 00:05:09.140
to the churches in Judea,

cue-79
00:05:09.860 --> 00:05:14.340
but they had heard that the one who once
persecuted them was now preaching the

cue-80
00:05:14.340 --> 00:05:16.140
faith he had tried to destroy.

cue-81
00:05:17.240 --> 00:05:19.780
Because of this, they glorified God.

cue-82
00:05:21.580 --> 00:05:25.200
This was a true conversion that came from
a powerful experience.

cue-83
00:05:26.320 --> 00:05:27.640
What was that experience?

cue-84
00:05:28.400 --> 00:05:32.160
Paul explains that God was pleased to
reveal His Son in him.

cue-85
00:05:33.180 --> 00:05:37.760
That is what the Damascus Road meant to
him. But when God speaks of

cue-86
00:05:37.760 --> 00:05:40.760
it, He sums it all up in one simple
statement.

cue-87
00:05:41.680 --> 00:05:42.680
Look, he is praying.

cue-88
00:05:43.580 --> 00:05:47.540
That is what it meant to God, and that is
what it always means to Him.

cue-89
00:05:48.400 --> 00:05:52.140
Prayer is the sign, the proof, and the
measure of grace.

cue-90
00:05:53.260 --> 00:05:58.080
When God works in a person and brings them
into His family as His children, the

cue-91
00:05:58.080 --> 00:05:58.979
result is this.

cue-92
00:05:59.790 --> 00:06:04.720
They begin to praySaul of Tarsus had
prayed all his life, but it

cue-93
00:06:04.720 --> 00:06:09.540
was not until that moment that he truly
prayed in the way God understands prayer.

cue-94
00:06:10.820 --> 00:06:14.480
The words of a simple children's hymn also
apply to adults.

cue-95
00:06:15.560 --> 00:06:18.640
I often say my prayers, but do I really
pray?

cue-96
00:06:20.030 --> 00:06:24.800
Prayer belongs to those who are God's
children, and it shows that they are His

cue-97
00:06:24.800 --> 00:06:25.220
children.

cue-98
00:06:26.280 --> 00:06:29.240
It seems that God divides people in a very
simple way,

cue-99
00:06:29.920 --> 00:06:31.960
those who pray and those who do not.

cue-100
00:06:32.960 --> 00:06:36.880
It is a simple test, but it is clear and
decisive.

cue-101
00:06:39.500 --> 00:06:41.040
The way God answers prayer.

cue-102
00:06:43.240 --> 00:06:44.580
God answers with joy.

cue-103
00:06:45.640 --> 00:06:50.080
There is a tone of delight in His words to
Ananias, like the joy seen in the

cue-104
00:06:50.080 --> 00:06:53.820
parables of the lost sheep, the lost coin,
and the lost son.

cue-105
00:06:54.780 --> 00:06:59.500
Look, he is praying shows that there is
joy in the heart of God the Father when

cue-106
00:06:59.500 --> 00:07:01.540
His lost children begin to pray.

cue-107
00:07:02.440 --> 00:07:05.220
God answers in a way that fits who He is.

cue-108
00:07:06.080 --> 00:07:10.480
Ananias may hesitate or question, but God
does not hesitate with people.

cue-109
00:07:11.320 --> 00:07:16.279
God is ready to answer when a person
reaches out to Him, and His response is

cue-110
00:07:16.280 --> 00:07:19.020
always greater than the cry that calls to
Him.

cue-111
00:07:20.200 --> 00:07:22.940
God's answer to Saul of Tarsus had two
parts.

cue-112
00:07:23.600 --> 00:07:26.140
He gave him a vision and sent him a
messenger,

cue-113
00:07:26.800 --> 00:07:29.520
a vision and a man that matched each
other.

cue-114
00:07:30.720 --> 00:07:32.030
This is often God's way.

cue-115
00:07:32.700 --> 00:07:36.160
First, He gives assurance, and then He
confirms it.

cue-116
00:07:36.980 --> 00:07:40.520
This is the kind of prayer that trusts God
and does not fail.

cue-117
00:07:41.460 --> 00:07:44.580
God's servants work together with Him in
the work of prayer.

cue-118
00:07:45.680 --> 00:07:50.680
This is part of the mystery of how God and
people cooperate. The Lord goes ahead

cue-119
00:07:50.680 --> 00:07:51.960
of the person He sends.

cue-120
00:07:52.880 --> 00:07:57.800
Saul was ready and waiting for the man he
had already seen in a vision from God,

cue-121
00:07:58.500 --> 00:08:01.240
and Ananias found him prepared and ready.

cue-122
00:08:03.360 --> 00:08:06.860
God gave Ananias the sign of prayer as
proof of grace.

cue-123
00:08:07.640 --> 00:08:11.439
It was His own sign, and it is still the
sign He gives today.

cue-124
00:08:12.560 --> 00:08:17.300
Is there any clearer proof that a person
belongs to God than that they truly pray?

cue-125
00:08:18.400 --> 00:08:21.700
Of Elijah, it is said that he prayed
earnestly.

cue-126
00:08:22.580 --> 00:08:26.680
Some people are said to live in an
atmosphere of devotion, but it is one

cue-127
00:08:26.680 --> 00:08:30.880
thing to be around prayer and another to
truly pray with sincerity.

cue-128
00:08:32.000 --> 00:08:36.040
Finney once attended a weekly prayer
meeting where many prayers were spoken,

cue-129
00:08:36.040 --> 00:08:37.600
yet no answers came.

cue-130
00:08:38.500 --> 00:08:41.040
Mueller prayed, and answers followed.

cue-131
00:08:41.990 --> 00:08:44.800
That is why people recognized him as a man
of God.

cue-132
00:08:45.840 --> 00:08:49.120
When I was a small child, about six or
seven years old,

cue-133
00:08:49.780 --> 00:08:51.660
I was sent to a neighbor's house one
morning.

cue-134
00:08:52.800 --> 00:08:55.980
I knocked, opened the door, and stepped
inside.

cue-135
00:08:56.980 --> 00:09:01.700
There, by a chair with an open Bible, Mrs.
Davenport was kneeling in prayer.

cue-136
00:09:02.780 --> 00:09:03.880
She did not notice me.

cue-137
00:09:04.660 --> 00:09:09.599
I stood quietly for a moment in deep
respect, then gently left and closed

cue-138
00:09:09.600 --> 00:09:14.600
the door. Many years have passed since
that day, but

cue-139
00:09:14.600 --> 00:09:15.780
I have never forgotten it.

cue-140
00:09:16.900 --> 00:09:21.760
From that moment on, I knew that Mrs.
Davenport was a true servant of God

cue-141
00:09:22.480 --> 00:09:23.520
because she prayed.

cue-142
00:09:24.480 --> 00:09:29.200
This is God's sure sign, and even the
world recognizes it as clear

cue-143
00:09:29.200 --> 00:09:29.540
proof.

cue-144
00:09:31.480 --> 00:09:35.640
Prayer changed everything for Saul of
Tarsus, and it always makes a

cue-145
00:09:35.640 --> 00:09:40.240
difference. It brought him a new assurance
of God, a stronger faith,

cue-146
00:09:40.240 --> 00:09:44.840
fellowship with God's people, healing, a
new calling, a new

cue-147
00:09:44.840 --> 00:09:46.840
inheritance, and new power.

cue-148
00:09:47.840 --> 00:09:51.520
Prayer changes things. It makes all things
possible

cue-149
00:09:52.220 --> 00:09:56.550
because it connects the one who prays with
God's unlimited power.

cue-150
00:09:57.800 --> 00:10:02.620
Do we truly pray? Do we mean what we say
when we pray? Does God place His

cue-151
00:10:02.620 --> 00:10:03.940
approval on our prayers?

cue-152
00:10:05.660 --> 00:10:07.280
Lord, teach us to pray.

cue-153
00:10:07.960 --> 00:10:12.700
Prayer is the voice of a humble sinner
turning back to God, while angels

cue-154
00:10:12.700 --> 00:10:15.520
rejoice and say, "Look, he is praying."

cue-155
00:10:16.420 --> 00:10:20.360
It is the very breath of a Christian, the
air they are meant to live in,

cue-156
00:10:21.240 --> 00:10:23.319
their word of hope even at death,

cue-157
00:10:24.060 --> 00:10:26.200
and with prayer they enter heaven.

cue-158
00:10:28.880 --> 00:10:29.620
Chapter Two:

cue-159
00:10:30.220 --> 00:10:31.340
Learning to Pray.

cue-160
00:10:34.160 --> 00:10:35.430
Can prayer be learned?

cue-161
00:10:36.460 --> 00:10:39.470
Isn't true prayer meant to flow freely
from the spirit?

cue-162
00:10:40.580 --> 00:10:43.720
John the Baptist gave his disciples a set
form of prayer,

cue-163
00:10:44.340 --> 00:10:48.020
and the disciples of Jesus also asked him
to teach them to pray.

cue-164
00:10:49.100 --> 00:10:53.480
They did not often ask him for things, and
when they did, they were often

cue-165
00:10:53.480 --> 00:10:54.120
mistaken.

cue-166
00:10:55.000 --> 00:10:57.060
Yet here they asked for something right.

cue-167
00:10:58.300 --> 00:10:59.200
Why did they ask?

cue-168
00:11:00.020 --> 00:11:05.020
Seeing Jesus pray stirred in them a desire
to pray as he did. But when

cue-169
00:11:05.020 --> 00:11:09.760
they tried, they realized they did not
know how. They felt the

cue-170
00:11:09.760 --> 00:11:14.120
need for some form to help them express
what was in their hearts to God.

cue-171
00:11:15.030 --> 00:11:17.220
They even pointed to the example of John.

cue-172
00:11:18.220 --> 00:11:23.180
People still do this, looking for forms
instead of seeking a living spirit

cue-173
00:11:23.180 --> 00:11:23.700
of prayer.

cue-174
00:11:24.640 --> 00:11:27.280
Forms are easier than praying from the
heart.

cue-175
00:11:28.100 --> 00:11:33.000
Repeating prayers on beads is easier than
speaking freely and honestly to

cue-176
00:11:33.000 --> 00:11:37.400
God. A prayer book can help those who
struggle to find words.

cue-177
00:11:38.600 --> 00:11:42.600
Such prayers can be sincere, and they can
truly help devotion.

cue-178
00:11:43.800 --> 00:11:47.620
In fact, this kind of prayer often needs
to be learned from others.

cue-179
00:11:48.760 --> 00:11:51.660
But this kind of prayer is often repeated
without thought.

cue-180
00:11:52.840 --> 00:11:57.380
Some repeat set prayers, while others are
unfamiliar with written prayers

cue-181
00:11:57.380 --> 00:11:57.920
altogether.

cue-182
00:11:59.080 --> 00:12:01.140
Most people begin praying with forms.

cue-183
00:12:01.800 --> 00:12:05.540
Many remember the simple, sincere prayers
they learned as children,

cue-184
00:12:06.280 --> 00:12:09.020
spoken with reverence and wonder at their
mother's

cue-185
00:12:09.020 --> 00:12:12.740
side.Personality in prayer.

cue-186
00:12:14.840 --> 00:12:18.200
It is not the prayers of others that make
someone a person of prayer.

cue-187
00:12:18.880 --> 00:12:23.520
True prayer, the kind that is effective,
is personal, close, and genuine.

cue-188
00:12:24.380 --> 00:12:29.340
Hannah said that she poured out her soul
before God. That is prayer, but

cue-189
00:12:29.340 --> 00:12:30.400
it is not the whole of it.

cue-190
00:12:31.030 --> 00:12:34.980
Listening and receiving from God are just
as important as speaking.

cue-191
00:12:36.100 --> 00:12:38.280
Saul of Tarsus had prayed from his youth,

cue-192
00:12:38.900 --> 00:12:43.340
but he did not truly pray until he met the
risen Lord on the Damascus road.

cue-193
00:12:44.540 --> 00:12:49.100
From Heaven's point of view, all that had
changed in him was summed up in the words,

cue-194
00:12:49.100 --> 00:12:50.820
"Look, he is praying."

cue-195
00:12:52.050 --> 00:12:55.990
The secret of Elijah's power in prayer was
that he truly prayed.

cue-196
00:12:57.010 --> 00:12:59.600
He did not just say words, he meant them.

cue-197
00:13:00.320 --> 00:13:01.890
His whole heart was involved.

cue-198
00:13:02.800 --> 00:13:04.880
He deeply desired what he asked for,

cue-199
00:13:05.540 --> 00:13:08.020
and he spoke with sincerity and passion.

cue-200
00:13:09.180 --> 00:13:12.860
This raises the question, can this kind of
prayer be taught?

cue-201
00:13:14.420 --> 00:13:16.380
It is this kind of prayer that is
effective.

cue-202
00:13:17.080 --> 00:13:21.340
Mere routine in worship or reading words
written by others without understanding

cue-203
00:13:21.940 --> 00:13:26.900
is not pleasing to God and does not help
people. Such prayers become

cue-204
00:13:26.900 --> 00:13:31.820
empty repetition. Much prayer, as far as
we can see, seems to have

cue-205
00:13:31.820 --> 00:13:32.500
no effect.

cue-206
00:13:33.510 --> 00:13:37.920
There may be many prayers offered, but
their value is not in how many there are.

cue-207
00:13:38.840 --> 00:13:41.860
Prayer cannot be measured by numbers or by
time.

cue-208
00:13:42.570 --> 00:13:45.240
The real issue is not quantity, but depth.

cue-209
00:13:46.020 --> 00:13:50.980
Prayer is measured by sincerity and
intensity. Some prayers are full

cue-210
00:13:50.980 --> 00:13:53.020
of feeling, yet seem unanswered.

cue-211
00:13:53.700 --> 00:13:58.640
At other times, we know we should pray
deeply, but we feel unable to do so.

cue-212
00:13:59.320 --> 00:14:00.780
We do not know how to pray.

cue-213
00:14:02.300 --> 00:14:03.700
Prayer learned by praying.

cue-214
00:14:05.540 --> 00:14:10.500
The only way to learn to pray is by
actually praying. No careful

cue-215
00:14:10.500 --> 00:14:14.500
reasoning or theory about prayer has ever
taught a person how to pray.

cue-216
00:14:15.600 --> 00:14:20.120
There are many questions about prayer, but
for the one who truly prays, these

cue-217
00:14:20.120 --> 00:14:25.100
questions are answered through experience,
through answered prayer, and the joy

cue-218
00:14:25.100 --> 00:14:26.060
of knowing God.

cue-219
00:14:27.220 --> 00:14:31.220
We do not know what we should pray for as
we ought, and if we wait until we

cue-220
00:14:31.220 --> 00:14:33.820
understand everything, we will never
begin.

cue-221
00:14:34.560 --> 00:14:37.620
We live by faith, and we walk by faith.

cue-222
00:14:38.560 --> 00:14:43.459
As has been observed, we understand very
little about the world around us, about

cue-223
00:14:43.460 --> 00:14:46.780
things like water, light, gravity, or
electricity.

cue-224
00:14:47.880 --> 00:14:52.840
Yet we still use them every day. Our lack
of full understanding does

cue-225
00:14:52.840 --> 00:14:57.620
not stop us from benefiting from them. In
the same way, we learn by

cue-226
00:14:57.620 --> 00:15:00.020
doing. We discover through practice.

cue-227
00:15:00.740 --> 00:15:05.120
Even if someone knew everything about
prayer in theory, without actually

cue-228
00:15:05.120 --> 00:15:08.240
praying, they would never truly learn how
to pray.

cue-229
00:15:10.060 --> 00:15:14.060
There have been people who became powerful
in prayer, and they learned how to

cue-230
00:15:14.060 --> 00:15:18.590
pray. At one time, they were like others
in their prayer life,

cue-231
00:15:18.590 --> 00:15:21.960
but they grew strong with God and saw
answers.

cue-232
00:15:23.040 --> 00:15:26.209
In every case, there was a turning point
of God's grace,

cue-233
00:15:26.980 --> 00:15:31.200
but it was through continued discipline
and practice that they discovered the

cue-234
00:15:31.200 --> 00:15:32.730
secret of spiritual power.

cue-235
00:15:33.790 --> 00:15:38.500
They were known as people of God because
they were people of prayer. Some were even

cue-236
00:15:38.500 --> 00:15:43.140
given names that reflected this, like
Praying John, Praying Mary,

cue-237
00:15:43.140 --> 00:15:46.000
Praying Bramwell, and Praying Hyde.

cue-238
00:15:47.020 --> 00:15:49.120
Early Methodists were strong in prayer.

cue-239
00:15:49.920 --> 00:15:53.360
Through prayer, they helped bring
spiritual change to England.

cue-240
00:15:54.300 --> 00:15:59.140
Through prayer, they fought against evil
and shook the gates of hell and saw God's

cue-241
00:15:59.140 --> 00:16:00.040
power at work.

cue-242
00:16:01.100 --> 00:16:02.380
How did they learn to pray?

cue-243
00:16:03.000 --> 00:16:07.740
They learned by praying often. They did
not just talk about prayer, they prayed.

cue-244
00:16:07.740 --> 00:16:10.660
They did not argue about it, they prayed.

cue-245
00:16:12.760 --> 00:16:13.900
Trained in prayer.

cue-246
00:16:16.080 --> 00:16:18.250
Prayer reaches both extremes.

cue-247
00:16:19.120 --> 00:16:24.080
It is so simple that even a child can
pray, and yet so deep that

cue-248
00:16:24.080 --> 00:16:26.580
only a childlike heart can truly pray.

cue-249
00:16:27.850 --> 00:16:31.460
A well-known hymn by Montgomery expresses
this truth clearly.

cue-250
00:16:32.340 --> 00:16:34.860
Prayer is the soul's sincere desire,

cue-251
00:16:35.580 --> 00:16:40.300
uttered or unexpressed, the motion of a
hidden fire that trembles in the breast.

cue-252
00:16:41.340 --> 00:16:46.200
Prayer is the simplest form of speech that
infant lips can try.

cue-253
00:16:46.200 --> 00:16:50.700
Prayer the sublimest strains that reach
the Majesty on high.

cue-254
00:16:52.260 --> 00:16:53.240
That is deeply true.

cue-255
00:16:53.840 --> 00:16:55.700
A simple cry brings God near.

cue-256
00:16:56.340 --> 00:16:58.700
A cry is stronger than carefully crafted
words.

cue-257
00:16:59.650 --> 00:17:01.580
The Pharisee prayed only to himself.

cue-258
00:17:02.200 --> 00:17:05.860
His prayers stayed stuck in his own pride
and empty thoughts.

cue-259
00:17:06.740 --> 00:17:09.180
But the tax collector cried out and was
heard.

cue-260
00:17:09.940 --> 00:17:14.660
We are not thinking about quick prayers in
moments of crisis, but about a steady

cue-261
00:17:14.660 --> 00:17:15.500
life of prayer.

cue-262
00:17:16.740 --> 00:17:20.560
This kind of prayer comes through
training, and no discipline is more

cue-263
00:17:20.560 --> 00:17:21.100
demanding.

cue-264
00:17:21.980 --> 00:17:26.200
Coleridge said that such prayer is the
highest use of the human heart's strength,

cue-265
00:17:26.880 --> 00:17:31.850
requiring the full focus of all a person's
abilities. He believed that

cue-266
00:17:31.850 --> 00:17:35.880
most worldly and even learned people are
not able to truly

cue-267
00:17:35.880 --> 00:17:40.800
pray. To pray as God desires is the
greatest work a person can

cue-268
00:17:40.800 --> 00:17:41.720
do on Earth.

cue-269
00:17:43.400 --> 00:17:47.760
Such a life of prayer has a cost. It
requires time.

cue-270
00:17:47.960 --> 00:17:52.920
Quick, rushed prayers or repeated words
spoken without thought will never

cue-271
00:17:52.920 --> 00:17:54.660
make a person strong in prayer.

cue-272
00:17:55.740 --> 00:18:00.140
To become skilled in any craft, people
give many hours each day to

cue-273
00:18:00.140 --> 00:18:04.940
practice. In the same way, our Lord rose
early in the morning to

cue-274
00:18:04.940 --> 00:18:08.920
pray, and at times, he spent the whole
night in prayer.

cue-275
00:18:10.100 --> 00:18:13.750
Those who have been strong in prayer have
given much time to it daily.

cue-276
00:18:14.600 --> 00:18:19.190
It may feel difficult to think about such
examples.In our busy lives,

cue-277
00:18:19.190 --> 00:18:21.800
we often feel there is no time to pray.

cue-278
00:18:22.900 --> 00:18:27.720
But without giving time, real, regular
time, we will never learn.

cue-279
00:18:28.820 --> 00:18:33.480
Surely it should be possible to give God
one hour out of each day. At the very

cue-280
00:18:33.480 --> 00:18:38.060
least, we can begin by setting aside a
fixed time each day for prayer.

cue-281
00:18:39.230 --> 00:18:42.250
We must make a serious decision to learn
how to pray,

cue-282
00:18:42.940 --> 00:18:47.860
to pray with all our heart and strength,
with both mind and will,

cue-283
00:18:47.900 --> 00:18:52.500
to truly believe that God hears us through
Christ and will act according to His

cue-284
00:18:52.500 --> 00:18:56.920
will. This is one of the greatest
achievements of the Christian life on

cue-285
00:18:56.920 --> 00:18:57.200
Earth.

cue-286
00:18:58.420 --> 00:19:01.280
Teach us to pray, O Lord, we ask you.

cue-287
00:19:02.800 --> 00:19:07.460
The praying spirit breathe, the watching
power impart, from all entanglements

cue-288
00:19:07.460 --> 00:19:12.340
beneath, call off my anxious heart. My
feeble mind sustain, by

cue-289
00:19:12.340 --> 00:19:17.340
worldly thoughts oppressed, appear and bid
me turn again to my eternal rest.

cue-290
00:19:19.240 --> 00:19:22.300
When you feel the strain of discipline,
remember these words.

cue-291
00:19:23.399 --> 00:19:27.160
Thou art oft most present, Lord, in weak,
distracted prayer.

cue-292
00:19:27.810 --> 00:19:31.500
A sinner out of heart with self most often
finds thee there.

cue-293
00:19:32.240 --> 00:19:36.960
For prayer that humbles sets the soul from
all delusions free and

cue-294
00:19:36.960 --> 00:19:40.540
teaches it how utterly, dear Lord, it
hangs on thee.

cue-295
00:19:43.440 --> 00:19:44.200
Chapter Three:

cue-296
00:19:45.000 --> 00:19:46.280
Praying in Secret.

cue-297
00:19:49.100 --> 00:19:53.120
If prayer is the greatest thing we can do
on Earth, then it requires a discipline

cue-298
00:19:53.120 --> 00:19:57.740
that matches its power. The life of prayer
has its own rules and demands.

cue-299
00:19:57.740 --> 00:20:02.660
Only those who are determined and steady
in heart will enter into it. Even

cue-300
00:20:02.660 --> 00:20:07.320
strong people can become worn out by deep
thinking. Focus takes more

cue-301
00:20:07.320 --> 00:20:08.740
effort than physical work.

cue-302
00:20:09.640 --> 00:20:14.600
Discipline limits our freedom and trains
the mind to pay attention. It

cue-303
00:20:14.600 --> 00:20:19.500
is harder to understand than to simply
act, and quiet meditation can be more

cue-304
00:20:19.500 --> 00:20:21.340
demanding than active service.

cue-305
00:20:22.360 --> 00:20:24.860
Many people do not pray because of what it
costs.

cue-306
00:20:25.920 --> 00:20:30.880
The cost is not mainly in intense moments
of pleading, but in daily faithfulness

cue-307
00:20:30.880 --> 00:20:31.500
to prayer.

cue-308
00:20:32.580 --> 00:20:34.740
This is the true test of devotion.

cue-309
00:20:35.660 --> 00:20:37.930
Nothing in the Christian life is harder to
keep up.

cue-310
00:20:39.020 --> 00:20:43.420
Some people dislike the idea that prayer
requires discipline and deep

cue-311
00:20:43.420 --> 00:20:48.260
effort. They do not pray this way, and
they would not want their children to

cue-312
00:20:48.260 --> 00:20:50.100
beg and cry for what they need.

cue-313
00:20:51.170 --> 00:20:52.080
That may be so,

cue-314
00:20:52.700 --> 00:20:55.820
but it is clear they do not pray in this
way either.

cue-315
00:20:57.040 --> 00:21:01.340
And comparing prayer to children asking
for things does not fully explain

cue-316
00:21:01.340 --> 00:21:06.320
it. The life of prayer is a place of
learning for those who truly want to

cue-317
00:21:06.360 --> 00:21:06.680
pray.

cue-318
00:21:08.240 --> 00:21:13.020
Those who come to learn are disciples.
They place themselves under the guidance

cue-319
00:21:13.020 --> 00:21:14.640
of the one they want to learn from,

cue-320
00:21:15.280 --> 00:21:19.140
and the first requirement for learning is
a willing and teachable spirit.

cue-321
00:21:20.180 --> 00:21:25.160
Our Lord has full authority to teach, and
He is both our example and our

cue-322
00:21:25.160 --> 00:21:25.920
teacher.

cue-323
00:21:26.820 --> 00:21:28.810
There is no higher authority than Him.

cue-324
00:21:29.800 --> 00:21:31.920
When we ask Him to teach us how to pray,

cue-325
00:21:32.540 --> 00:21:35.920
we give our minds and hearts to His
instruction,

cue-326
00:21:35.960 --> 00:21:40.700
and we commit ourselves to follow Him with
faithful and trusting obedience.

cue-327
00:21:42.920 --> 00:21:44.860
What does our Lord teach us about prayer?

cue-328
00:21:47.440 --> 00:21:51.420
One of the first things He teaches is that
there should be a special place for

cue-329
00:21:51.420 --> 00:21:51.760
prayer.

cue-330
00:21:52.520 --> 00:21:56.920
It is true that the whole Earth belongs to
the Lord, and there is no place where

cue-331
00:21:56.920 --> 00:21:58.260
prayer cannot be heard.

cue-332
00:21:59.300 --> 00:22:02.140
God desires that people pray everywhere.

cue-333
00:22:03.360 --> 00:22:06.540
Wherever we are, He is near, not far away.

cue-334
00:22:07.640 --> 00:22:11.920
Wherever there is a praying heart, that
place becomes God's sanctuary.

cue-335
00:22:12.960 --> 00:22:17.860
Yet Jesus Himself made it a habit to go to
a quiet, private place to pray.

cue-336
00:22:18.940 --> 00:22:21.620
He needed times of silence and separation.

cue-337
00:22:22.540 --> 00:22:24.320
He taught His disciples the same.

cue-338
00:22:25.160 --> 00:22:30.140
When you pray, do not be like the
hypocrites. They love to pray, standing in

cue-339
00:22:30.140 --> 00:22:34.900
public places so others can see them.
Truly, they have already

cue-340
00:22:34.900 --> 00:22:36.099
received their reward.

cue-341
00:22:36.740 --> 00:22:41.480
But when you pray, go into your room,
close the door, and pray to your

cue-342
00:22:41.480 --> 00:22:46.300
Father in secret, and your Father, who
sees what is done in secret,

cue-343
00:22:46.300 --> 00:22:47.190
will reward you.

cue-344
00:22:48.540 --> 00:22:53.420
Prayer may be offered anywhere, but our
Lord teaches us the importance of having a

cue-345
00:22:53.420 --> 00:22:56.640
private place set apart for meeting with
God.

cue-346
00:22:58.440 --> 00:23:01.600
Why does He insist on a private room and a
closed door?

cue-347
00:23:02.540 --> 00:23:05.970
The first reason is that God desires
honesty in prayer.

cue-348
00:23:06.940 --> 00:23:09.160
Hypocrites do not pray in secret.

cue-349
00:23:09.820 --> 00:23:14.660
Prayers that are only for show need an
audience. They are meant to be heard by

cue-350
00:23:14.660 --> 00:23:19.240
people, and their reward is in well-spoken
words, an appearance of

cue-351
00:23:19.240 --> 00:23:22.340
sincerity, and a reputation for being
religious.

cue-352
00:23:23.600 --> 00:23:25.550
But these things mean nothing to God.

cue-353
00:23:26.230 --> 00:23:28.300
They cannot stand in His presence.

cue-354
00:23:29.460 --> 00:23:32.880
True prayer is between the soul and God
alone.

cue-355
00:23:34.260 --> 00:23:36.160
The silent spaces of the soul.

cue-356
00:23:38.520 --> 00:23:40.720
The soul needs quiet and stillness.

cue-357
00:23:41.400 --> 00:23:46.260
It is in these silent moments that we
learn to pray. There, alone with

cue-358
00:23:46.260 --> 00:23:51.160
God, our Lord tells us to pray to our
Father, who is unseen and who sees

cue-359
00:23:51.160 --> 00:23:51.540
all.

cue-360
00:23:52.380 --> 00:23:54.900
There is no greater test than being alone.

cue-361
00:23:55.660 --> 00:23:59.100
In silence and solitude, many people feel
afraid.

cue-362
00:23:59.989 --> 00:24:04.960
The heart often pulls back from being
alone with God, who sees everything.

cue-363
00:24:04.960 --> 00:24:06.440
Who can remain in His presence?

cue-364
00:24:07.070 --> 00:24:10.680
Who can live with God, who is pure and
without any darkness?

cue-365
00:24:11.900 --> 00:24:16.780
To come before Him in this way, hearts
must be pure and conduct must be clean.

cue-366
00:24:17.900 --> 00:24:22.619
Yet if most people spent even half an hour
each day alone with God in a quiet

cue-367
00:24:22.620 --> 00:24:22.970
place,

cue-368
00:24:23.700 --> 00:24:28.636
it would completely change their lives.For
this kind of prayer,

cue-369
00:24:29.296 --> 00:24:31.936
every part of the soul must be awake and
alert.

cue-370
00:24:32.956 --> 00:24:37.856
When our Lord took Peter, James, and John
with him to pray in a quiet place,

cue-371
00:24:37.856 --> 00:24:39.896
they struggled to stay awake.

cue-372
00:24:40.756 --> 00:24:45.726
This happened both on the mountain of
glory and in the garden of suffering. Only

cue-373
00:24:45.726 --> 00:24:50.016
when they were fully awake did they see
his glory and understand his

cue-374
00:24:50.016 --> 00:24:54.856
sorrow. There are quiet places where
people do not speak,

cue-375
00:24:54.856 --> 00:24:56.296
yet they still fall asleep.

cue-376
00:24:57.236 --> 00:25:01.936
Daydreaming is not meditation, and being
half asleep is not prayer.

cue-377
00:25:03.096 --> 00:25:08.056
The secret place of prayer requires the
full attention of both mind and heart.

cue-378
00:25:09.556 --> 00:25:11.256
Bless the Lord, O my soul,

cue-379
00:25:11.956 --> 00:25:14.696
and all that is within me, bless his holy
name.

cue-380
00:25:16.316 --> 00:25:20.216
Just as in praise, so in prayer the whole
person is involved.

cue-381
00:25:21.296 --> 00:25:25.236
There is an important difference between
private prayer and prayer with others.

cue-382
00:25:25.996 --> 00:25:29.536
Both bring their own kind of blessing, but
they are not the same.

cue-383
00:25:30.376 --> 00:25:35.036
Prayer with others is less demanding. The
sense of fellowship gives

cue-384
00:25:35.036 --> 00:25:37.696
courage and helps people express
themselves.

cue-385
00:25:38.496 --> 00:25:43.416
Praying together can feel supportive, but
it can also lead people to rely on others

cue-386
00:25:43.416 --> 00:25:45.056
to do the thinking for them.

cue-387
00:25:46.236 --> 00:25:49.576
In private prayer, the soul stands alone
before God.

cue-388
00:25:50.316 --> 00:25:55.156
Thoughts are personal, prayers are sincere
and original, and motives are

cue-389
00:25:55.156 --> 00:25:55.816
examined.

cue-390
00:25:56.736 --> 00:26:01.416
Prayer with others builds fellowship, but
private prayer shapes and strengthens the

cue-391
00:26:01.416 --> 00:26:01.976
individual.

cue-392
00:26:03.196 --> 00:26:07.836
Who can measure the impact of spending
even one hour a day alone with

cue-393
00:26:07.836 --> 00:26:08.236
God?

cue-394
00:26:11.256 --> 00:26:12.476
The hill of the Lord.

cue-395
00:26:15.116 --> 00:26:18.816
The way into God's presence is not open to
everyone without care.

cue-396
00:26:19.596 --> 00:26:24.196
The private place a person enters may be
their own, but it becomes holy because God

cue-397
00:26:24.196 --> 00:26:24.756
is there.

cue-398
00:26:26.216 --> 00:26:29.676
To someone with a worldly mind, there is
no sense of his presence.

cue-399
00:26:30.536 --> 00:26:33.576
It is the person who truly seeks God who
finds him.

cue-400
00:26:34.776 --> 00:26:39.026
There are some who do not receive an
answer. Some people cannot truly pray.

cue-401
00:26:40.136 --> 00:26:44.516
James says that certain people should not
expect to receive anything from the Lord.

cue-402
00:26:45.456 --> 00:26:50.456
Even before Christ taught about prayer,
the psalmist said, "If I hold on to

cue-403
00:26:50.456 --> 00:26:52.856
sin in my heart, the Lord will not hear
me,"

cue-404
00:26:53.476 --> 00:26:55.226
Psalm sixty-six eighteen.

cue-405
00:26:56.456 --> 00:27:00.156
In that private place, there is both
judgment and grace.

cue-406
00:27:00.856 --> 00:27:02.016
God sees everything.

cue-407
00:27:02.716 --> 00:27:07.696
Sins we have forgotten come back to mind,
and hidden things are fully exposed before

cue-408
00:27:07.696 --> 00:27:07.916
him.

cue-409
00:27:08.856 --> 00:27:11.236
Yet his throne of grace is there too,

cue-410
00:27:11.856 --> 00:27:13.576
or no one would dare come near.

cue-411
00:27:14.596 --> 00:27:19.346
Anyone who wants to enter God's presence
and remain there must truly desire

cue-412
00:27:19.346 --> 00:27:23.016
him and be willing to live honestly in his
light.

cue-413
00:27:24.836 --> 00:27:28.556
Our Lord placed strong emphasis on having
a forgiving spirit.

cue-414
00:27:29.596 --> 00:27:34.136
More than anything else, refusing to
forgive from the heart blocks the way into

cue-415
00:27:34.136 --> 00:27:35.656
God's presence in prayer.

cue-416
00:27:36.716 --> 00:27:41.076
God will not accept any offering until we
are first made right with others.

cue-417
00:27:42.316 --> 00:27:46.296
If you are offering your gift at the altar
and remember that your brother has

cue-418
00:27:46.296 --> 00:27:47.296
something against you,

cue-419
00:27:48.156 --> 00:27:49.256
leave your gift there.

cue-420
00:27:49.936 --> 00:27:54.596
First, go and be reconciled to your
brother, and then come and offer your

cue-421
00:27:54.596 --> 00:27:59.056
gift. Jesus also connected faith in prayer
with

cue-422
00:27:59.056 --> 00:27:59.696
forgiveness.

cue-423
00:28:00.736 --> 00:28:04.976
Whatever you ask in prayer, believe that
you have received it, and it will be

cue-424
00:28:04.976 --> 00:28:05.476
yours.

cue-425
00:28:06.656 --> 00:28:11.516
And when you stand praying, forgive anyone
you have anything against so that your

cue-426
00:28:11.516 --> 00:28:16.416
Father in heaven may forgive you. But if
you do not forgive others,

cue-427
00:28:16.416 --> 00:28:18.916
your Father will not forgive your sins.

cue-428
00:28:20.156 --> 00:28:24.916
Why did he stress forgiveness so strongly?
For the same reason the law and the

cue-429
00:28:24.916 --> 00:28:26.716
prophets stressed righteousness.

cue-430
00:28:27.736 --> 00:28:32.536
Those who come to a holy God must seek to
be holy. Those who come to a

cue-431
00:28:32.536 --> 00:28:34.716
merciful God must show mercy.

cue-432
00:28:35.496 --> 00:28:40.176
Anyone who asks for grace must also
believe in it and extend it to

cue-433
00:28:40.176 --> 00:28:40.556
others.

cue-434
00:28:42.736 --> 00:28:44.056
Thine inner chamber.

cue-435
00:28:46.856 --> 00:28:51.496
No one should feel discouraged about
beginning to pray. Just as schools teach

cue-436
00:28:51.496 --> 00:28:55.056
step by step, learning to pray also grows
over time.

cue-437
00:28:56.496 --> 00:29:01.415
Those who became strong in prayer and
spent hours each day alone with God all

cue-438
00:29:01.416 --> 00:29:06.136
began as beginners. They grew little by
little. For our

cue-439
00:29:06.136 --> 00:29:11.016
comfort, remember this: the place we enter
is our own inner room,

cue-440
00:29:11.016 --> 00:29:14.236
and the God who meets us there is our
Father.

cue-441
00:29:15.516 --> 00:29:19.656
Many years ago, a young girl quietly came
into my room where I was staying.

cue-442
00:29:20.716 --> 00:29:23.796
She happily talked about the small joys of
her world.

cue-443
00:29:24.756 --> 00:29:29.226
When I asked if her father was awake, she
looked at me with bright respect and said,

cue-444
00:29:30.156 --> 00:29:33.576
"Oh, my daddy always talks with God in the
drawing room before breakfast."

cue-445
00:29:34.636 --> 00:29:36.596
Happy father, happy child,

cue-446
00:29:37.736 --> 00:29:38.536
happy God.

cue-447
00:29:41.856 --> 00:29:42.536
Chapter four:

cue-448
00:29:43.276 --> 00:29:45.296
The inner room and the closed door.

cue-449
00:29:47.216 --> 00:29:51.916
But when you pray, go into your room,
close the door, and pray to your Father,

cue-450
00:29:51.916 --> 00:29:52.796
who is unseen.

cue-451
00:29:53.726 --> 00:29:57.156
Then your Father, who sees what is done in
secret, will reward you.

cue-452
00:29:59.086 --> 00:30:02.716
There are two main difficulties when we
try to follow this command.

cue-453
00:30:03.396 --> 00:30:06.616
First, many people do not have a true
inner room.

cue-454
00:30:07.236 --> 00:30:12.236
There is no place in their lives set apart
for quiet and privacy. They may not

cue-455
00:30:12.236 --> 00:30:16.556
have a room of their own, and even if they
did, they often have no free time.

cue-456
00:30:17.756 --> 00:30:22.696
Closing a door does not always create real
quiet, either outwardly or

cue-457
00:30:22.696 --> 00:30:23.156
inwardly.

cue-458
00:30:24.246 --> 00:30:29.156
We know that even locked doors cannot
fully keep things out.Thoughts can

cue-459
00:30:29.156 --> 00:30:34.076
pass through more easily than sound, and
the enemy is more subtle than any

cue-460
00:30:34.076 --> 00:30:34.976
human invention.

cue-461
00:30:36.016 --> 00:30:40.036
Those who have practiced private prayer
know that there are many distractions and

cue-462
00:30:40.036 --> 00:30:43.456
struggles waiting at the doorway of the
soul's quiet place.

cue-463
00:30:44.936 --> 00:30:46.956
Where shall we find the secret place?

cue-464
00:30:49.376 --> 00:30:53.196
My goal is not to give strict
instructions, but to offer simple

cue-465
00:30:53.196 --> 00:30:58.156
suggestions. Books on prayer have often
felt more discouraging than helpful to

cue-466
00:30:58.156 --> 00:31:01.036
me. They can be too rigid or too
demanding.

cue-467
00:31:01.756 --> 00:31:05.196
Instead of helping, they sometimes make
prayer feel harder.

cue-468
00:31:06.396 --> 00:31:08.376
I want to speak openly and personally.

cue-469
00:31:09.056 --> 00:31:11.916
All my life, I have wanted to learn how to
pray.

cue-470
00:31:13.016 --> 00:31:17.576
With that desire, I have tried many
different ways and approaches to prayer,

cue-471
00:31:18.336 --> 00:31:19.916
some helpful, some not.

cue-472
00:31:21.056 --> 00:31:21.856
Without pride,

cue-473
00:31:22.476 --> 00:31:25.666
I want to share in humility what I have
learned.

cue-474
00:31:26.796 --> 00:31:31.456
I speak only from my own experience. I do
not judge how others pray,

cue-475
00:31:31.456 --> 00:31:36.216
criticize their guidance, or question
their experiences. I will speak

cue-476
00:31:36.216 --> 00:31:40.636
plainly, and you can decide for yourself
what is helpful.

cue-477
00:31:41.496 --> 00:31:43.786
Let us begin with the problem of privacy.

cue-478
00:31:44.476 --> 00:31:48.836
Many followers of Christ have no place
where they can go to pray alone. They

cue-479
00:31:48.836 --> 00:31:52.336
live, sleep, and work with others all the
time.

cue-480
00:31:53.056 --> 00:31:55.136
They cannot easily get away from people.

cue-481
00:31:55.996 --> 00:32:00.156
Does this not show that the doors of God's
house should always be open?

cue-482
00:32:01.016 --> 00:32:06.016
One Monday morning, a man who was seeking
God stopped me on the main street after

cue-483
00:32:06.016 --> 00:32:11.015
I had preached the day before. There were
several churches nearby, but all of them

cue-484
00:32:11.016 --> 00:32:11.516
were locked.

cue-485
00:32:12.276 --> 00:32:17.076
We had to go to another church just to
find a quiet place to pray. Church doors

cue-486
00:32:17.076 --> 00:32:21.956
should always be open. Even so, that alone
does not fully meet the

cue-487
00:32:21.956 --> 00:32:22.276
need.

cue-488
00:32:23.166 --> 00:32:27.956
The secret place of prayer should be part
of daily life. It should be something we

cue-489
00:32:27.956 --> 00:32:31.416
carry with us, a regular part of how we
live each day.

cue-490
00:32:32.916 --> 00:32:37.536
A place must be found where we can meet
with God. A heart that truly longs for

cue-491
00:32:37.536 --> 00:32:39.015
Him will find a way.

cue-492
00:32:40.416 --> 00:32:42.896
It may be outdoors or in some quiet
corner,

cue-493
00:32:43.496 --> 00:32:45.756
but there will be a place set apart
within.

cue-494
00:32:46.976 --> 00:32:51.356
If this is not possible, the soul must
learn to create a quiet space within

cue-495
00:32:51.356 --> 00:32:51.916
itself,

cue-496
00:32:52.716 --> 00:32:54.296
even when others are nearby,

cue-497
00:32:54.976 --> 00:32:56.416
and be alone with God.

cue-498
00:32:57.456 --> 00:33:01.016
Still, having a private place for prayer
is a great blessing.

cue-499
00:33:02.016 --> 00:33:04.556
God desires that people pray everywhere,

cue-500
00:33:05.236 --> 00:33:09.516
but His deepest presence is often found in
quiet and lonely places.

cue-501
00:33:10.776 --> 00:33:13.456
There, He meets with us closely and
personally,

cue-502
00:33:14.136 --> 00:33:17.096
speaking with us as a friend speaks with a
friend.

cue-503
00:33:19.296 --> 00:33:21.136
How can we secure the closed door?

cue-504
00:33:23.196 --> 00:33:26.596
How can we keep the world out and stop our
minds from wandering?

cue-505
00:33:27.696 --> 00:33:32.596
Focusing the mind is difficult in any
task, but it is especially hard in private

cue-506
00:33:32.596 --> 00:33:33.016
prayer.

cue-507
00:33:34.036 --> 00:33:38.436
There are many distractions, thoughts that
stir the conscience, memories that

cue-508
00:33:38.436 --> 00:33:42.416
interrupt, and concerns that press in
during this quiet time.

cue-509
00:33:43.636 --> 00:33:46.396
Simple steps can help create outward
quiet.

cue-510
00:33:47.336 --> 00:33:50.206
Some people use small signals to avoid
interruption.

cue-511
00:33:51.236 --> 00:33:54.596
But even if the room is quiet, the mind
can still wander.

cue-512
00:33:55.536 --> 00:33:58.816
Being alone physically is not enough if
our thoughts are scattered.

cue-513
00:34:00.036 --> 00:34:03.495
So the real question is how to quiet the
mind and heart.

cue-514
00:34:04.516 --> 00:34:07.236
The closed door must also be within us.

cue-515
00:34:08.236 --> 00:34:12.596
We must gently turn our attention back to
God again and again

cue-516
00:34:13.316 --> 00:34:14.916
and keep our focus on Him.

cue-517
00:34:16.036 --> 00:34:20.156
Only then can we truly be alone with Him
in prayer.

cue-518
00:34:20.456 --> 00:34:25.016
Attention is a choice of the will.
Concentration is keeping that attention

cue-519
00:34:25.016 --> 00:34:29.316
fixed on one thing. The will can be
trained, and the ability to

cue-520
00:34:29.316 --> 00:34:33.976
concentrate can grow. A trained mind
learns to focus, to think

cue-521
00:34:33.976 --> 00:34:38.856
clearly, and to stay fixed on what
matters. Through patience, the

cue-522
00:34:38.856 --> 00:34:42.656
soul is strengthened, and through
discipline, the mind is shaped.

cue-523
00:34:43.576 --> 00:34:45.976
God is present in the secret place,

cue-524
00:34:47.236 --> 00:34:52.136
so the first step is to recognize that He
is there. Call every

cue-525
00:34:52.136 --> 00:34:57.096
part of your mind and body to remember and
become aware of His presence.

cue-526
00:34:57.096 --> 00:34:58.656
Hold firmly to this truth.

cue-527
00:34:59.476 --> 00:35:04.316
Do not allow distractions, do not give in
to wandering thoughts, and do not let your

cue-528
00:35:04.316 --> 00:35:05.256
mind drift.

cue-529
00:35:06.176 --> 00:35:11.056
Every part of you must be awake and ready.
The apostles on the mountain were

cue-530
00:35:11.056 --> 00:35:11.496
sleepy,

cue-531
00:35:12.136 --> 00:35:15.036
but when they fully woke up, they saw His
glory.

cue-532
00:35:16.236 --> 00:35:21.116
Daydreaming is not meditation. Drowsiness
is not thinking. Sitting in

cue-533
00:35:21.116 --> 00:35:23.016
dull stillness is not prayer.

cue-534
00:35:23.836 --> 00:35:28.736
Prayer in the secret place always requires
the full attention of the whole person.

cue-535
00:35:30.396 --> 00:35:33.096
Our Lord gave His disciples a pattern for
prayer,

cue-536
00:35:33.736 --> 00:35:38.256
and it does not begin with singing or
asking, but with thinking about God.

cue-537
00:35:39.076 --> 00:35:42.616
Our Father, who is in heaven, holy is Your
name.

cue-538
00:35:43.806 --> 00:35:46.636
This is how many of the great prayers in
the Bible begin.

cue-539
00:35:47.836 --> 00:35:49.976
I have found it helpful to start this way.

cue-540
00:35:50.636 --> 00:35:55.436
I think with love and wonder about who God
is, His character, His power,

cue-541
00:35:55.436 --> 00:35:58.576
His greatness, His grace, and His glory.

cue-542
00:35:59.836 --> 00:36:03.556
As I reflect on these things, my heart
begins to grow warm.

cue-543
00:36:04.596 --> 00:36:08.996
This focus becomes like a protective wall,
keeping distractions away.

cue-544
00:36:10.236 --> 00:36:15.036
That is why prayer in the secret place
often begins with praise and thanksgiving.

cue-545
00:36:15.036 --> 00:36:19.676
It is in this place that we begin to see
the glory of the Lord.

cue-546
00:36:21.656 --> 00:36:23.516
The Word of God in the Holy Presence.

cue-547
00:36:26.296 --> 00:36:31.236
I take no book with me into the secret
place except the Bible. It is my prayer

cue-548
00:36:31.236 --> 00:36:36.052
book.I do not use outward aids like a
cross or crucifix. My

cue-549
00:36:36.052 --> 00:36:38.212
altar is within, where I meet God.

cue-550
00:36:38.932 --> 00:36:43.912
Others may have different ways, and many
people use devotional books, but I do not

cue-551
00:36:43.912 --> 00:36:45.332
even take a hymn book with me.

cue-552
00:36:46.272 --> 00:36:51.132
I use the Bible by searching its truth,
receiving its promises, and turning its

cue-553
00:36:51.132 --> 00:36:55.272
psalms and prayers into my own
thanksgiving and requests.

cue-554
00:36:56.692 --> 00:37:00.832
In that quiet place, I do not think about
criticism or analysis,

cue-555
00:37:01.492 --> 00:37:04.152
just as I do not analyze my food while
eating.

cue-556
00:37:05.312 --> 00:37:10.272
God's Word is more necessary to me than
daily food. It stirs my heart

cue-557
00:37:10.272 --> 00:37:11.982
and fills me with deep power.

cue-558
00:37:13.592 --> 00:37:18.272
The Word of God teaches us how to pray.
The position of the body should depend on

cue-559
00:37:18.272 --> 00:37:22.892
health and comfort. Kneeling is usually
helpful and shows reverence.

cue-560
00:37:23.612 --> 00:37:28.212
One friend of mine prefers to sit, placing
an empty chair beside him as a

cue-561
00:37:28.212 --> 00:37:29.832
reminder of God's presence.

cue-562
00:37:31.032 --> 00:37:35.152
While kneeling is a good habit, each
person must choose what fits their

cue-563
00:37:35.152 --> 00:37:36.892
condition of body and soul.

cue-564
00:37:38.032 --> 00:37:42.232
Still, it is right that we kneel before
the Lord our Maker.

cue-565
00:37:43.512 --> 00:37:48.512
Prayer is more than asking for things, but
even our requests should be guided by

cue-566
00:37:48.512 --> 00:37:49.302
the Holy Spirit.

cue-567
00:37:50.532 --> 00:37:54.332
I find it helpful to look back over my
daily life in God's presence.

cue-568
00:37:55.072 --> 00:37:57.092
It is there that I make my plans.

cue-569
00:37:58.652 --> 00:38:03.592
God reveals His pattern for life in His
presence. Thomas Champness

cue-570
00:38:03.592 --> 00:38:07.912
used to speak with God each morning about
his work and those he served.

cue-571
00:38:08.912 --> 00:38:13.732
God guides us quietly and personally, and
this is best understood in private

cue-572
00:38:13.732 --> 00:38:18.712
fellowship with Him. It is there that we
become sure of His will and

cue-573
00:38:18.712 --> 00:38:19.972
learn His way.

cue-574
00:38:22.092 --> 00:38:24.192
It is also the place of intercession.

cue-575
00:38:25.212 --> 00:38:29.892
Here we can speak freely with God about
others. Our family, church,

cue-576
00:38:29.892 --> 00:38:34.892
work, friendships, nation, and the world
should all be brought before Him

cue-577
00:38:34.892 --> 00:38:39.852
in sincere and trusting prayer. It is
helpful to pray for people one by

cue-578
00:38:39.852 --> 00:38:44.811
one. Leaders can pray through their lists
of names, and teachers can do

cue-579
00:38:44.812 --> 00:38:49.792
the same for those they guide. Keep a list
of people and needs to

cue-580
00:38:49.792 --> 00:38:50.812
remember in prayer.

cue-581
00:38:51.592 --> 00:38:56.432
There is no need to tell others what you
tell God. The Father sees, hears,

cue-582
00:38:56.432 --> 00:38:58.332
and knows in secret.

cue-583
00:38:59.132 --> 00:39:01.102
Leave everything in His hands.

cue-584
00:39:01.852 --> 00:39:04.371
God, who is in secret, is our Father.

cue-585
00:39:05.052 --> 00:39:09.812
Prayer is like a child speaking to a
loving parent. He knows our needs even

cue-586
00:39:09.812 --> 00:39:14.812
before we speak, and He is able to do far
more than we can ask or imagine.

cue-587
00:39:15.792 --> 00:39:18.492
So we should pray with confidence and
without doubt.

cue-588
00:39:19.452 --> 00:39:23.332
In the secret place, we learn that silence
can be better than speaking,

cue-589
00:39:23.952 --> 00:39:26.232
and listening is a vital part of prayer.

cue-590
00:39:27.412 --> 00:39:32.272
Those who speak are heard, but those who
listen begin to truly hear

cue-591
00:39:32.272 --> 00:39:32.612
God.

cue-592
00:39:33.852 --> 00:39:37.392
Of Jesus, it is written in Mark chapter
one, verse thirty-five,

cue-593
00:39:38.382 --> 00:39:43.172
"Very early in the morning, while it was
still dark, he got up, went to a

cue-594
00:39:43.172 --> 00:39:45.172
quiet place, and prayed."

cue-595
00:39:48.592 --> 00:39:49.392
Chapter five:

cue-596
00:39:50.472 --> 00:39:52.312
The Word of God and Prayer.

cue-597
00:39:54.952 --> 00:39:58.732
The Word of God brings life to the soul
and teaches us how to pray.

cue-598
00:39:59.612 --> 00:40:03.732
The psalmist speaks for all who pray when
he says there are times when the soul

cue-599
00:40:03.732 --> 00:40:05.012
feels low and weak.

cue-600
00:40:05.852 --> 00:40:09.632
"My soul clings to the dust; give me life
according to your word."

cue-601
00:40:10.892 --> 00:40:15.272
In such times, he always turns to God's
Word for help and guidance.

cue-602
00:40:16.272 --> 00:40:20.532
Paul also connects the Word of God with
prayer. He speaks of

cue-603
00:40:20.532 --> 00:40:24.502
taking the sword of the Spirit, which is
the Word of God,

cue-604
00:40:25.212 --> 00:40:28.242
and then praying always with all kinds of
prayer,

cue-605
00:40:28.932 --> 00:40:32.492
staying alert and continuing faithfully
for all believers.

cue-606
00:40:33.692 --> 00:40:38.532
This kind of watchfulness means being
diligent, patient, attentive, and

cue-607
00:40:38.532 --> 00:40:39.142
respectful.

cue-608
00:40:40.212 --> 00:40:43.112
We must search the Word if we want to
learn how to pray.

cue-609
00:40:44.152 --> 00:40:48.971
God is spirit, and those who worship Him
must worship in spirit and in

cue-610
00:40:48.971 --> 00:40:49.292
truth.

cue-611
00:40:52.012 --> 00:40:53.031
Aids to devotion.

cue-612
00:40:55.332 --> 00:41:00.012
I do not judge how others practice their
devotion. I speak only for myself.

cue-613
00:41:00.972 --> 00:41:05.952
Private prayer is so hard to keep up that
I do not criticize those who use helps

cue-614
00:41:05.952 --> 00:41:10.732
that I personally find distracting. Some
people are helped by symbols or

cue-615
00:41:10.732 --> 00:41:13.432
pictures. Many use devotional books.

cue-616
00:41:14.092 --> 00:41:19.032
Writers like Thomas à Kempis, Lancelot
Andrews, William Law, and

cue-617
00:41:19.032 --> 00:41:23.892
Andrew Murray, along with the hymns of
the church, have helped many people learn

cue-618
00:41:23.892 --> 00:41:24.412
to pray.

cue-619
00:41:25.512 --> 00:41:29.952
I value these in their place, but I do not
bring them into my inner room of prayer.

cue-620
00:41:31.622 --> 00:41:33.492
There are two dangers to avoid:

cue-621
00:41:34.132 --> 00:41:37.062
false emotion and too much mental
distraction.

cue-622
00:41:38.032 --> 00:41:41.142
One sincere believer, who was very active
in serving others,

cue-623
00:41:41.872 --> 00:41:43.532
realized he was not praying.

cue-624
00:41:44.541 --> 00:41:48.132
He decided to spend half an hour each day
in private prayer.

cue-625
00:41:49.172 --> 00:41:52.672
But after a month, he stopped because it
felt unreal.

cue-626
00:41:53.382 --> 00:41:57.872
He could not keep speaking or thinking for
that long when he felt no one was there.

cue-627
00:41:58.952 --> 00:42:02.352
Instead of sensing God's presence, he felt
an absence.

cue-628
00:42:03.692 --> 00:42:08.612
True prayer cannot be based on pretending
or forcing emotion. The heart

cue-629
00:42:08.612 --> 00:42:13.592
cannot keep up something unreal day after
day. The mind also cannot

cue-630
00:42:13.592 --> 00:42:14.912
function in emptiness.

cue-631
00:42:15.872 --> 00:42:20.712
God is present in secret, and it is His
real presence that makes that

cue-632
00:42:20.712 --> 00:42:21.412
place holy.

cue-633
00:42:22.762 --> 00:42:25.252
Worship must have both spirit and truth.

cue-634
00:42:26.252 --> 00:42:29.492
Nowhere is this more important than in the
quiet place of

cue-635
00:42:29.492 --> 00:42:34.520
prayer.The

cue-636
00:42:34.520 --> 00:42:39.419
fire of devotion is lit and strengthened
by truth, but that truth must reach the

cue-637
00:42:39.420 --> 00:42:44.320
heart. Studying spiritual things does not
always lead to real devotion.

cue-638
00:42:45.220 --> 00:42:49.540
A person can become so focused on ideas
that they miss the experience itself.

cue-639
00:42:50.680 --> 00:42:55.640
Learning about spiritual truth does not
always become a living reality. Even the

cue-640
00:42:55.640 --> 00:43:00.600
experiences of others can mislead us if we
rely on them instead of seeking

cue-641
00:43:00.600 --> 00:43:01.960
God for ourselves.

cue-642
00:43:03.140 --> 00:43:06.600
Even the Bible, if used wrongly, can
become a hindrance.

cue-643
00:43:07.400 --> 00:43:08.880
Light itself can blind.

cue-644
00:43:09.800 --> 00:43:14.600
Our Lord rebuked religious teachers
because their misuse of scripture kept

cue-645
00:43:14.600 --> 00:43:15.880
them from seeing the truth.

cue-646
00:43:16.800 --> 00:43:21.800
Things meant to help us can become
obstacles. What should guide us can trip

cue-647
00:43:21.800 --> 00:43:22.000
us.

cue-648
00:43:22.880 --> 00:43:27.820
In matters of the soul, each person must
find the help that truly leads

cue-649
00:43:27.820 --> 00:43:28.640
them to God.

cue-650
00:43:32.140 --> 00:43:33.700
The devotional use of the Bible.

cue-651
00:43:36.300 --> 00:43:39.440
Can we still take the Bible with us into
the place of prayer?

cue-652
00:43:40.520 --> 00:43:44.480
One of the greatest losses has been that
many no longer use it as a devotional

cue-653
00:43:44.480 --> 00:43:44.740
book.

cue-654
00:43:45.620 --> 00:43:49.040
A person cannot truly pray from a book
they no longer trust.

cue-655
00:43:49.930 --> 00:43:53.980
Truth is necessary both for God and for
us.

cue-656
00:43:55.220 --> 00:43:59.240
If we are to worship, we must do so in
spirit and in truth.

cue-657
00:44:00.460 --> 00:44:05.040
Some teachers often criticize the
traditional view of the Bible, yet still

cue-658
00:44:05.040 --> 00:44:06.920
claim that nothing has been lost.

cue-659
00:44:08.090 --> 00:44:12.880
They say it remains the living and
powerful word of God. They also

cue-660
00:44:12.880 --> 00:44:17.880
admit that Jesus accepted the scriptures
as they were. He found his

cue-661
00:44:17.880 --> 00:44:22.880
message in them, fed his soul on them,
and depended on them in every major moment

cue-662
00:44:22.880 --> 00:44:23.500
of his life.

cue-663
00:44:24.760 --> 00:44:27.980
A disciple should be willing to follow the
example of his Lord.

cue-664
00:44:29.720 --> 00:44:34.000
There are ways of studying the Bible that
do not belong to the inner place of

cue-665
00:44:34.000 --> 00:44:34.290
prayer.

cue-666
00:44:35.530 --> 00:44:39.900
Methods such as studying history, literary
analysis, and critical

cue-667
00:44:39.900 --> 00:44:44.120
approaches deal with outward matters and
belong in study and

cue-668
00:44:44.120 --> 00:44:48.719
discussion. They focus on the external
setting and the gradual

cue-669
00:44:48.720 --> 00:44:50.360
unfolding of revealed truth.

cue-670
00:44:51.300 --> 00:44:55.980
But in the place of prayer, the scriptures
are received as the living and sovereign

cue-671
00:44:55.980 --> 00:44:56.900
word of God.

cue-672
00:44:57.940 --> 00:45:02.160
Though many writers were inspired, there
is only one true author.

cue-673
00:45:03.420 --> 00:45:08.260
As it is written, "Holy men of God spoke
as they were moved by the Holy Spirit."

cue-674
00:45:09.580 --> 00:45:13.520
Questions about dates, authorship, and
similar matters are set

cue-675
00:45:13.520 --> 00:45:18.360
aside, not because ignorance helps prayer,
but because such

cue-676
00:45:18.360 --> 00:45:20.340
questions are not relevant there.

cue-677
00:45:21.500 --> 00:45:25.200
Every part of scripture has a message tied
to its time and place,

cue-678
00:45:25.800 --> 00:45:29.680
but it also carries a truth that is
eternal and for all

cue-679
00:45:29.680 --> 00:45:34.529
people. Historical knowledge helps bring
fuller understanding,

cue-680
00:45:34.529 --> 00:45:38.010
yet the soul in prayer comes to scripture
to meet God.

cue-681
00:45:39.080 --> 00:45:43.940
To the praying soul, it is the unfailing,
sovereign, and saving word of

cue-682
00:45:43.980 --> 00:45:44.340
God.

cue-683
00:45:45.460 --> 00:45:49.120
So we can still take the scriptures into
the quiet place of prayer.

cue-684
00:45:50.340 --> 00:45:54.320
Even scholars often admit that their
debates are not about the most important

cue-685
00:45:54.320 --> 00:45:59.300
matters, and in the end, their certain
conclusions are often only

cue-686
00:45:59.300 --> 00:46:00.880
widely accepted ideas.

cue-687
00:46:02.700 --> 00:46:07.160
I do not want to dwell too much on
biblical criticism, but it may help if I

cue-688
00:46:07.160 --> 00:46:09.020
explain how I view the scriptures.

cue-689
00:46:10.060 --> 00:46:14.340
To me, there is a clear comparison between
the word of the Lord and the law of the

cue-690
00:46:14.340 --> 00:46:14.740
land.

cue-691
00:46:15.600 --> 00:46:20.520
A judge and jury accept the law. Their
role is not to criticize or change

cue-692
00:46:20.520 --> 00:46:23.029
it, but to understand and apply it.

cue-693
00:46:24.100 --> 00:46:28.060
They are not concerned with the politics
or the people who created the law.

cue-694
00:46:29.120 --> 00:46:33.619
It can be interesting to study the history
behind a law, to learn the situation it

cue-695
00:46:33.620 --> 00:46:38.220
addressed, the efforts of reformers, who
wrote it, and how it was revised.

cue-696
00:46:39.060 --> 00:46:43.080
But that work belongs to historians and
specialists.

cue-697
00:46:43.720 --> 00:46:48.220
Even a lawyer may not know these details.
His task is to know the law

cue-698
00:46:48.220 --> 00:46:48.760
itself.

cue-699
00:46:49.700 --> 00:46:54.320
The judge's task is to interpret it, and
the jury's task is to

cue-700
00:46:54.320 --> 00:46:55.779
submit to its authority.

cue-701
00:46:56.940 --> 00:47:01.280
In the same way, with the word of God,
questions about how many authors there

cue-702
00:47:01.280 --> 00:47:06.240
were, how the books were formed, or what
sources were used are not the main

cue-703
00:47:06.240 --> 00:47:06.900
concern.

cue-704
00:47:07.870 --> 00:47:12.080
The scriptures have moved beyond their
human and historical beginnings.

cue-705
00:47:12.700 --> 00:47:17.600
Because they were given by inspiration,
they remain the enduring word of the Lord.

cue-706
00:47:17.600 --> 00:47:22.180
We take the Bible into the place of
prayer not to study its

cue-707
00:47:22.180 --> 00:47:23.100
literary history,

cue-708
00:47:23.720 --> 00:47:26.900
but to listen for what the Lord, our God,
is saying to us.

cue-709
00:47:29.440 --> 00:47:31.020
The praying method in the word.

cue-710
00:47:33.620 --> 00:47:37.260
St. Paul said, "I will pray with the
understanding also."

cue-711
00:47:38.500 --> 00:47:40.950
The word of God gives understanding to
prayer.

cue-712
00:47:41.700 --> 00:47:44.930
The Bible is not an easy book for those
who are unfamiliar with it.

cue-713
00:47:45.580 --> 00:47:49.840
Because of this, many turn to simple,
structured devotional books.

cue-714
00:47:50.660 --> 00:47:55.650
Yet the Bible itself is meant to be a
guide to prayer for ordinary people if

cue-715
00:47:55.650 --> 00:47:56.960
it is rightly understood.

cue-716
00:47:58.180 --> 00:48:03.180
I think it may help you most if I explain
my own way of using it. The

cue-717
00:48:03.180 --> 00:48:08.100
first question is where to begin. Each
person must find his own starting

cue-718
00:48:08.100 --> 00:48:08.460
point.

cue-719
00:48:09.600 --> 00:48:10.880
I began with the Psalms.

cue-720
00:48:11.560 --> 00:48:14.380
The next question is the best time of day.

cue-721
00:48:15.480 --> 00:48:20.300
When I first began, I had to wake at five
in the morning and be at work by six,

cue-722
00:48:20.300 --> 00:48:25.260
so I read my passage the night before. I
read the selected portion

cue-723
00:48:25.260 --> 00:48:29.480
slowly, with a spirit of prayer, going
over it several times.

cue-724
00:48:30.660 --> 00:48:35.500
Then, on my knees, I took it line by line,
turning each part

cue-725
00:48:35.500 --> 00:48:37.260
into prayer and thanksgiving.

cue-726
00:48:38.440 --> 00:48:42.940
After that, I wrote down the verse or
phrase that especially spoke to

cue-727
00:48:42.940 --> 00:48:47.340
me.The next morning, as I dressed, I read
it again,

cue-728
00:48:48.030 --> 00:48:52.990
briefly committed the day to God, and
carried the verse with me.

cue-729
00:48:52.990 --> 00:48:57.430
Before I followed this method, I used to
try to force myself into a mood of prayer,

cue-730
00:48:58.130 --> 00:49:03.090
but I lacked direction, and prayer became
empty words with no sense of

cue-731
00:49:03.090 --> 00:49:03.770
listening.

cue-732
00:49:04.650 --> 00:49:09.650
Since then, prayer has become full of
wonder, rich in thought, and a

cue-733
00:49:09.650 --> 00:49:11.070
true fellowship with God

cue-734
00:49:11.730 --> 00:49:15.910
because it is guided, awakened, and
inspired by His Word.

cue-735
00:49:18.690 --> 00:49:20.270
Along with this simple method,

cue-736
00:49:20.890 --> 00:49:25.309
I have found great help in using the
marginal references, especially those in

cue-737
00:49:25.310 --> 00:49:26.390
the Revised Version.

cue-738
00:49:27.430 --> 00:49:31.970
The Holy Spirit teaches us to compare
Scripture with Scripture and spiritual

cue-739
00:49:31.970 --> 00:49:33.790
truth with spiritual truth.

cue-740
00:49:34.610 --> 00:49:38.830
The same Spirit who inspired the
Scriptures is given to help us understand

cue-741
00:49:38.830 --> 00:49:39.090
them.

cue-742
00:49:39.790 --> 00:49:42.670
The Holy Spirit and the Word of God never
disagree.

cue-743
00:49:43.410 --> 00:49:48.380
Revelation unfolds step by step, and each
part has its place and

cue-744
00:49:48.380 --> 00:49:48.910
meaning.

cue-745
00:49:49.770 --> 00:49:52.790
Watching this unfolding deeply moves the
soul.

cue-746
00:49:53.690 --> 00:49:57.270
New insights awaken the mind and stir
worship and praise.

cue-747
00:49:58.190 --> 00:49:58.910
Is this prayer?

cue-748
00:49:59.790 --> 00:50:04.270
Yes, it is, so long as it remains focused
on devotion and is not

cue-749
00:50:04.270 --> 00:50:05.990
pursued for any other purpose.

cue-750
00:50:07.310 --> 00:50:12.250
I once tried using passages meant for
study or examination as my devotional

cue-751
00:50:12.250 --> 00:50:12.570
reading,

cue-752
00:50:13.470 --> 00:50:16.050
but it left my time empty and unhelpful.

cue-753
00:50:17.230 --> 00:50:21.970
God desires the full attention of the
spirit, just as we long to be aware of His

cue-754
00:50:21.970 --> 00:50:22.870
real presence.

cue-755
00:50:24.030 --> 00:50:28.630
The soul is never less alone than when it
is alone with God.

cue-756
00:50:29.830 --> 00:50:32.470
How to use the Word in prayer.

cue-757
00:50:34.230 --> 00:50:39.210
It is best to use only the Bible so that
Scripture explains Scripture.

cue-758
00:50:40.130 --> 00:50:44.430
I find it helpful to take the words of the
psalmists and prophets and turn them into

cue-759
00:50:44.430 --> 00:50:44.760
prayer.

cue-760
00:50:45.530 --> 00:50:50.270
Avoid distractions that pull you away from
this purpose. I have also

cue-761
00:50:50.270 --> 00:50:54.790
noticed that many well-known Bible
scholars use the Authorized Version in

cue-762
00:50:54.790 --> 00:50:56.159
their personal devotions,

cue-763
00:50:56.910 --> 00:50:59.189
and I recommend following their example.

cue-764
00:51:00.670 --> 00:51:01.690
Search the Scriptures.

cue-765
00:51:02.550 --> 00:51:03.970
When the Word comes alive,

cue-766
00:51:04.570 --> 00:51:06.390
the heart soon burns with it.

cue-767
00:51:07.580 --> 00:51:09.870
The Word of God is like God's world.

cue-768
00:51:10.590 --> 00:51:12.290
All of it is interesting and wonderful,

cue-769
00:51:12.930 --> 00:51:16.970
yet there are places we return to again
and again with special love.

cue-770
00:51:18.250 --> 00:51:23.090
There are passages we never tire of, and
others made sacred by deep personal

cue-771
00:51:23.090 --> 00:51:23.890
meaning.

cue-772
00:51:24.430 --> 00:51:29.130
Some pages of the Bible become worn from
frequent use, and some are marked by

cue-773
00:51:29.130 --> 00:51:29.610
tears.

cue-774
00:51:30.810 --> 00:51:33.030
There is no book of prayer like the
Psalms.

cue-775
00:51:34.070 --> 00:51:37.230
Certain Psalms seem to reflect the journey
of the soul.

cue-776
00:51:38.410 --> 00:51:43.390
I especially love Psalms thirty-seven,
forty-six, eighty, and one

cue-777
00:51:43.390 --> 00:51:46.030
hundred and sixteen, along with many
others.

cue-778
00:51:47.290 --> 00:51:51.970
Usually, I read through a whole Psalm,
then return to a few verses that stand out

cue-779
00:51:51.970 --> 00:51:53.630
to me and meditate on them.

cue-780
00:51:54.610 --> 00:51:58.810
How often I have answered worry with trust
in Psalm thirty-seven,

cue-781
00:51:59.590 --> 00:52:04.250
committing my way to the Lord, repeating
and praying the words, "Rest in the

cue-782
00:52:04.250 --> 00:52:06.379
Lord and wait patiently for Him."

cue-783
00:52:07.650 --> 00:52:12.510
My soul finds joy in the promise that if I
delight in the Lord, He will

cue-784
00:52:12.510 --> 00:52:14.290
give me the desires of my heart.

cue-785
00:52:15.510 --> 00:52:20.370
It is a great thing to take the Lord's own
words, speak them in praise, and

cue-786
00:52:20.370 --> 00:52:22.190
use them as prayers before Him.

cue-787
00:52:24.050 --> 00:52:28.230
The forty-sixth Psalm is just as
wonderful, with its three parts:

cue-788
00:52:28.850 --> 00:52:31.470
disaster, conflict, and witness.

cue-789
00:52:32.750 --> 00:52:37.410
Then I return to the first verse, which
describes God as our refuge,

cue-790
00:52:37.410 --> 00:52:38.580
strength, and help.

cue-791
00:52:39.870 --> 00:52:44.340
A refuge is a place of safety in dangers
where we are completely helpless.

cue-792
00:52:45.170 --> 00:52:50.060
What can we do against a shaking earth,
falling mountains, or raging storms?

cue-793
00:52:51.270 --> 00:52:54.810
When sudden trouble comes and everything
seems to give way beneath us,

cue-794
00:52:55.430 --> 00:52:57.010
God is our refuge.

cue-795
00:52:57.970 --> 00:53:02.780
The eternal God is thy refuge, and
underneath are the everlasting arms,

cue-796
00:53:03.830 --> 00:53:05.210
always underneath,

cue-797
00:53:06.090 --> 00:53:08.290
always deeper than our deepest need.

cue-798
00:53:09.230 --> 00:53:10.950
God is also our strength.

cue-799
00:53:12.150 --> 00:53:16.550
There are demands we cannot meet and
enemies we cannot face on our own.

cue-800
00:53:17.490 --> 00:53:22.350
He giveth power to the faint, and to them
that have no might, He increaseth

cue-801
00:53:22.350 --> 00:53:22.750
strength.

cue-802
00:53:24.070 --> 00:53:27.440
At once, the mind turns to the great
people of faith,

cue-803
00:53:28.050 --> 00:53:31.870
and we are encouraged with the promise
that strength will be given for each

cue-804
00:53:31.870 --> 00:53:34.850
day. God is also our help.

cue-805
00:53:35.770 --> 00:53:40.490
There are times when we are not enough on
our own. A helper comes near,

cue-806
00:53:40.490 --> 00:53:44.890
bringing support, encouragement, guidance,
and strength to act.

cue-807
00:53:46.030 --> 00:53:47.850
What more could we need for assurance?

cue-808
00:53:48.630 --> 00:53:52.230
It is no wonder the heart draws close to
God and quietly says,

cue-809
00:53:53.000 --> 00:53:55.490
"I will trust and not be afraid."

cue-810
00:53:57.010 --> 00:54:01.290
The Lord of Hosts is with us. The God of
Jacob is our refuge.

cue-811
00:54:02.550 --> 00:54:05.510
I have often prayed through Psalm one
hundred and sixteen.

cue-812
00:54:06.190 --> 00:54:08.550
It was one of the first gifts God gave me.

cue-813
00:54:09.400 --> 00:54:13.710
There is no need to change the wording
since every verse already speaks

cue-814
00:54:13.710 --> 00:54:18.640
personally. I love how it moves between
deep sorrow and joyful

cue-815
00:54:18.640 --> 00:54:19.300
thanksgiving,

cue-816
00:54:20.010 --> 00:54:24.070
and I spend much time on the promises made
by a soul that has been saved.

cue-817
00:54:25.250 --> 00:54:27.310
The writer had gone through great depths.

cue-818
00:54:27.970 --> 00:54:32.910
Troubles came all at once, and worst of
all, he had lost his trust in both

cue-819
00:54:32.910 --> 00:54:34.390
God and people.

cue-820
00:54:35.670 --> 00:54:37.790
But deliverance came when he prayed.

cue-821
00:54:38.670 --> 00:54:42.710
Prayer led to praise, and praise became a
thankful

cue-822
00:54:42.710 --> 00:54:47.502
offering.Return to your rest, O my soul,
for the

cue-823
00:54:47.502 --> 00:54:52.482
Lord has been good to you. For you have
delivered my soul from death, my eyes

cue-824
00:54:52.482 --> 00:54:55.082
from tears, and my feet from falling.

cue-825
00:54:56.212 --> 00:54:59.982
I will walk before the Lord in the land of
the living.

cue-826
00:55:01.922 --> 00:55:04.922
There are passages of Scripture that I
read at certain times.

cue-827
00:55:06.022 --> 00:55:10.982
One of my earliest efforts at serious
Bible study was to arrange in order the

cue-828
00:55:10.982 --> 00:55:14.672
actions and words of our Lord during the
week of His passion.

cue-829
00:55:15.692 --> 00:55:19.482
I still return to those passages each year
during that sacred week.

cue-830
00:55:20.551 --> 00:55:24.801
There are also suitable readings for
Advent and other seasons of the Christian

cue-831
00:55:24.802 --> 00:55:25.062
year.

cue-832
00:55:26.482 --> 00:55:28.412
When I begin using a new Bible,

cue-833
00:55:29.082 --> 00:55:33.932
I first mark the passages in the Gospel of
John where our Lord promises the Holy

cue-834
00:55:33.932 --> 00:55:34.342
Spirit.

cue-835
00:55:35.522 --> 00:55:40.042
I read these regularly between Easter and
Pentecost, and in doing so,

cue-836
00:55:40.042 --> 00:55:43.822
my place of prayer becomes like the upper
room of my Lord.

cue-837
00:55:44.902 --> 00:55:49.382
There are also three portions of Scripture
that I have read on fixed days for more

cue-838
00:55:49.382 --> 00:55:50.482
than forty years.

cue-839
00:55:51.642 --> 00:55:56.442
Every Sunday morning, I read Revelation
chapter five, and every Sunday night,

cue-840
00:55:56.442 --> 00:55:59.442
Revelation chapter seven, beginning at
verse nine.

cue-841
00:56:00.682 --> 00:56:03.882
I do this because Sunday is the central
day of my week.

cue-842
00:56:05.082 --> 00:56:09.602
I may preach on other days, but this is
the Lord's Day, set apart for

cue-843
00:56:09.602 --> 00:56:11.682
worship and the ministry of the Word.

cue-844
00:56:12.862 --> 00:56:17.542
On this day, I carry the responsibility of
interceding, teaching,

cue-845
00:56:17.542 --> 00:56:20.122
proclaiming, and calling others to faith.

cue-846
00:56:21.382 --> 00:56:25.602
I am to represent Christ, preach Christ,
and plead for Christ.

cue-847
00:56:26.822 --> 00:56:29.342
For such work, I need a clear vision of
Him.

cue-848
00:56:30.202 --> 00:56:34.802
Nowhere do I see Him more fully than in
these passages, revealed at the center of

cue-849
00:56:34.802 --> 00:56:39.602
the throne, among the redeemed, surrounded
by angels, and over all

cue-850
00:56:39.602 --> 00:56:40.162
creation.

cue-851
00:56:41.362 --> 00:56:46.362
After seeing His glory and saying, "Amen,
hallelujah," I am ready to face

cue-852
00:56:46.362 --> 00:56:50.902
the day. At night, I return again to the
vision of His final victory.

cue-853
00:56:51.882 --> 00:56:55.282
I commit the day to Him and find rest in
His presence.

cue-854
00:56:56.962 --> 00:57:01.862
On Monday morning, I always read Isaiah
forty-one, beginning at verse

cue-855
00:57:01.862 --> 00:57:02.102
eight.

cue-856
00:57:03.102 --> 00:57:06.632
Monday can be a difficult day for one who
has preached on Sunday.

cue-857
00:57:07.371 --> 00:57:11.942
The brightness of the Lord's Day can seem
to fade, and discouragement may come.

cue-858
00:57:13.112 --> 00:57:17.961
I determined early in my ministry that if
I had to face such feelings, I would

cue-859
00:57:17.962 --> 00:57:18.802
not give in to them.

cue-860
00:57:19.682 --> 00:57:22.512
God gave me this passage as a safeguard
against them.

cue-861
00:57:23.412 --> 00:57:26.012
This began in my first month after leaving
college.

cue-862
00:57:27.042 --> 00:57:31.802
One Monday morning, I was in my room,
wrapped in a blanket, cold and unwell.

cue-863
00:57:31.802 --> 00:57:34.182
It rained heavily all morning.

cue-864
00:57:35.742 --> 00:57:37.562
Near noon, a visitor arrived,

cue-865
00:57:38.302 --> 00:57:42.022
H.S.B. Yates, a minister I had only met a
few times.

cue-866
00:57:43.102 --> 00:57:44.882
When I asked how he was, he said,

cue-867
00:57:45.591 --> 00:57:47.682
"I am a worm and no man."

cue-868
00:57:48.942 --> 00:57:50.502
He was deeply discouraged.

cue-869
00:57:51.582 --> 00:57:55.702
Though his church had been full the night
before, he had been troubled afterward

cue-870
00:57:55.702 --> 00:57:57.061
with doubt and fear.

cue-871
00:57:58.182 --> 00:58:01.122
He asked me what I did when I felt low and
worthless.

cue-872
00:58:01.982 --> 00:58:05.182
I had just been reading Isaiah forty-one,
so I said,

cue-873
00:58:05.992 --> 00:58:09.542
"This chapter is for you. It is God's
promise to a worm."

cue-874
00:58:10.822 --> 00:58:12.782
We read it together and prayed through it.

cue-875
00:58:13.742 --> 00:58:15.202
He left greatly comforted.

cue-876
00:58:16.062 --> 00:58:20.882
Since then, I have read that passage every
Monday morning. I have found it a strong

cue-877
00:58:20.882 --> 00:58:22.642
defense against discouragement.

cue-878
00:58:23.642 --> 00:58:28.442
Because of it, Monday has often become one
of my most active and joyful days.

cue-879
00:58:29.682 --> 00:58:34.302
In this way, I continue through the Bible,
using its passages to guide my

cue-880
00:58:34.302 --> 00:58:36.232
prayer and strengthen my soul.

cue-881
00:58:37.782 --> 00:58:42.462
These are personal words, but now you can
understand why the Word of the Lord is so

cue-882
00:58:42.462 --> 00:58:43.222
precious to me.

cue-883
00:58:44.302 --> 00:58:48.742
All along, I have kept in mind those who
are busy and burdened with work,

cue-884
00:58:49.382 --> 00:58:51.972
who have little time or space for quiet
prayer.

cue-885
00:58:53.312 --> 00:58:57.882
That is why I urge the use of the Bible as
the only necessary book for

cue-886
00:58:57.882 --> 00:58:58.442
devotion.

cue-887
00:58:59.522 --> 00:59:04.202
For the same reason, I recommend reading
short portions so that prayer

cue-888
00:59:04.202 --> 00:59:07.662
remains the main focus in the times set
apart for God.

cue-889
00:59:10.922 --> 00:59:13.522
Chapter six: Praying in the Name.

cue-890
00:59:16.302 --> 00:59:19.142
The most amazing promises are given about
prayer.

cue-891
00:59:19.822 --> 00:59:23.002
The Old Testament is full of both promises
and examples.

cue-892
00:59:23.842 --> 00:59:28.662
God promised help, guidance, grace, and
rescue to those who

cue-893
00:59:28.662 --> 00:59:31.302
called on Him and trusted their lives to
Him.

cue-894
00:59:32.502 --> 00:59:36.562
Nothing was too hard for the Lord, and
nothing was impossible for those who

cue-895
00:59:36.562 --> 00:59:37.002
prayed.

cue-896
00:59:38.222 --> 00:59:41.722
Some verses strongly challenge us to pray.
For example,

cue-897
00:59:42.542 --> 00:59:46.272
"Thus says the Lord, the Holy One of
Israel, and its Maker:

cue-898
00:59:47.122 --> 00:59:51.762
Ask me about the things to come concerning
my children, and command me concerning

cue-899
00:59:51.762 --> 00:59:53.302
the work of my hands."

cue-900
00:59:54.602 --> 00:59:59.122
Here, prayer moves from simply asking to
speaking with bold authority.

cue-901
01:00:00.182 --> 01:00:02.222
There is no limit to what prayer can do.

cue-902
01:00:02.912 --> 01:00:06.722
The Old Testament proves this through many
examples that show its power.

cue-903
01:00:07.722 --> 01:00:11.382
Jesus speaks in the same unlimited way. He
says,

cue-904
01:00:12.042 --> 01:00:17.042
"Ask and it will be given to you. Seek and
you will find.

cue-905
01:00:17.042 --> 01:00:19.282
Knock and it will be opened to you.

cue-906
01:00:19.962 --> 01:00:24.902
For everyone who asks receives. The one
who seeks finds,

cue-907
01:00:24.902 --> 01:00:27.002
and to the one who knocks it will be
opened."

cue-908
01:00:28.262 --> 01:00:33.182
He gave prayer a new foundation, greater
confidence, and a wider reach.

cue-909
01:00:33.992 --> 01:00:37.302
He based it on the truth that God is our
Father in heaven.

cue-910
01:00:38.122 --> 01:00:41.342
Prayer is like a child asking a loving
parent.

cue-911
01:00:42.362 --> 01:00:46.872
If you, though you are sinful, know how to
give good gifts to your children,

cue-912
01:00:47.571 --> 01:00:51.762
how much more will your Father in heaven
give good things to those who ask

cue-913
01:00:51.762 --> 01:00:56.386
Him?There is another saying of Jesus that
is even more surprising.

cue-914
01:00:57.186 --> 01:01:01.526
Therefore I tell you, whatever you ask for
in prayer, believe that you have received

cue-915
01:01:01.526 --> 01:01:03.166
it, and it will be yours.

cue-916
01:01:05.306 --> 01:01:07.586
Whatsoever you shall ask in my name.

cue-917
01:01:10.346 --> 01:01:14.405
The promises about prayer reach their
highest point in the upper room on that

cue-918
01:01:14.406 --> 01:01:15.366
unforgettable night,

cue-919
01:01:15.986 --> 01:01:18.646
filled with both deep truth and coming
sorrow.

cue-920
01:01:19.766 --> 01:01:23.366
Jesus said that he himself would be the
foundation of prayer.

cue-921
01:01:24.086 --> 01:01:28.806
From then on, they were to pray in a new
way, in his name, and their

cue-922
01:01:28.806 --> 01:01:31.086
prayers would be answered because of him.

cue-923
01:01:32.306 --> 01:01:36.825
Just as there are seven sayings from the
cross, there are also seven teachings

cue-924
01:01:36.826 --> 01:01:38.666
about prayer given in the upper room.

cue-925
01:01:39.766 --> 01:01:43.266
These gather together everything taught in
scripture about prayer,

cue-926
01:01:43.886 --> 01:01:46.466
expanding and confirming God's promises.

cue-927
01:01:47.646 --> 01:01:52.646
It feels almost wrong to change them, for
no other words are like them. And whatever

cue-928
01:01:52.646 --> 01:01:53.786
you ask in my name,

cue-929
01:01:54.446 --> 01:01:59.386
I will do it so that the Father may be
glorified in the Son. If you ask

cue-930
01:01:59.386 --> 01:02:00.446
anything in my name,

cue-931
01:02:01.146 --> 01:02:03.066
I will do it.

cue-932
01:02:03.566 --> 01:02:06.546
If you remain in me and my words remain in
you,

cue-933
01:02:07.166 --> 01:02:10.306
you may ask whatever you wish, and it will
be done for you.

cue-934
01:02:12.166 --> 01:02:16.926
You did not choose me, but I chose you and
appointed you to go and bear fruit,

cue-935
01:02:17.706 --> 01:02:18.966
fruit that will last.

cue-936
01:02:19.706 --> 01:02:23.126
Then the Father will give you whatever you
ask in my name.

cue-937
01:02:24.766 --> 01:02:29.525
Now you are filled with sorrow, but I will
see you again, and your hearts will

cue-938
01:02:29.526 --> 01:02:34.526
rejoice, and no one will take away your
joy. In that day, you will

cue-939
01:02:34.526 --> 01:02:38.306
no longer ask me anything. Truly, truly, I
say to you,

cue-940
01:02:38.946 --> 01:02:43.946
whatever you ask the Father in my name, he
will give you. Until now you

cue-941
01:02:43.946 --> 01:02:48.766
have not asked anything in my name. Ask
and you will receive,

cue-942
01:02:48.766 --> 01:02:53.606
so that your joy may be complete. In that
day you will ask

cue-943
01:02:53.606 --> 01:02:54.426
in my name.

cue-944
01:02:56.346 --> 01:03:00.896
These are remarkable promises given to
those who pray in the name of our Lord and

cue-945
01:03:00.896 --> 01:03:02.286
Savior Jesus Christ.

cue-946
01:03:03.316 --> 01:03:07.266
They are broad and far-reaching. Anything,
whatever you ask.

cue-947
01:03:08.486 --> 01:03:12.246
Prayer reaches its highest place when it
is offered in his name,

cue-948
01:03:13.326 --> 01:03:17.146
because it brings the one who prays into
close unity with him.

cue-949
01:03:20.006 --> 01:03:22.406
In the name of our Lord Jesus Christ.

cue-950
01:03:25.266 --> 01:03:30.226
Our Lord did not explain what it means to
pray in his name. The meaning was

cue-951
01:03:30.226 --> 01:03:34.686
already clear to every Israelite. God was
present in his name.

cue-952
01:03:35.526 --> 01:03:40.526
He had chosen his people so they would
understand, guard, and represent his

cue-953
01:03:40.526 --> 01:03:40.836
name.

cue-954
01:03:41.646 --> 01:03:46.006
But when they dishonored his name in their
own land and brought shame to it among

cue-955
01:03:46.006 --> 01:03:46.686
the nations,

cue-956
01:03:47.306 --> 01:03:48.726
he acted to restore them

cue-957
01:03:49.366 --> 01:03:50.726
for the honor of his name.

cue-958
01:03:51.966 --> 01:03:56.786
I do not do this for your sake, but for my
holy name's sake, which you have

cue-959
01:03:56.786 --> 01:03:59.206
dishonored among the nations where you
have gone.

cue-960
01:04:00.226 --> 01:04:03.126
And I will make my great name holy again.

cue-961
01:04:04.486 --> 01:04:06.766
Our Lord speaks as God himself.

cue-962
01:04:07.826 --> 01:04:12.826
To pray in Christ's name means much more
than simply adding the words for Christ's

cue-963
01:04:12.826 --> 01:04:14.306
sake to our prayers.

cue-964
01:04:15.386 --> 01:04:20.326
A name represents a person's character,
nature, and identity. The

cue-965
01:04:20.326 --> 01:04:25.276
person is present in the name. So to pray
in Christ's name is to

cue-966
01:04:25.276 --> 01:04:28.626
pray in a way that agrees with his
character and his will.

cue-967
01:04:29.686 --> 01:04:32.476
It is to pray as someone who is united
with him,

cue-968
01:04:33.206 --> 01:04:38.186
whose thoughts reflect his mind, whose
desires match his desires,

cue-969
01:04:38.186 --> 01:04:40.466
and whose purpose is the same as his.

cue-970
01:04:42.146 --> 01:04:46.886
When a person is united with Christ in
this way, it helps us understand and

cue-971
01:04:46.886 --> 01:04:49.346
properly apply the promises about prayer.

cue-972
01:04:50.426 --> 01:04:55.186
The promises that seem absolute and
unlimited are shaped and guided by him.

cue-973
01:04:56.406 --> 01:05:00.966
In the Old Testament, prayer depended on
urgency, deep feeling, and

cue-974
01:05:00.966 --> 01:05:01.686
sincerity.

cue-975
01:05:02.806 --> 01:05:07.735
God answered those who cried out to him in
great need, who sought him with all their

cue-976
01:05:07.735 --> 01:05:10.326
heart, and who were honest in their
motives.

cue-977
01:05:11.166 --> 01:05:16.126
People learned that God desires truth in
the inner being. They were not heard if

cue-978
01:05:16.126 --> 01:05:20.306
they held on to sin in their hearts or
spoke to him with false words.

cue-979
01:05:21.506 --> 01:05:26.506
Our Lord also taught that prayer requires
persistence and a forgiving spirit.

cue-980
01:05:27.626 --> 01:05:29.366
But when we pray in his name,

cue-981
01:05:30.206 --> 01:05:33.886
all these conditions come together and are
made simple in him.

cue-982
01:05:35.106 --> 01:05:39.886
Sincerity is tested by his name. Motives
are judged by his name.

cue-983
01:05:39.886 --> 01:05:44.346
Prayer is examined by his name. Prayer is
made holy by his name.

cue-984
01:05:45.046 --> 01:05:49.926
Prayer is accepted through his name when
it agrees with his character, his mind,

cue-985
01:05:49.926 --> 01:05:52.546
his desires, and his purpose.

cue-986
01:05:53.806 --> 01:05:58.726
This is why in John fifteen seven, his
words are closely tied to his

cue-987
01:05:58.726 --> 01:05:59.026
name.

cue-988
01:06:00.126 --> 01:06:02.746
If you remain in me and my words remain in
you,

cue-989
01:06:03.366 --> 01:06:06.726
you may ask whatever you wish, and it will
be done for you.

cue-990
01:06:08.016 --> 01:06:10.246
This is similar to what the psalmist says,

cue-991
01:06:11.066 --> 01:06:15.106
Delight yourself in the Lord, and he will
give you the desires of your heart.

cue-992
01:06:16.046 --> 01:06:17.606
And also what John writes,

cue-993
01:06:18.286 --> 01:06:22.926
Beloved, if our hearts do not condemn us,
we have confidence before

cue-994
01:06:22.926 --> 01:06:27.706
God. And whatever we ask, we receive from
him, because we keep his

cue-995
01:06:27.706 --> 01:06:32.345
commandments and do what pleases him.
Prayers offered in

cue-996
01:06:32.346 --> 01:06:37.246
Christ's name are examined and made holy
by his nature, his purpose, and

cue-997
01:06:37.246 --> 01:06:37.726
his will.

cue-998
01:06:38.906 --> 01:06:41.186
When they agree with him, he approves
them.

cue-999
01:06:43.046 --> 01:06:44.286
For the sake of the name.

cue-1000
01:06:46.626 --> 01:06:50.266
It means even more than this. We are heard
because of him.

cue-1001
01:06:50.946 --> 01:06:55.806
He himself is the one who presents our
prayers. He lives forever to

cue-1002
01:06:55.806 --> 01:07:00.130
pray for us.In Revelation, he is shown as
taking our

cue-1003
01:07:00.130 --> 01:07:03.130
prayers and adding to them the fire from
the altar,

cue-1004
01:07:03.810 --> 01:07:05.800
making them powerful and acceptable.

cue-1005
01:07:07.150 --> 01:07:12.069
He told his disciples that he was going to
the Father and would pray for them,

cue-1006
01:07:12.070 --> 01:07:15.630
and whatever they ask the Father in his
name, the Father would do.

cue-1007
01:07:16.670 --> 01:07:20.830
They would be heard not because of
themselves, but because of him.

cue-1008
01:07:22.310 --> 01:07:26.470
When I was in Leeds, a man traveled a long
distance to visit a factory he was

cue-1009
01:07:26.470 --> 01:07:27.110
interested in.

cue-1010
01:07:27.990 --> 01:07:31.610
He wrote to the company, but his request
was politely refused.

cue-1011
01:07:32.530 --> 01:07:37.430
He then went in person and gave them his
card, but it was returned, and he

cue-1012
01:07:37.430 --> 01:07:38.410
was not allowed in.

cue-1013
01:07:39.540 --> 01:07:43.790
No matter what he said, he could not get
past the small window in the front office.

cue-1014
01:07:44.750 --> 01:07:48.510
He shared his disappointment with a
friend, who suggested that I might help

cue-1015
01:07:48.510 --> 01:07:48.650
him.

cue-1016
01:07:49.950 --> 01:07:50.990
So he came to see me.

cue-1017
01:07:51.670 --> 01:07:54.750
I gave him my card and wrote a note to the
head of the company.

cue-1018
01:07:55.970 --> 01:08:00.370
The next day, he went again, made his
request, and handed them my card.

cue-1019
01:08:01.610 --> 01:08:04.650
This time, every door was opened to him at
once.

cue-1020
01:08:05.610 --> 01:08:09.070
His request was granted, but not because
of who he was.

cue-1021
01:08:09.990 --> 01:08:11.350
The owner saw me in him.

cue-1022
01:08:12.150 --> 01:08:15.390
In this same way, we pray in Christ's
name.

cue-1023
01:08:16.210 --> 01:08:21.209
He approves our requests and makes them
his own, and the Father listens

cue-1024
01:08:21.210 --> 01:08:21.570
to him.

cue-1025
01:08:22.750 --> 01:08:27.670
We are not heard because we speak loudly
or use beautiful words or shed

cue-1026
01:08:27.670 --> 01:08:28.590
many tears.

cue-1027
01:08:29.470 --> 01:08:32.630
We are not heard because of our good deeds
or sacrifices.

cue-1028
01:08:33.510 --> 01:08:36.420
Prayer in his name is answered because of
who he is.

cue-1029
01:08:37.550 --> 01:08:39.940
In the quiet place of prayer, we ask,

cue-1030
01:08:40.570 --> 01:08:42.930
seek, and knock in his holy name.

cue-1031
01:08:44.170 --> 01:08:47.230
We offer our prayers with full confidence
in his promise.

cue-1032
01:08:48.250 --> 01:08:51.710
You did not choose me, but I chose you and
appointed you,

cue-1033
01:08:52.510 --> 01:08:56.530
so that whatever you ask the Father in my
name, he may give it to you.

cue-1034
01:08:57.590 --> 01:08:59.690
Ask, and you will receive.

cue-1035
01:09:02.850 --> 01:09:03.610
Chapter Seven:

cue-1036
01:09:04.370 --> 01:09:06.410
Praying in the Spirit.

cue-1037
01:09:08.390 --> 01:09:13.270
Early in 1882, I had an experience that
lifted my life to a new level of

cue-1038
01:09:13.270 --> 01:09:17.470
understanding and power. I received the
gift of the Holy Spirit.

cue-1039
01:09:18.090 --> 01:09:22.630
I was led in ways I did not understand,
for I had hardly even heard that such an

cue-1040
01:09:22.630 --> 01:09:23.999
experience was possible.

cue-1041
01:09:25.340 --> 01:09:29.790
The pressure of a task that felt
impossible made me aware of my need.

cue-1042
01:09:30.950 --> 01:09:35.510
I had no strength or ability, either in my
work or in my prayers.

cue-1043
01:09:36.190 --> 01:09:37.680
So I began to pray for power,

cue-1044
01:09:38.390 --> 01:09:39.080
for my work,

cue-1045
01:09:39.750 --> 01:09:44.650
and God led me to the answer by first
teaching me how to pray.

cue-1046
01:09:44.650 --> 01:09:47.990
This surprised me because I thought I
already knew how to pray.

cue-1047
01:09:49.230 --> 01:09:51.710
I had prayed much about the work God had
given me.

cue-1048
01:09:52.710 --> 01:09:54.770
But when I truly began to seek power,

cue-1049
01:09:55.480 --> 01:09:58.240
I started to hear things I had not noticed
before,

cue-1050
01:09:59.030 --> 01:10:01.420
even before I began to understand them
clearly.

cue-1051
01:10:02.710 --> 01:10:04.980
I listened to testimonies I had once
ignored.

cue-1052
01:10:05.600 --> 01:10:10.490
Others had also come to God because they
lacked power, but they always connected

cue-1053
01:10:10.490 --> 01:10:14.950
power with a deeper experience of
holiness, something I had not really

cue-1054
01:10:14.950 --> 01:10:15.490
desired.

cue-1055
01:10:16.700 --> 01:10:18.100
What I wanted was power.

cue-1056
01:10:18.770 --> 01:10:20.350
I wanted power to succeed.

cue-1057
01:10:21.250 --> 01:10:24.349
My main concern was the success that power
would bring.

cue-1058
01:10:25.120 --> 01:10:29.550
I wanted success that would fill my
church, save people, and break down the

cue-1059
01:10:29.550 --> 01:10:30.810
strongholds of Satan.

cue-1060
01:10:31.870 --> 01:10:34.290
I was young, and I was impatient.

cue-1061
01:10:35.010 --> 01:10:38.050
Twelve of us began to pray together, and
the answer came

cue-1062
01:10:38.750 --> 01:10:41.800
in a way we never expected, like when his
people

cue-1063
01:10:42.590 --> 01:10:46.010
passed through the sea, protected by walls
like crystal.

cue-1064
01:10:46.730 --> 01:10:51.230
He led us to Pentecost. That experience
became the key to my whole life.

cue-1065
01:10:51.990 --> 01:10:55.070
It awakened my understanding and cleansed
my heart.

cue-1066
01:10:55.930 --> 01:11:00.910
It gave me new joy and new power, a new
love, and a deeper compassion.

cue-1067
01:11:02.050 --> 01:11:06.550
It opened the Bible to me in a new way and
gave me a new message to share.

cue-1068
01:11:07.610 --> 01:11:12.610
Above all, it gave me a new understanding
and a closer fellowship with

cue-1069
01:11:12.610 --> 01:11:13.699
God in prayer.

cue-1070
01:11:14.900 --> 01:11:17.150
It taught me how to pray in the Spirit.

cue-1071
01:11:19.020 --> 01:11:20.470
The cooperation of the Spirit.

cue-1072
01:11:22.500 --> 01:11:25.170
The Holy Spirit always works together with
us.

cue-1073
01:11:25.770 --> 01:11:30.570
He does not act alone. He chooses to work
through people to express his thoughts,

cue-1074
01:11:30.570 --> 01:11:33.610
reveal truth, and carry out God's will.

cue-1075
01:11:34.310 --> 01:11:38.950
He lives in the body of Christ, just as
Christ lived in the body prepared for him

cue-1076
01:11:38.950 --> 01:11:39.930
by the Holy Spirit.

cue-1077
01:11:41.130 --> 01:11:45.690
God's message came through the Spirit of
truth, but it was written down by human

cue-1078
01:11:45.690 --> 01:11:46.230
hands.

cue-1079
01:11:47.290 --> 01:11:51.850
This partnership between God and people is
seen throughout the whole work of

cue-1080
01:11:51.850 --> 01:11:53.300
salvation in Christ.

cue-1081
01:11:54.470 --> 01:11:59.190
Jesus was born of a woman, but he was
conceived by the Holy Spirit. He

cue-1082
01:11:59.190 --> 01:12:03.010
grew and learned in Joseph's home, guided
by the Spirit.

cue-1083
01:12:04.070 --> 01:12:08.670
His teaching and ministry were done in the
power of the Spirit. He offered himself

cue-1084
01:12:08.670 --> 01:12:13.370
to God through the eternal Spirit, and it
was the Spirit who raised him from the

cue-1085
01:12:13.370 --> 01:12:13.690
dead.

cue-1086
01:12:14.560 --> 01:12:17.030
This same pattern continues in our
salvation.

cue-1087
01:12:17.930 --> 01:12:20.890
There is always both a human part and a
divine part.

cue-1088
01:12:21.810 --> 01:12:26.550
There is a shared witness, a shared
guidance, a shared work, and even a

cue-1089
01:12:26.550 --> 01:12:27.830
shared intercession.

cue-1090
01:12:28.890 --> 01:12:32.610
We pray in the Spirit, and the Spirit also
prays for us.

cue-1091
01:12:35.170 --> 01:12:37.030
The fellowship of the Spirit in prayer.

cue-1092
01:12:39.670 --> 01:12:43.650
The Holy Spirit does not act on his own or
for his own purposes.

cue-1093
01:12:44.310 --> 01:12:49.070
His work is to glorify Christ, and
everything he does is based on what

cue-1094
01:12:49.070 --> 01:12:50.490
Christ has already finished.

cue-1095
01:12:51.410 --> 01:12:54.470
He could not be given until Jesus was
glorified.

cue-1096
01:12:55.510 --> 01:13:00.470
In the same way, there can be no true
Pentecost in our experience until

cue-1097
01:13:00.470 --> 01:13:05.314
Christ is honored as Lord.The Spirit is
the gift given

cue-1098
01:13:05.314 --> 01:13:10.254
after Christ's coronation, whom the Father
has made both Lord and Christ.

cue-1099
01:13:11.474 --> 01:13:15.954
Our partnership with the Spirit in prayer
comes through our life in Christ.

cue-1100
01:13:16.934 --> 01:13:20.434
This is explained in Romans eight, verses
nine to twenty-seven.

cue-1101
01:13:21.374 --> 01:13:24.294
Those who pray in the Spirit must live in
the Spirit.

cue-1102
01:13:25.174 --> 01:13:29.994
If the Spirit is to pray for us, He must
live within us. If we live by our

cue-1103
01:13:29.994 --> 01:13:31.934
sinful nature, we will die.

cue-1104
01:13:32.814 --> 01:13:35.794
But if we are led by the Spirit and live
according to Him,

cue-1105
01:13:36.414 --> 01:13:40.034
then He lives in us, works through us, and
guides us.

cue-1106
01:13:41.034 --> 01:13:42.274
Then this becomes true.

cue-1107
01:13:43.114 --> 01:13:45.134
The Spirit helps us in our weakness.

cue-1108
01:13:46.164 --> 01:13:51.154
We do not know how we should pray, but the
Spirit himself prays for us with deep

cue-1109
01:13:51.154 --> 01:13:53.814
feelings that cannot be put into words.

cue-1110
01:13:55.034 --> 01:14:00.014
And God, who searches our hearts, knows
the mind of the Spirit because the Spirit

cue-1111
01:14:00.014 --> 01:14:02.874
prays for God's people according to his
will.

cue-1112
01:14:04.134 --> 01:14:08.934
The Holy Spirit understands the deep
things of God. He takes what belongs to

cue-1113
01:14:08.934 --> 01:14:11.154
Christ and makes it known to us.

cue-1114
01:14:12.054 --> 01:14:13.834
God knows the mind of the Spirit,

cue-1115
01:14:14.714 --> 01:14:19.714
so we pray in the Spirit, taught and
guided by Him, and He also prays for

cue-1116
01:14:19.714 --> 01:14:21.734
us in ways beyond words.

cue-1117
01:14:23.084 --> 01:14:25.774
This is how prayer truly works in the New
Testament.

cue-1118
01:14:27.114 --> 01:14:31.234
Even though I did not understand it at the
time, this is what happened to me when

cue-1119
01:14:31.234 --> 01:14:35.774
God gave me new understanding, new joy,
and new power in prayer.

cue-1120
01:14:37.034 --> 01:14:41.394
A new person came to live within me and
made my heart his place of worship.

cue-1121
01:14:42.634 --> 01:14:45.234
So now I live, but not by my own strength.

cue-1122
01:14:46.154 --> 01:14:49.014
In the same way, I pray, but not by
myself.

cue-1123
01:14:49.954 --> 01:14:53.654
I pray in the Spirit, and the Spirit
himself prays within me.

cue-1124
01:14:55.294 --> 01:14:57.074
The Spirit helping our weakness.

cue-1125
01:14:59.254 --> 01:15:02.654
The Holy Spirit teaches and guides all
true prayer.

cue-1126
01:15:03.694 --> 01:15:07.574
It is very true that we do not know what
we should pray for as we ought.

cue-1127
01:15:08.294 --> 01:15:12.474
There is no area where we reach the limits
of our understanding more quickly than in

cue-1128
01:15:12.474 --> 01:15:17.084
prayer. We usually pray for things that
feel urgent and obvious,

cue-1129
01:15:18.094 --> 01:15:22.874
but we cannot see deeply enough or far
enough to know what we truly need.

cue-1130
01:15:24.014 --> 01:15:28.783
Most people want good health, a
comfortable home, pleasant circumstances,

cue-1131
01:15:28.783 --> 01:15:32.514
happy friendships, more money, and
greater success.

cue-1132
01:15:33.714 --> 01:15:36.903
But who can be sure these things are truly
best for them?

cue-1133
01:15:38.114 --> 01:15:42.934
God sees much more than we do, and his
will may be different.

cue-1134
01:15:42.934 --> 01:15:45.903
Many people have prayed with deep sorrow
for someone to live

cue-1135
01:15:46.594 --> 01:15:49.894
and later came to thank God that he took
them when he did.

cue-1136
01:15:50.874 --> 01:15:54.354
God knew what was ahead and spared them
from what was to come.

cue-1137
01:15:55.224 --> 01:15:58.634
The Holy Spirit knows the mind of Christ
and the will of God.

cue-1138
01:15:59.314 --> 01:16:02.654
He teaches us both how to pray and what to
pray for.

cue-1139
01:16:03.354 --> 01:16:08.114
If anyone lacks wisdom, they should ask
God not only for answers,

cue-1140
01:16:08.114 --> 01:16:12.654
but for the spirit of wisdom who teaches,
strengthens, and guides.

cue-1141
01:16:14.274 --> 01:16:19.254
The Holy Spirit also shapes the right
conditions for prayer. We can ask

cue-1142
01:16:19.254 --> 01:16:24.194
wrongly, not only in what we ask, but in
why we ask it. He

cue-1143
01:16:24.194 --> 01:16:28.094
makes our desires pure and brings them
into agreement with God's will

cue-1144
01:16:28.734 --> 01:16:32.314
so that we begin to desire what God
desires to give.

cue-1145
01:16:33.534 --> 01:16:38.114
That is why when we delight ourselves in
the Lord, He gives us the desires of our

cue-1146
01:16:38.114 --> 01:16:41.494
hearts because our desires have become
like His.

cue-1147
01:16:42.734 --> 01:16:47.734
The Spirit also expresses the deep needs
of our souls, even when we can't put them

cue-1148
01:16:47.734 --> 01:16:48.454
into words.

cue-1149
01:16:49.634 --> 01:16:54.634
His deep stirrings come before our
prayers, and our prayers grow out of what

cue-1150
01:16:54.634 --> 01:16:56.194
He is already doing within us.

cue-1151
01:16:57.794 --> 01:17:00.094
In Him, we find everything we need for
prayer:

cue-1152
01:17:00.694 --> 01:17:04.964
life, desire, wisdom, faith, intercession,
and power.

cue-1153
01:17:05.664 --> 01:17:10.334
He awakens desire, purifies our motives,
gives us confidence, and

cue-1154
01:17:10.334 --> 01:17:11.574
strengthens our faith.

cue-1155
01:17:13.464 --> 01:17:14.754
The prayer of the Spirit.

cue-1156
01:17:17.334 --> 01:17:19.134
This is the true meaning of prayer.

cue-1157
01:17:19.794 --> 01:17:24.534
It is more than asking for things. It is
sharing life with God. It is

cue-1158
01:17:24.534 --> 01:17:29.514
fellowship, partnership, and unity with
the Father and the Son through the Holy

cue-1159
01:17:29.514 --> 01:17:29.914
Spirit.

cue-1160
01:17:30.874 --> 01:17:35.814
Prayer is more than words. In fact, it is
often strongest when no words

cue-1161
01:17:35.814 --> 01:17:36.384
are spoken.

cue-1162
01:17:37.134 --> 01:17:42.004
It is more than making requests, for it
reaches its highest point when it simply

cue-1163
01:17:42.004 --> 01:17:44.214
worships and asks for nothing.

cue-1164
01:17:45.374 --> 01:17:49.474
A child once walked into his father's
study and came up to him at his desk.

cue-1165
01:17:50.354 --> 01:17:51.774
The father turned and said,

cue-1166
01:17:52.574 --> 01:17:53.474
"What do you want, son?"

cue-1167
01:17:54.554 --> 01:17:55.554
The child replied,

cue-1168
01:17:56.224 --> 01:17:58.474
"Nothing, Dad. I just wanted to be with
you."

cue-1169
01:17:59.744 --> 01:18:02.914
This mystery of the Spirit is the key to
many other mysteries.

cue-1170
01:18:03.824 --> 01:18:08.584
The Lord shares his secrets with those who
pray in close fellowship with the Spirit.

cue-1171
01:18:08.584 --> 01:18:13.234
There are different levels of prayer. At
one level, we

cue-1172
01:18:13.234 --> 01:18:15.294
pray and ask God to help us.

cue-1173
01:18:16.314 --> 01:18:17.684
But there is a higher way

cue-1174
01:18:18.434 --> 01:18:23.414
where the Spirit prays and we agree with
Him. His prayer becomes

cue-1175
01:18:23.414 --> 01:18:24.074
our prayer.

cue-1176
01:18:24.774 --> 01:18:29.414
He prays within our hearts while our Lord
continually prays for us at the

cue-1177
01:18:29.414 --> 01:18:30.514
Father's right hand.

cue-1178
01:18:31.414 --> 01:18:36.314
The Spirit within us works in us, shaping
our desires and actions so

cue-1179
01:18:36.314 --> 01:18:39.414
that we follow the will and purpose of our
Father in heaven.

cue-1180
01:18:40.594 --> 01:18:44.354
He is God the Spirit, representing both
the Father and the Son,

cue-1181
01:18:45.134 --> 01:18:46.974
and the three are one God.

cue-1182
01:18:48.134 --> 01:18:50.014
He is the power working within us.

cue-1183
01:18:50.854 --> 01:18:55.594
He brings hearts together in prayer and
makes them united and strong in

cue-1184
01:18:55.594 --> 01:18:56.274
intercession.

cue-1185
01:18:57.414 --> 01:19:00.854
The confidence that our prayers are
answered comes from Him.

cue-1186
01:19:01.954 --> 01:19:06.882
He makes prayer the most powerful force in
God's kingdom.The secret of

cue-1187
01:19:06.882 --> 01:19:07.882
it all is in Him.

cue-1188
01:19:08.491 --> 01:19:13.482
The power of it all comes through Him. The
joy of it all is found with Him. The

cue-1189
01:19:13.482 --> 01:19:17.922
greatest thing God ever did for me was to
teach me how to pray in the Spirit.

cue-1190
01:19:18.842 --> 01:19:23.362
We are not truly people of prayer in the
fullest sense until we are filled with the

cue-1191
01:19:23.362 --> 01:19:24.142
Holy Spirit.

cue-1192
01:19:25.402 --> 01:19:26.102
So we pray,

cue-1193
01:19:26.722 --> 01:19:29.542
Lord, teach us to pray in the Spirit.

cue-1194
01:19:32.622 --> 01:19:33.222
Chapter Eight:

cue-1195
01:19:33.982 --> 01:19:35.562
Praying to God Our Father.

cue-1196
01:19:37.942 --> 01:19:40.922
Jesus based prayer on a personal
relationship.

cue-1197
01:19:41.962 --> 01:19:46.742
He taught us to call God our Father, and
this truth of being His children changes

cue-1198
01:19:46.742 --> 01:19:47.842
everything about prayer.

cue-1199
01:19:48.962 --> 01:19:53.532
Even if some difficulties remain, there
must be communication between a father and

cue-1200
01:19:53.532 --> 01:19:54.211
his child.

cue-1201
01:19:55.402 --> 01:20:00.022
To say that a child cannot ask anything
from a father would take away the meaning

cue-1202
01:20:00.022 --> 01:20:01.062
of both words.

cue-1203
01:20:02.222 --> 01:20:06.982
A child has the right to ask, and a father
has the responsibility to

cue-1204
01:20:06.982 --> 01:20:09.262
listen with love and understanding.

cue-1205
01:20:10.361 --> 01:20:15.082
The true wonder is not that God answers
prayer, but that He is our Father.

cue-1206
01:20:15.942 --> 01:20:20.882
Once we understand that, prayer becomes
natural and reasonable. If

cue-1207
01:20:20.882 --> 01:20:24.222
God is truly our Father, then prayer must
be possible.

cue-1208
01:20:25.122 --> 01:20:28.822
God would not be a father if His children
could not come to Him in

cue-1209
01:20:28.822 --> 01:20:33.822
prayer. All that Jesus taught about having
a childlike heart in God's

cue-1210
01:20:33.822 --> 01:20:38.142
kingdom would make no sense if God were
not truly our Father.

cue-1211
01:20:39.542 --> 01:20:44.202
This relationship means we can come to Him
freely, closely, and

cue-1212
01:20:44.202 --> 01:20:48.842
without fear. Some children of great men
have thought of their fathers

cue-1213
01:20:48.842 --> 01:20:51.942
as distant figures instead of loving
parents.

cue-1214
01:20:52.922 --> 01:20:57.282
In the same way, some people think of God
as only an authority or an

cue-1215
01:20:57.282 --> 01:20:57.992
institution.

cue-1216
01:20:59.122 --> 01:21:01.222
But this is not how Jesus revealed Him.

cue-1217
01:21:02.942 --> 01:21:03.962
Our Father in Heaven.

cue-1218
01:21:05.982 --> 01:21:10.982
Calling God our Father does not lessen His
greatness. He is still the Holy and Most

cue-1219
01:21:10.982 --> 01:21:13.422
High God, the one who lives forever.

cue-1220
01:21:14.422 --> 01:21:18.542
When Jesus spoke of God caring for
sparrows and lilies in the Sermon on the

cue-1221
01:21:18.542 --> 01:21:23.542
Mount, He did not take away anything from
the greatness seen in Isaiah's vision.

cue-1222
01:21:24.562 --> 01:21:29.282
The everlasting God, the Lord, the creator
of the ends of the earth.

cue-1223
01:21:30.402 --> 01:21:35.402
He is still the King eternal, immortal,
invisible, the only

cue-1224
01:21:35.402 --> 01:21:40.382
wise God, the blessed and only ruler, the
King of Kings and Lord

cue-1225
01:21:40.382 --> 01:21:45.362
of Lords, who alone is immortal and lives
in unapproachable light, whom

cue-1226
01:21:45.362 --> 01:21:47.842
no one has seen or can see.

cue-1227
01:21:48.562 --> 01:21:53.282
There are many descriptions of God's glory
and greatness, and it is good to think

cue-1228
01:21:53.282 --> 01:21:58.032
about them with worship and awe. But Jesus
Christ brought all of this

cue-1229
01:21:58.032 --> 01:21:59.692
into a personal relationship.

cue-1230
01:22:00.542 --> 01:22:01.502
He is our Father.

cue-1231
01:22:02.142 --> 01:22:06.462
That is the greatest truth of all. To a
child, he is simply

cue-1232
01:22:06.462 --> 01:22:10.882
father. Others may feel afraid, but a
child does not.

cue-1233
01:22:12.062 --> 01:22:15.542
I remember when I was young being invited
to visit the parsonage.

cue-1234
01:22:16.202 --> 01:22:20.422
I was so nervous that I walked past the
door several times before I found the

cue-1235
01:22:20.422 --> 01:22:21.322
courage to knock.

cue-1236
01:22:22.322 --> 01:22:24.222
My heart was pounding as I stood there.

cue-1237
01:22:24.882 --> 01:22:29.362
But when I was let inside, I was surprised
to see the respected minister on the

cue-1238
01:22:29.362 --> 01:22:31.282
floor playing with his children.

cue-1239
01:22:32.462 --> 01:22:37.262
They were laughing, climbing on him, and
even using his long beard like

cue-1240
01:22:37.262 --> 01:22:38.802
reins as if he were a horse.

cue-1241
01:22:39.762 --> 01:22:40.702
He was their father.

cue-1242
01:22:41.391 --> 01:22:44.142
They did not feel the fear that others
felt toward him.

cue-1243
01:22:45.282 --> 01:22:50.242
As they grew older and began to understand
his importance, their respect increased,

cue-1244
01:22:50.242 --> 01:22:53.162
but their confidence and freedom with him
did not change.

cue-1245
01:22:54.702 --> 01:22:57.862
Children in their father's house are free
and unafraid.

cue-1246
01:23:00.022 --> 01:23:02.202
Pray to the Father who is in secret.

cue-1247
01:23:04.762 --> 01:23:08.182
Heaven itself cannot contain God our
Father,

cue-1248
01:23:08.222 --> 01:23:10.482
yet He is present in the inner place of
the soul.

cue-1249
01:23:11.502 --> 01:23:14.482
He is there in secret, and He sees in
secret.

cue-1250
01:23:15.422 --> 01:23:18.252
He waits for us to open the door of our
hearts to Him.

cue-1251
01:23:19.292 --> 01:23:24.262
This is holy ground and should be
approached with reverence. The soul must

cue-1252
01:23:24.262 --> 01:23:27.282
gather all its strength for this highest
act of prayer.

cue-1253
01:23:28.562 --> 01:23:33.522
Here, the mind must be clear and focused,
thinking deeply about God

cue-1254
01:23:33.522 --> 01:23:34.602
and about life.

cue-1255
01:23:35.822 --> 01:23:40.042
Thinking about God is more than just
thinking our own ideas about Him.

cue-1256
01:23:41.202 --> 01:23:44.702
True fellowship with Him goes deeper than
any study or teaching.

cue-1257
01:23:45.602 --> 01:23:50.522
Private prayer is life itself, speaking in
the awareness that God our Father is

cue-1258
01:23:50.522 --> 01:23:50.982
present.

cue-1259
01:23:51.862 --> 01:23:56.661
Before Him, everything is opened
willingly, all pretending is removed from

cue-1260
01:23:56.662 --> 01:23:57.302
our motives,

cue-1261
01:23:57.922 --> 01:24:02.402
all false desire is stripped away, and all
dishonesty is taken from our

cue-1262
01:24:02.402 --> 01:24:02.942
words.

cue-1263
01:24:04.322 --> 01:24:07.612
Quietness is the best preparation before
speaking to God.

cue-1264
01:24:08.842 --> 01:24:13.582
When we understand His greatness as our
Father, it gives new meaning to His

cue-1265
01:24:13.582 --> 01:24:13.982
glory,

cue-1266
01:24:14.922 --> 01:24:19.682
and prayer opens up new depths when we see
the majesty of our Father in Heaven.

cue-1267
01:24:20.662 --> 01:24:25.102
If God is our Father, then we can pray.
But if He is such a loving

cue-1268
01:24:25.102 --> 01:24:27.402
father, why do we need to pray at all?

cue-1269
01:24:28.482 --> 01:24:29.122
Jesus said,

cue-1270
01:24:29.862 --> 01:24:34.702
"When you pray, do not keep repeating
empty words like those who do not

cue-1271
01:24:34.702 --> 01:24:38.902
know God. They think they will be heard
because of their many words.

cue-1272
01:24:39.552 --> 01:24:43.642
Do not be like them, for your Father knows
what you need before you ask Him."

cue-1273
01:24:44.862 --> 01:24:45.712
So why ask?

cue-1274
01:24:46.462 --> 01:24:51.402
We do not pray to give God information. He
already knows. We do not

cue-1275
01:24:51.402 --> 01:24:56.382
pray to persuade Him. His love does not
need to be convinced. No good father

cue-1276
01:24:56.382 --> 01:24:59.282
would give his child a stone when he asks
for bread

cue-1277
01:24:59.922 --> 01:25:02.222
or something harmful when he asks for
food.

cue-1278
01:25:03.382 --> 01:25:08.242
A father's wisdom and love work together
to meet real needs, not to mock

cue-1279
01:25:08.242 --> 01:25:13.054
them.Even human fathers, though imperfect,
know how to

cue-1280
01:25:13.054 --> 01:25:14.074
care for their children.

cue-1281
01:25:15.114 --> 01:25:19.134
If you, though you are sinful, know how to
give good gifts to your children,

cue-1282
01:25:20.154 --> 01:25:24.394
how much more will your Father in heaven
give good things to those who ask him?

cue-1283
01:25:25.894 --> 01:25:27.874
Ask and it will be given to you;

cue-1284
01:25:28.494 --> 01:25:33.154
seek and you will find; knock and the door
will be opened to you.

cue-1285
01:25:33.814 --> 01:25:38.394
For everyone who asks receives; the one
who seeks finds,

cue-1286
01:25:38.394 --> 01:25:42.134
and to the one who knocks, the door will
be opened

cue-1287
01:25:43.974 --> 01:25:45.434
if you call on him as Father.

cue-1288
01:25:47.794 --> 01:25:50.994
We are not trying here to solve every
question about prayer.

cue-1289
01:25:51.674 --> 01:25:56.114
We want to learn how to pray, and empty
arguments do not help us do that.

cue-1290
01:25:57.154 --> 01:26:01.664
When a person goes into prayer, no part of
that person should be left behind.

cue-1291
01:26:02.814 --> 01:26:07.714
Reason is a gift from God just as much as
emotion is, and if either one is

cue-1292
01:26:07.714 --> 01:26:11.774
separated from the other, the soul becomes
weak and incomplete.

cue-1293
01:26:12.874 --> 01:26:17.634
Love may sometimes see what reason cannot,
but reason helps guard that

cue-1294
01:26:17.634 --> 01:26:19.384
vision and apply it to life.

cue-1295
01:26:20.584 --> 01:26:24.974
Our spiritual life is built on knowing
God, but this is not a knowledge that

cue-1296
01:26:24.974 --> 01:26:26.854
human effort alone can gain.

cue-1297
01:26:27.834 --> 01:26:30.294
Love is what binds us to God in prayer.

cue-1298
01:26:31.394 --> 01:26:36.114
If we try to explain love only by reason,
we can cool its warmth.

cue-1299
01:26:37.154 --> 01:26:41.454
But if reason is pushed aside, emotion can
become uncontrolled.

cue-1300
01:26:42.654 --> 01:26:44.874
Study and preaching both have their place,

cue-1301
01:26:45.514 --> 01:26:50.494
but the inner place of prayer should be
set apart. There, prayer

cue-1302
01:26:50.494 --> 01:26:54.934
gives light to our thinking, and our
thinking feeds the fire of the heart.

cue-1303
01:26:56.154 --> 01:26:59.224
Seeing God as Father is the key to
understanding prayer.

cue-1304
01:26:59.914 --> 01:27:01.514
God is more than Creator.

cue-1305
01:27:02.154 --> 01:27:06.534
He is our Father, our heavenly Father,
holy Father, righteous

cue-1306
01:27:06.534 --> 01:27:11.514
Father. He is the God of love, and he is
also the God of

cue-1307
01:27:11.514 --> 01:27:11.914
law.

cue-1308
01:27:13.064 --> 01:27:18.014
The Sabbath was made for man, and God's
universe was made for the family of God

cue-1309
01:27:20.734 --> 01:27:22.234
in the glory of his Father.

cue-1310
01:27:24.834 --> 01:27:29.814
The fact that we pray to God as our Father
in heaven teaches us much about how we

cue-1311
01:27:29.814 --> 01:27:30.394
should pray.

cue-1312
01:27:31.474 --> 01:27:33.934
The Son of God delighted in his Father's
glory.

cue-1313
01:27:34.574 --> 01:27:38.574
He often rose early to look upon his glory
and enjoy his presence.

cue-1314
01:27:39.414 --> 01:27:43.143
He rejoiced in the Father's greatness and
in the majesty of his power.

cue-1315
01:27:44.334 --> 01:27:47.483
It is good to think carefully about what
Jesus said of the Father,

cue-1316
01:27:48.164 --> 01:27:48.834
"My Father."

cue-1317
01:27:49.834 --> 01:27:53.974
Every time he spoke those words, they were
full of love and honor.

cue-1318
01:27:55.034 --> 01:28:00.034
God is spirit, and those who worship him
must worship in spirit and truth,

cue-1319
01:28:00.034 --> 01:28:02.734
for the Father is seeking such people to
worship him.

cue-1320
01:28:03.794 --> 01:28:04.374
"My Father

cue-1321
01:28:05.114 --> 01:28:06.034
is greater than all.

cue-1322
01:28:07.114 --> 01:28:08.454
I and the Father are one."

cue-1323
01:28:09.374 --> 01:28:12.994
Jesus loved to speak about the Father's
care and generous love.

cue-1324
01:28:13.754 --> 01:28:18.694
Nothing is too small for him. Each person
matters to him as though there were no

cue-1325
01:28:18.694 --> 01:28:19.274
one else.

cue-1326
01:28:19.894 --> 01:28:24.714
Even a single sparrow is not forgotten,
and human beings are so precious to

cue-1327
01:28:24.714 --> 01:28:27.654
him that even the hairs on their heads are
numbered.

cue-1328
01:28:28.834 --> 01:28:33.554
Jesus lived in complete surrender to the
will of his holy and righteous Father.

cue-1329
01:28:34.694 --> 01:28:38.834
He did not pray in order to bend the
Father's will to his own desires.

cue-1330
01:28:39.834 --> 01:28:42.334
He prayed that the Father's will would be
done.

cue-1331
01:28:43.174 --> 01:28:47.794
Even in deep suffering and agonizing
prayer, he remained obedient to the

cue-1332
01:28:47.794 --> 01:28:48.594
Father's will.

cue-1333
01:28:50.154 --> 01:28:53.094
Because we pray to our heavenly Father in
the secret place,

cue-1334
01:28:53.714 --> 01:28:56.694
we can come with the simple openness of
little children.

cue-1335
01:28:57.754 --> 01:29:00.934
There is nothing too small or too great to
bring to him.

cue-1336
01:29:01.754 --> 01:29:05.774
We come as his children, and we trust him
as our Father in heaven.

cue-1337
01:29:06.874 --> 01:29:09.434
His answer will often be greater than what
we ask.

cue-1338
01:29:10.234 --> 01:29:12.474
Prayer itself teaches and trains us.

cue-1339
01:29:13.354 --> 01:29:18.134
The Holy Spirit instructs us in the school
of prayer. A true father blesses not

cue-1340
01:29:18.134 --> 01:29:20.774
only with readiness but also with wisdom.

cue-1341
01:29:21.954 --> 01:29:26.654
Sometimes God waits for the right time.
Sometimes the answer is given long

cue-1342
01:29:26.654 --> 01:29:28.694
before the person who prayed knows it.

cue-1343
01:29:29.334 --> 01:29:29.874
But still,

cue-1344
01:29:30.494 --> 01:29:32.774
everyone who asks receives.

cue-1345
01:29:34.114 --> 01:29:39.114
As Adoniram Judson lay dying, he heard of
a striking answer to a prayer he

cue-1346
01:29:39.114 --> 01:29:42.614
had offered for the Jews while serving as
a missionary in Burma.

cue-1347
01:29:43.694 --> 01:29:44.074
He said,

cue-1348
01:29:44.954 --> 01:29:49.894
"I never prayed sincerely and earnestly
for anything unless it came.

cue-1349
01:29:49.894 --> 01:29:54.734
At some time, no matter how far away,
somehow, in some form,

cue-1350
01:29:55.474 --> 01:29:58.974
often the very last way I would have
expected, it came."

cue-1351
01:30:00.734 --> 01:30:05.554
When you pray, go into your inner room,
close the door, and pray to your

cue-1352
01:30:05.554 --> 01:30:07.094
Father who is in secret,

cue-1353
01:30:08.264 --> 01:30:12.914
to him who is able to do immeasurably more
than all we ask or think.

cue-1354
01:30:16.214 --> 01:30:19.314
Chapter nine: The importunity of prayer.

cue-1355
01:30:22.034 --> 01:30:24.794
Jesus taught people to pray to God as
Father.

cue-1356
01:30:25.454 --> 01:30:30.394
This is the heart of his teaching. When
you pray, say, "Our Father, who is in

cue-1357
01:30:30.394 --> 01:30:30.694
heaven."

cue-1358
01:30:31.674 --> 01:30:33.854
He warned against showing off in prayer.

cue-1359
01:30:34.594 --> 01:30:39.474
Prayer must be in a private place with the
door shut. In that secret

cue-1360
01:30:39.474 --> 01:30:42.514
place, prayer should be simple and
sincere.

cue-1361
01:30:44.074 --> 01:30:49.014
False religion cannot survive where empty
repetition and impressive language

cue-1362
01:30:49.014 --> 01:30:49.994
are not allowed.

cue-1363
01:30:51.174 --> 01:30:54.174
Fathers and children do not make speeches
to one another.

cue-1364
01:30:54.934 --> 01:30:56.274
God is not far away.

cue-1365
01:30:56.914 --> 01:31:01.734
He is near. He does not need to be
informed because Jesus says,

cue-1366
01:31:02.354 --> 01:31:05.194
"Your Father knows what you need before
you ask him."

cue-1367
01:31:06.134 --> 01:31:10.974
He does not need to be persuaded either,
for if you, though you are sinful,

cue-1368
01:31:10.974 --> 01:31:13.494
know how to give good gifts to your
children,

cue-1369
01:31:14.214 --> 01:31:18.193
how much more will your Father in heaven
give good things to those who ask

cue-1370
01:31:18.194 --> 01:31:22.164
him?Nothing could be simpler or more
comforting.

cue-1371
01:31:23.284 --> 01:31:27.743
Ask and you will receive, for everyone who
asks

cue-1372
01:31:27.744 --> 01:31:28.484
receives.

cue-1373
01:31:30.784 --> 01:31:32.824
Importunity and persistence.

cue-1374
01:31:35.563 --> 01:31:40.424
Alongside this teaching, Jesus also gave
the parables of the friend at midnight

cue-1375
01:31:40.424 --> 01:31:41.884
and the unjust judge.

cue-1376
01:31:42.764 --> 01:31:47.224
These parables are different from many
others because they teach by contrast, not

cue-1377
01:31:47.224 --> 01:31:47.943
by likeness.

cue-1378
01:31:48.804 --> 01:31:52.744
God is not like the unwilling friend or
the unjust judge.

cue-1379
01:31:53.924 --> 01:31:57.624
So why did Jesus tell these stories? The
shared point is this.

cue-1380
01:31:58.324 --> 01:32:01.324
In both cases, persistence won the answer.

cue-1381
01:32:02.244 --> 01:32:06.644
If people are not heard because of many
words, they may still be heard because

cue-1382
01:32:06.644 --> 01:32:07.644
they keep asking.

cue-1383
01:32:08.724 --> 01:32:12.484
So what place does this kind of
persistence have in the prayers of

cue-1384
01:32:12.484 --> 01:32:17.304
children speaking to their heavenly
Father? Jesus himself prayed with

cue-1385
01:32:17.304 --> 01:32:19.504
deep feeling and persistence.

cue-1386
01:32:19.544 --> 01:32:23.184
He rose early to pray. He spent whole
nights in prayer.

cue-1387
01:32:24.204 --> 01:32:29.104
Hebrews five verse seven says that he
offered prayers and requests with loud

cue-1388
01:32:29.104 --> 01:32:30.784
cries and tears.

cue-1389
01:32:31.914 --> 01:32:34.444
The scene in Gethsemane is full of
mystery.

cue-1390
01:32:35.064 --> 01:32:39.404
He prayed to God as Father, yet his prayer
was filled with deep suffering.

cue-1391
01:32:40.584 --> 01:32:42.464
He knelt down and prayed, saying,

cue-1392
01:32:43.104 --> 01:32:46.244
"Father, if you are willing, take this cup
from me,

cue-1393
01:32:46.944 --> 01:32:50.204
yet not my will but yours be done."

cue-1394
01:32:51.484 --> 01:32:56.484
And being in deep agony, he prayed more
earnestly, and his sweat was like drops

cue-1395
01:32:56.484 --> 01:32:58.424
of blood falling to the ground.

cue-1396
01:32:59.624 --> 01:33:04.384
Matthew twenty-six, verses thirty-eight to
forty-six tells us that he prayed the

cue-1397
01:33:04.384 --> 01:33:06.124
same words three times.

cue-1398
01:33:07.144 --> 01:33:11.984
Jesus did many mighty works. He calmed
storms, cast out demons,

cue-1399
01:33:11.984 --> 01:33:13.384
and raised the dead.

cue-1400
01:33:14.384 --> 01:33:16.824
In none of these do we see strain or
struggle.

cue-1401
01:33:17.524 --> 01:33:22.404
Power went out from him, and his work made
him tired. Yet there was always a sense

cue-1402
01:33:22.404 --> 01:33:24.764
of authority and ease in what he did.

cue-1403
01:33:25.944 --> 01:33:27.424
But of his praying it is said,

cue-1404
01:33:28.203 --> 01:33:30.064
"As he prayed, he sweat."

cue-1405
01:33:31.084 --> 01:33:33.764
He prayed in agony, even to the point of
blood.

cue-1406
01:33:35.004 --> 01:33:36.144
If God is Father,

cue-1407
01:33:36.884 --> 01:33:39.924
why was there such agony in the prayers of
his Son?

cue-1408
01:33:41.784 --> 01:33:43.084
Prayer and supplication.

cue-1409
01:33:45.584 --> 01:33:50.384
There is a group of words that broadens
our understanding of prayer and shows that

cue-1410
01:33:50.384 --> 01:33:54.084
it is not always as easy and simple as it
may first seem.

cue-1411
01:33:55.284 --> 01:34:00.024
The man who came at midnight was ready to
beg, plead, and keep asking

cue-1412
01:34:00.024 --> 01:34:01.634
until his request was granted.

cue-1413
01:34:02.794 --> 01:34:07.704
That does not sound much like a child
speaking to a heavenly Father. God is not

cue-1414
01:34:07.704 --> 01:34:12.684
like that unwilling friend, but prayer
that wins an answer can look like that

cue-1415
01:34:12.684 --> 01:34:13.854
kind of persistence.

cue-1416
01:34:14.794 --> 01:34:17.504
The same is true in the parable of the
unjust judge.

cue-1417
01:34:18.244 --> 01:34:22.744
God is not like that judge, but prayer can
still involve pleading and

cue-1418
01:34:22.744 --> 01:34:24.864
continuing until the answer comes.

cue-1419
01:34:25.924 --> 01:34:27.504
A petition simply asks.

cue-1420
01:34:28.104 --> 01:34:32.204
Supplication begs earnestly. Pleading
presents reasons.

cue-1421
01:34:33.744 --> 01:34:36.804
Job wanted a chance to present his case
before God.

cue-1422
01:34:37.884 --> 01:34:39.884
"Oh, that I knew where I might find him,

cue-1423
01:34:40.504 --> 01:34:42.464
that I might come even to his seat.

cue-1424
01:34:43.124 --> 01:34:47.764
I would lay my case before him and fill my
mouth with arguments. I would know the

cue-1425
01:34:47.764 --> 01:34:51.294
words he would answer me and understand
what he would say to me."

cue-1426
01:34:52.704 --> 01:34:56.644
God invites us to reason with him, and
prayer is given the freedom to

cue-1427
01:34:56.644 --> 01:35:01.244
plead. But if God is our Father, if he
already knows our

cue-1428
01:35:01.244 --> 01:35:03.004
needs and is ready to hear us,

cue-1429
01:35:03.634 --> 01:35:06.404
why should prayer include begging and
pleading?

cue-1430
01:35:08.364 --> 01:35:09.664
Striving and wrestling.

cue-1431
01:35:12.424 --> 01:35:13.704
When Peter was in prison,

cue-1432
01:35:14.364 --> 01:35:17.224
earnest prayer for him was made to God by
the church.

cue-1433
01:35:18.094 --> 01:35:22.024
They kept praying through the night and
continued until the answer came.

cue-1434
01:35:23.044 --> 01:35:26.904
We see the same kind of persistence in the
prayer of the Syrophoenician woman.

cue-1435
01:35:27.544 --> 01:35:32.224
She held on and would not give up until
Jesus praised her faith and

cue-1436
01:35:32.224 --> 01:35:33.424
granted her request.

cue-1437
01:35:34.604 --> 01:35:37.564
The New Testament often connects prayer
with striving.

cue-1438
01:35:38.324 --> 01:35:40.424
Paul urges the Christians in Rome,

cue-1439
01:35:41.054 --> 01:35:45.984
"By our Lord Jesus Christ and by the love
of the Spirit, strive together with

cue-1440
01:35:45.984 --> 01:35:50.104
me in your prayers to God for me." Romans
fifteen thirty.

cue-1441
01:35:51.124 --> 01:35:56.084
He praises Epaphras as a faithful pastor
who labored earnestly in prayer,

cue-1442
01:35:56.084 --> 01:35:57.264
Colossians four twelve.

cue-1443
01:35:58.104 --> 01:36:02.504
And Paul says that he himself struggled
greatly for the Colossians.

cue-1444
01:36:03.464 --> 01:36:08.444
Prayer is work. It involves effort,
struggle, and labor. But

cue-1445
01:36:08.444 --> 01:36:10.544
why should prayer require such effort?

cue-1446
01:36:11.424 --> 01:36:14.184
The idea of wrestling is also connected
with prayer.

cue-1447
01:36:14.844 --> 01:36:19.784
This does not mean that we wrestle against
God, but that prayer requires firm focus,

cue-1448
01:36:19.784 --> 01:36:22.284
determination, and watchfulness.

cue-1449
01:36:23.544 --> 01:36:28.404
It is clear that prayer is not always the
easy matter it may seem to be when we

cue-1450
01:36:28.404 --> 01:36:33.394
think only of simply asking our heavenly
Father for what we want.

cue-1451
01:36:33.394 --> 01:36:37.914
There is deep struggle in it. There is
labor in it. There is pleading in it.

cue-1452
01:36:37.914 --> 01:36:39.134
There is persistence in it.

cue-1453
01:36:40.134 --> 01:36:43.964
Perhaps Coleridge was not far from the
truth when he said that prayer is the

cue-1454
01:36:43.964 --> 01:36:48.784
highest work of which the human heart is
capable and the greatest effort in the

cue-1455
01:36:48.784 --> 01:36:50.444
Christian's battle on Earth.

cue-1456
01:36:52.264 --> 01:36:54.103
The paradox of prayer.

cue-1457
01:36:56.124 --> 01:37:00.724
Prayer is full of things that seem
opposite to each other. It is so simple

cue-1458
01:37:00.724 --> 01:37:05.404
that a child can pray and yet so deep that
the wisest people cannot fully

cue-1459
01:37:05.404 --> 01:37:06.164
explain it.

cue-1460
01:37:06.914 --> 01:37:11.894
It is so easy that even the weak can pray
and yet so demanding that it calls

cue-1461
01:37:11.894 --> 01:37:15.244
for all our energy, understanding, and
strength.

cue-1462
01:37:16.444 --> 01:37:21.404
Prayer is so natural that it seems to need
no teaching, and yet it rises so

cue-1463
01:37:21.404 --> 01:37:25.264
far above human nature that it cannot be
learned by human wisdom

cue-1464
01:37:25.264 --> 01:37:29.832
alone.Prayer is a world of its own, and no
single

cue-1465
01:37:29.832 --> 01:37:32.512
comparison from life can fully explain it.

cue-1466
01:37:33.672 --> 01:37:38.152
The relationship between father and child
means more in scripture than we often

cue-1467
01:37:38.152 --> 01:37:38.812
think today.

cue-1468
01:37:39.932 --> 01:37:44.572
Jesus spoke of God as our heavenly Father,
our holy Father, and our

cue-1469
01:37:44.572 --> 01:37:45.442
righteous Father.

cue-1470
01:37:46.332 --> 01:37:49.252
Peter speaks of him as both Father and
judge.

cue-1471
01:37:50.612 --> 01:37:55.552
The modern mind does not like the idea of
prayer that includes agony, pleading,

cue-1472
01:37:55.552 --> 01:37:58.272
striving, wrestling, and persistence.

cue-1473
01:37:59.112 --> 01:38:03.152
People think that this is not how loving
parents would want their children to come

cue-1474
01:38:03.152 --> 01:38:06.732
to them, and so they assume it must not be
the right way to pray.

cue-1475
01:38:07.872 --> 01:38:11.972
For many years, I kept with me a symbolic
check drawn on the bank of

cue-1476
01:38:11.972 --> 01:38:16.612
heaven. Dr. A.T. Pearson sent it to me
from America one Christmas.

cue-1477
01:38:17.232 --> 01:38:21.272
It was made out to the bearer and promised
to provide whatever I might need.

cue-1478
01:38:22.392 --> 01:38:27.092
On it were the words, "My God will supply
all your need according to his

cue-1479
01:38:27.092 --> 01:38:29.482
riches in glory by Christ Jesus."

cue-1480
01:38:30.532 --> 01:38:32.772
Is prayer really just like cashing a
check?

cue-1481
01:38:33.452 --> 01:38:38.232
Is it really that simple? Is God simply
standing at the counter ready to hand

cue-1482
01:38:38.232 --> 01:38:39.492
over whatever we ask?

cue-1483
01:38:40.412 --> 01:38:44.472
Experience quickly corrects anyone who
thinks that is all prayer is.

cue-1484
01:38:45.572 --> 01:38:46.752
If prayer were only that,

cue-1485
01:38:47.412 --> 01:38:50.952
why would Jesus speak of a secret place
and a closed door?

cue-1486
01:38:53.092 --> 01:38:54.032
The cost of prayer.

cue-1487
01:38:56.852 --> 01:39:01.192
If God is our Father, then we are his
children, and children should grow to be

cue-1488
01:39:01.192 --> 01:39:04.492
like their father in character, nature,
and mind.

cue-1489
01:39:05.632 --> 01:39:10.332
The holy Father is the father of holy
children. He is in the secret place, and

cue-1490
01:39:10.332 --> 01:39:11.812
we meet him there in secret.

cue-1491
01:39:12.772 --> 01:39:16.172
To be alone with God is to stand before
his judgment.

cue-1492
01:39:17.312 --> 01:39:18.332
The psalmist said,

cue-1493
01:39:19.132 --> 01:39:22.992
"If I had cherished sin in my heart, the
Lord would not have listened."

cue-1494
01:39:23.912 --> 01:39:27.052
We cannot truly pray while our own hearts
condemn us.

cue-1495
01:39:27.932 --> 01:39:31.432
God does not hand out commands the way a
store hands out goods.

cue-1496
01:39:32.352 --> 01:39:35.932
He speaks with his children and invites
them to reason with him.

cue-1497
01:39:36.802 --> 01:39:41.752
He is ready to bless, but he also blesses
with wisdom and care.

cue-1498
01:39:43.152 --> 01:39:45.652
Prayer is both a discipline and a
training.

cue-1499
01:39:46.512 --> 01:39:50.572
Jesus spoke wisely when he said not to
throw pearls before swine.

cue-1500
01:39:51.252 --> 01:39:55.932
God works in an orderly and holy way.
Intensity belongs to prayer.

cue-1501
01:39:56.592 --> 01:39:59.812
God is found by those who seek him with
all their heart.

cue-1502
01:40:00.932 --> 01:40:05.492
Wrestling prayer prevails. The earnest
prayer of a righteous person has great

cue-1503
01:40:05.492 --> 01:40:05.862
power.

cue-1504
01:40:07.512 --> 01:40:12.212
God hates false fire. We must never try to
force feelings or

cue-1505
01:40:12.212 --> 01:40:17.032
create an artificial intensity. Avoid
anything mechanical or lifeless.

cue-1506
01:40:17.032 --> 01:40:20.012
Stay away from casual and careless
prayer.

cue-1507
01:40:20.672 --> 01:40:23.612
Be cautious of easy and cheap ideas of
prayer,

cue-1508
01:40:24.272 --> 01:40:28.692
as though it were only like drawing money
from a bank or picking goods from a store.

cue-1509
01:40:28.692 --> 01:40:33.432
Methods and forms may have their place in
public or church

cue-1510
01:40:33.432 --> 01:40:33.772
prayer.

cue-1511
01:40:34.432 --> 01:40:38.412
But when you are alone with God, be truly
alone with him.

cue-1512
01:40:39.572 --> 01:40:40.832
Begin with silence.

cue-1513
01:40:41.552 --> 01:40:46.492
Speak simply. Listen humbly. Do not leave
until you have had a real sense

cue-1514
01:40:46.492 --> 01:40:47.532
of fellowship with him.

cue-1515
01:40:48.672 --> 01:40:52.932
We do not need to persuade God, but he
must train and prepare us.

cue-1516
01:40:53.812 --> 01:40:58.512
In every condition and at every time, pour
out your heart to him in

cue-1517
01:40:58.512 --> 01:41:01.072
prayer and pleading with thanksgiving.

cue-1518
01:41:02.272 --> 01:41:06.872
And if the Spirit leads you into deep
inward groaning, do not be afraid of the

cue-1519
01:41:06.872 --> 01:41:08.512
pain that can come with prayer.

cue-1520
01:41:09.692 --> 01:41:14.052
Some blessings in God's kingdom are only
received through strong and wholehearted

cue-1521
01:41:14.052 --> 01:41:14.692
seeking.

cue-1522
01:41:15.632 --> 01:41:19.432
A minister once told of a Sunday school
teacher who had become discouraged with

cue-1523
01:41:19.432 --> 01:41:21.412
his class and wanted to give it up.

cue-1524
01:41:22.592 --> 01:41:27.472
The superintendent urged him to try once
more and asked him to promise that for

cue-1525
01:41:27.472 --> 01:41:32.072
three months he would pray privately every
day for each boy in the class.

cue-1526
01:41:33.252 --> 01:41:37.712
Every boy in that class was converted, and
four of them later became

cue-1527
01:41:37.712 --> 01:41:40.492
ministers who were greatly used by God.

cue-1528
01:41:44.051 --> 01:41:44.751
Chapter Ten:

cue-1529
01:41:45.492 --> 01:41:46.872
The Reward of Prayer.

cue-1530
01:41:48.962 --> 01:41:51.592
"Your Father who sees in secret will
reward you."

cue-1531
01:41:52.872 --> 01:41:55.832
Jesus did not hesitate to connect prayer
with reward.

cue-1532
01:41:56.522 --> 01:41:59.121
And who can measure the blessings that
come through prayer?

cue-1533
01:42:00.232 --> 01:42:04.882
Even those who deny that prayer changes
outward circumstances often still

cue-1534
01:42:04.882 --> 01:42:07.372
admit that it changes the person who
prays.

cue-1535
01:42:08.392 --> 01:42:12.812
The value of a daily habit of withdrawing
from the world and meeting God in

cue-1536
01:42:12.812 --> 01:42:15.212
private is impossible to overstate.

cue-1537
01:42:16.432 --> 01:42:20.972
To think about eternal things, to turn the
mind toward what cannot be seen,

cue-1538
01:42:20.972 --> 01:42:25.652
and to honestly seek fellowship with God
rescues life from being

cue-1539
01:42:25.652 --> 01:42:27.872
restless, worried, and empty.

cue-1540
01:42:29.072 --> 01:42:34.072
Even apart from specific answers, the
influence of regular private prayer is

cue-1541
01:42:34.072 --> 01:42:34.872
beyond measure.

cue-1542
01:42:36.112 --> 01:42:39.872
I want to consider three, perhaps four,
examples.

cue-1543
01:42:40.952 --> 01:42:45.752
It has been said that the mountains of the
Bible richly reward anyone who climbs

cue-1544
01:42:45.752 --> 01:42:45.862
them,

cue-1545
01:42:46.572 --> 01:42:51.232
and no life in scripture is more filled
with mountain scenes than the life of

cue-1546
01:42:51.232 --> 01:42:51.772
Moses.

cue-1547
01:42:52.952 --> 01:42:57.722
For forty years, he wandered among lonely
mountains, tending his flock and wrestling

cue-1548
01:42:57.722 --> 01:43:00.772
with great questions about his people and
about God.

cue-1549
01:43:01.872 --> 01:43:06.692
He had been educated in all the wisdom of
Egypt, but when God wanted to teach him,

cue-1550
01:43:06.692 --> 01:43:10.432
he brought him out of the valley and up
into the mountain.

cue-1551
01:43:11.612 --> 01:43:16.252
It was there in the silence of those
ancient heights that the polished man of

cue-1552
01:43:16.252 --> 01:43:20.852
the court and the learned scholar was
prepared for the work of leading and

cue-1553
01:43:20.852 --> 01:43:22.262
delivering God's people.

cue-1554
01:43:23.832 --> 01:43:28.572
His service both began and ended on the
mountain. Before every new

cue-1555
01:43:28.572 --> 01:43:32.912
step and at every great crisis, God called
him upwards, and he

cue-1556
01:43:32.912 --> 01:43:37.576
wentWhenever the burden of his calling
became too heavy, he

cue-1557
01:43:37.576 --> 01:43:39.676
hurried to seek God on the mountain.

cue-1558
01:43:40.796 --> 01:43:44.836
What he found there is still a wonder to
the world. The mountain of God was a

cue-1559
01:43:44.836 --> 01:43:49.836
special place set apart as holy. God
commanded that boundaries be

cue-1560
01:43:49.836 --> 01:43:53.436
placed around it so that even cattle
would not wander onto it.

cue-1561
01:43:54.576 --> 01:43:57.116
Set bounds around the mountain and make it
holy.

cue-1562
01:43:58.016 --> 01:43:59.616
The people were not allowed to come near.

cue-1563
01:44:00.236 --> 01:44:02.756
Even priests and elders had to stop at the
boundary.

cue-1564
01:44:03.376 --> 01:44:05.196
No companions could go all the way.

cue-1565
01:44:05.876 --> 01:44:10.716
Even his closest friends had to remain
behind while the servant of God went

cue-1566
01:44:10.716 --> 01:44:12.236
alone into the holy place.

cue-1567
01:44:13.376 --> 01:44:17.406
The Lord told Moses to prepare himself and
come up early in the morning.

cue-1568
01:44:18.336 --> 01:44:23.116
God wants a person at his best. All these
instructions in the books of

cue-1569
01:44:23.116 --> 01:44:27.396
Moses point forward to the teaching of
Jesus in the Sermon on the Mount.

cue-1570
01:44:28.606 --> 01:44:32.616
There is a special sense in which God is
present in the secret place.

cue-1571
01:44:33.236 --> 01:44:36.636
He is there in secret, and he sees in
secret.

cue-1572
01:44:37.736 --> 01:44:41.776
God calls us up to the mountain. Come
away. Come up. Come up

cue-1573
01:44:41.776 --> 01:44:46.716
early. Before sunrise, both Jesus and
Moses were alone with God.

cue-1574
01:44:47.596 --> 01:44:51.396
Let us go up with Moses and learn what he
found on the mountain of God.

cue-1575
01:44:53.136 --> 01:44:54.676
The place of revelation.

cue-1576
01:44:56.256 --> 01:44:58.296
Moses found God on the mountain.

cue-1577
01:44:58.956 --> 01:45:00.896
Read the story in Exodus three.

cue-1578
01:45:01.976 --> 01:45:05.436
After forty years of exile because he had
tried to help God's people,

cue-1579
01:45:06.096 --> 01:45:09.996
this shepherd prince came to know the God
of Israel in a personal way.

cue-1580
01:45:11.196 --> 01:45:15.186
He was not completely unfamiliar with God
while he was still in Egypt.

cue-1581
01:45:16.066 --> 01:45:19.576
He had already turned away from the
privileges and pleasures of the royal

cue-1582
01:45:19.576 --> 01:45:19.986
palace

cue-1583
01:45:20.636 --> 01:45:23.776
and chosen to stand with the suffering
people of his own race.

cue-1584
01:45:24.976 --> 01:45:29.796
He had shown great zeal for God, but he
had never received a personal revelation

cue-1585
01:45:29.796 --> 01:45:31.816
of him until that day on the mountain.

cue-1586
01:45:32.996 --> 01:45:35.656
Many people serve God in outward ways.

cue-1587
01:45:36.256 --> 01:45:41.196
Many work and suffer for Him, yet never
enter the holy place of close fellowship

cue-1588
01:45:41.196 --> 01:45:43.276
where God makes Himself known.

cue-1589
01:45:44.236 --> 01:45:49.056
It is there in secret that He reveals
Himself in a way He does not reveal

cue-1590
01:45:49.056 --> 01:45:52.136
Himself to those who have no inner place
of prayer.

cue-1591
01:45:53.316 --> 01:45:56.456
Moses also discovered himself when he
found God.

cue-1592
01:45:57.416 --> 01:46:02.396
That is not always pleasant, and it
usually is not. He was a disappointed

cue-1593
01:46:02.396 --> 01:46:07.356
reformer. He had sacrificed much for
Israel only to find the

cue-1594
01:46:07.356 --> 01:46:11.856
people resisting him, doubting his
motives, and mistrusting his purpose.

cue-1595
01:46:13.116 --> 01:46:17.356
For forty years, he had thought about a
wicked king and a weak,

cue-1596
01:46:17.356 --> 01:46:22.056
ungrateful people. He carried his hurt
like a martyr and the

cue-1597
01:46:22.056 --> 01:46:26.836
sadness of a failed leader. Then the voice
from the fire said,

cue-1598
01:46:27.516 --> 01:46:29.176
"Put your hand inside your cloak."

cue-1599
01:46:30.476 --> 01:46:34.256
When he did, his hand became leprous,
white as snow.

cue-1600
01:46:35.336 --> 01:46:36.116
This shocked him.

cue-1601
01:46:36.876 --> 01:46:41.476
He had thought the problem was in others,
but now he saw that his own heart and

cue-1602
01:46:41.476 --> 01:46:43.536
hands were not clean either.

cue-1603
01:46:44.916 --> 01:46:49.276
This is the kind of discovery people make
on God's mountain, and one reason why we

cue-1604
01:46:49.276 --> 01:46:50.736
are often slow to go there.

cue-1605
01:46:51.716 --> 01:46:53.896
But Moses found more than his sin.

cue-1606
01:46:54.556 --> 01:46:59.556
He found himself. He found hidden
strength. He found his calling. He

cue-1607
01:46:59.556 --> 01:47:04.496
discovered that the staff he carried every
day was a sign and tool of

cue-1608
01:47:04.496 --> 01:47:05.256
God's power.

cue-1609
01:47:06.476 --> 01:47:10.716
When God reveals Himself to us, He also
reveals us to ourselves.

cue-1610
01:47:11.536 --> 01:47:13.876
Moses found the will of God on the
mountain.

cue-1611
01:47:14.536 --> 01:47:19.496
There he received the law. After forty
days alone with God, he came

cue-1612
01:47:19.496 --> 01:47:23.136
down carrying heaven's laws on two stone
tablets.

cue-1613
01:47:23.996 --> 01:47:28.096
Those laws still stand as the foundation
of just government among

cue-1614
01:47:28.096 --> 01:47:32.576
people. Even after many centuries, they
remain basic to

cue-1615
01:47:32.576 --> 01:47:33.416
civilization.

cue-1616
01:47:34.316 --> 01:47:39.016
He received not only the commandments that
would guide human life for all time, but

cue-1617
01:47:39.016 --> 01:47:41.996
also detailed instructions for daily
matters.

cue-1618
01:47:43.156 --> 01:47:45.636
Look at the directions for building the
tabernacle.

cue-1619
01:47:46.316 --> 01:47:47.816
Nothing was too small to matter.

cue-1620
01:47:48.416 --> 01:47:53.216
Nails, fringes, tongs, and snuffers were
all included. Every

cue-1621
01:47:53.216 --> 01:47:57.996
detail was planned on the mountain. Every
pattern was fixed and approved by

cue-1622
01:47:57.996 --> 01:47:58.416
God.

cue-1623
01:47:59.436 --> 01:48:04.195
The way to the mountain is still open. The
pattern for each life can still be seen

cue-1624
01:48:04.196 --> 01:48:06.116
in the secret place with God.

cue-1625
01:48:07.136 --> 01:48:10.816
Even the humblest follower of Jesus may
know God's will directly.

cue-1626
01:48:11.676 --> 01:48:15.156
Every believer has the privilege of being
fully sure of God's will.

cue-1627
01:48:16.736 --> 01:48:18.976
God's attention to detail is amazing.

cue-1628
01:48:19.596 --> 01:48:21.496
Nothing is too small for His wisdom.

cue-1629
01:48:22.116 --> 01:48:25.716
Go straight to Him. Do not depend first on
other people.

cue-1630
01:48:26.376 --> 01:48:31.276
Bring every question openly before Him,
and He will make His will clear to you.

cue-1631
01:48:32.036 --> 01:48:35.676
When God speaks, His voice is plain enough
to understand.

cue-1632
01:48:36.696 --> 01:48:40.206
Questions that belong to daily life should
be settled on the mountain

cue-1633
01:48:40.916 --> 01:48:43.826
because when there is certainty with God
in the secret place,

cue-1634
01:48:44.436 --> 01:48:48.016
there will be victory in ordinary life and
in difficult places too.

cue-1635
01:48:50.136 --> 01:48:51.096
The place of power.

cue-1636
01:48:53.036 --> 01:48:55.976
There is a striking story in Exodus
seventeen.

cue-1637
01:48:56.616 --> 01:48:58.676
It tells of Israel's first battle.

cue-1638
01:48:59.476 --> 01:49:01.456
The Amalekites attacked them at Rephidim.

cue-1639
01:49:02.256 --> 01:49:06.356
Joshua led the army in the field while
Moses went up the mountain to pray.

cue-1640
01:49:07.236 --> 01:49:10.096
The battle changed back and forth in a
remarkable way.

cue-1641
01:49:10.816 --> 01:49:13.676
First, one side seemed to win, then the
other.

cue-1642
01:49:14.636 --> 01:49:19.136
At last, it became clear that the outcome
did not depend mainly on the soldiers

cue-1643
01:49:19.136 --> 01:49:19.556
below,

cue-1644
01:49:20.216 --> 01:49:22.196
but on the prayer of those above.

cue-1645
01:49:23.336 --> 01:49:25.926
The unarmed hand of prayer ruled the
battle,

cue-1646
01:49:26.876 --> 01:49:31.596
and whenever Moses held up his hand,
Israel prevailed, and whenever he lowered

cue-1647
01:49:31.596 --> 01:49:33.716
his hand, Amalek prevailed.

cue-1648
01:49:34.696 --> 01:49:35.716
The lesson is clear.

cue-1649
01:49:36.436 --> 01:49:41.192
Power is one reward of prayer.It takes us
a long time to

cue-1650
01:49:41.192 --> 01:49:44.402
learn that prayer is more important than
organization,

cue-1651
01:49:45.052 --> 01:49:49.592
more powerful than armies, more
influential than wealth, and stronger than

cue-1652
01:49:49.592 --> 01:49:50.342
human learning.

cue-1653
01:49:51.462 --> 01:49:55.872
Prayer that prevails makes people
unconquerable. Those who prevail in the

cue-1654
01:49:55.872 --> 01:49:59.512
secret place with God cannot truly be
defeated anywhere.

cue-1655
01:50:00.672 --> 01:50:03.152
All things are possible through secret
prayer.

cue-1656
01:50:04.992 --> 01:50:06.552
The place of fellowship.

cue-1657
01:50:09.412 --> 01:50:14.192
On the mountain, the Lord spoke with Moses
face to face as a man speaks with his

cue-1658
01:50:14.192 --> 01:50:14.592
friend.

cue-1659
01:50:15.592 --> 01:50:19.001
Like Abraham, Moses was brought into
friendship with God.

cue-1660
01:50:19.852 --> 01:50:23.112
He did not come only to make requests or
receive commands.

cue-1661
01:50:23.712 --> 01:50:26.732
He came for fellowship, for close
communion with God.

cue-1662
01:50:27.922 --> 01:50:32.712
The inner room of prayer is like a place
where the soul meets God in friendship and

cue-1663
01:50:32.712 --> 01:50:33.772
open sharing.

cue-1664
01:50:34.672 --> 01:50:37.312
It is a place for listening as well as
speaking.

cue-1665
01:50:38.372 --> 01:50:43.172
The most important part of prayer is not
only what we say to God, but what God

cue-1666
01:50:43.172 --> 01:50:43.952
says to us.

cue-1667
01:50:44.791 --> 01:50:46.172
It is not a place for hurry.

cue-1668
01:50:46.822 --> 01:50:50.152
The soul must become quiet and wait before
the Lord.

cue-1669
01:50:51.632 --> 01:50:54.512
The mountain is also the place of
intercession.

cue-1670
01:50:55.752 --> 01:51:00.232
Exodus thirty-two, verses nine to fourteen
tells how Moses pleaded for

cue-1671
01:51:00.232 --> 01:51:03.252
Israel. He stood in the gap for the
people.

cue-1672
01:51:03.952 --> 01:51:05.832
God looks for those who will do this.

cue-1673
01:51:06.952 --> 01:51:11.732
Ezekiel twenty-two thirty says that he
looks for someone to stand in the breach.

cue-1674
01:51:12.372 --> 01:51:16.192
God invites us to speak for others and
plead on their behalf.

cue-1675
01:51:17.112 --> 01:51:19.502
He allows himself to be approached in this
way.

cue-1676
01:51:20.232 --> 01:51:25.032
How bold Abraham was in prayer. How
courageously Moses stood before

cue-1677
01:51:25.032 --> 01:51:27.112
God and pleaded for Israel.

cue-1678
01:51:27.992 --> 01:51:30.752
How deeply Paul prayed for his fellow
Jews.

cue-1679
01:51:31.802 --> 01:51:36.472
We are commanded to pray for one another,
and no one can fully measure the blessings

cue-1680
01:51:36.472 --> 01:51:38.032
that come through intercession.

cue-1681
01:51:39.232 --> 01:51:42.252
It was on the mountain that Moses saw
God's glory.

cue-1682
01:51:43.072 --> 01:51:45.632
This is also part of the secret place of
prayer.

cue-1683
01:51:46.312 --> 01:51:51.292
It was on a mountain that Jesus was
transfigured. The glory seen there is also

cue-1684
01:51:51.292 --> 01:51:53.352
shared. Prayer changes us.

cue-1685
01:51:54.192 --> 01:51:58.892
When Moses came down from the mountain,
his face was shining, though he did not

cue-1686
01:51:58.892 --> 01:52:03.852
know it. That is the secret of true
humility with glory.

cue-1687
01:52:03.852 --> 01:52:07.172
When Jesus prayed, he was transfigured
before them.

cue-1688
01:52:07.772 --> 01:52:12.452
Glory is another reward of prayer. The
Lord who calls his servant up the

cue-1689
01:52:12.452 --> 01:52:17.271
mountain also sends him back down again.
Peter wanted to remain on the

cue-1690
01:52:17.272 --> 01:52:22.272
mountain, but we go up so that we may come
back down. There are idols

cue-1691
01:52:22.272 --> 01:52:27.092
to confront, sinful passions to overcome,
confused people to help,

cue-1692
01:52:27.092 --> 01:52:31.952
troubled fathers and broken sons and
daughters who need the vision and

cue-1693
01:52:31.952 --> 01:52:32.912
power of God.

cue-1694
01:52:34.152 --> 01:52:36.092
Come up, then go down.

cue-1695
01:52:36.802 --> 01:52:40.352
God wants us on the mountain, and he also
wants us in the valley.

cue-1696
01:52:41.232 --> 01:52:42.812
Moses died on the mountain.

cue-1697
01:52:43.512 --> 01:52:48.412
Those who go up and down at God's command
will one day go up at last and never

cue-1698
01:52:48.412 --> 01:52:49.312
come down again.

cue-1699
01:52:52.432 --> 01:52:53.172
Chapter eleven:

cue-1700
01:52:53.792 --> 01:52:54.932
The power of prayer.

cue-1701
01:52:57.712 --> 01:53:02.512
In the New Testament, Elijah is chosen as
the example of prayer. Many people in the

cue-1702
01:53:02.512 --> 01:53:07.052
Old Testament prayed and received powerful
answers from God. The scriptures are full

cue-1703
01:53:07.052 --> 01:53:10.092
of stories of those who called on God and
were delivered.

cue-1704
01:53:11.152 --> 01:53:15.672
Jacob prayed so earnestly that his name
was changed from Jacob to Israel.

cue-1705
01:53:16.802 --> 01:53:21.702
Moses was especially a man of prayer.
Through it, he was sustained, guided,

cue-1706
01:53:21.702 --> 01:53:26.652
and changed. Daniel prayed regularly and
faithfully, and

cue-1707
01:53:26.652 --> 01:53:29.012
his life was deeply shaped by prayer.

cue-1708
01:53:30.252 --> 01:53:34.212
There were many others as well, from
Abraham to the last of the prophets,

cue-1709
01:53:34.212 --> 01:53:38.952
including kings, priests, soldiers,
reformers, widows, and

cue-1710
01:53:38.952 --> 01:53:39.982
those who suffered.

cue-1711
01:53:41.232 --> 01:53:43.862
So why was Elijah chosen from among them
all?

cue-1712
01:53:45.792 --> 01:53:46.912
A mighty man.

cue-1713
01:53:49.192 --> 01:53:54.182
Elijah is given greater importance in the
New Testament than in the Old, and it

cue-1714
01:53:54.182 --> 01:53:58.032
is always helpful when the New Testament
explains something from the Old.

cue-1715
01:53:59.352 --> 01:54:04.072
In the Old Testament, we are told what
Elijah did, but not clearly where his

cue-1716
01:54:04.072 --> 01:54:05.432
power came from.

cue-1717
01:54:06.132 --> 01:54:11.072
His life was marked by sudden dramatic
appearances, and it ended in a remarkable

cue-1718
01:54:11.072 --> 01:54:11.372
way.

cue-1719
01:54:12.592 --> 01:54:17.012
He lived mostly alone and often felt
alone, saying, "I alone."

cue-1720
01:54:18.312 --> 01:54:22.732
The Old Testament ends with a promise that
he would return, and the New Testament

cue-1721
01:54:22.732 --> 01:54:25.962
begins by showing that this promise was
fulfilled.

cue-1722
01:54:27.152 --> 01:54:31.852
Elijah stood for God, challenged kings,
and influenced the fate of

cue-1723
01:54:31.852 --> 01:54:32.392
nations.

cue-1724
01:54:33.162 --> 01:54:36.612
The New Testament explains his life and
power in a simple way.

cue-1725
01:54:37.432 --> 01:54:38.592
He was a man of prayer.

cue-1726
01:54:39.312 --> 01:54:43.652
In the Old Testament, prayer is clearly
part of his life, but the New Testament

cue-1727
01:54:43.652 --> 01:54:48.032
shows that prayer was the whole reason for
who he was and what he did.

cue-1728
01:54:49.232 --> 01:54:53.172
He was a great man, but he had the same
human struggles as others.

cue-1729
01:54:54.232 --> 01:54:55.832
What made him different was prayer.

cue-1730
01:54:56.772 --> 01:54:58.272
As Epistle of James says,

cue-1731
01:54:58.932 --> 01:55:02.232
"Elijah was a man just like us, and he
prayed."

cue-1732
01:55:03.352 --> 01:55:08.052
Prayer explains Elijah's life just as it
explains the lives of Abraham,

cue-1733
01:55:08.052 --> 01:55:10.532
Jacob, David, and Daniel.

cue-1734
01:55:11.652 --> 01:55:15.752
Yet there was something especially
powerful about Elijah's prayers that set

cue-1735
01:55:15.752 --> 01:55:18.452
him apart even among those who prayed
greatly.

cue-1736
01:55:19.492 --> 01:55:20.092
What was it?

cue-1737
01:55:20.772 --> 01:55:24.132
Why did people come to know God as the
Lord God of Elijah?

cue-1738
01:55:25.992 --> 01:55:27.152
Miracles of power.

cue-1739
01:55:29.252 --> 01:55:32.542
Elijah's prayers show the supernatural
power of prayer.

cue-1740
01:55:33.352 --> 01:55:36.602
His prayers were acts of power, true
miracles.

cue-1741
01:55:37.572 --> 01:55:42.071
This is how the New Testament describes
them. There has been some difficulty in

cue-1742
01:55:42.072 --> 01:55:46.576
translating James five sixteen.The older
version says,

cue-1743
01:55:47.206 --> 01:55:50.856
"The effectual fervent prayer of a
righteous man avails much."

cue-1744
01:55:51.896 --> 01:55:52.956
Another version says,

cue-1745
01:55:53.566 --> 01:55:56.886
"The prayer of a righteous man is powerful
in its working."

cue-1746
01:55:58.176 --> 01:56:00.436
Dr. Rendell Harris translates it as,

cue-1747
01:56:01.216 --> 01:56:04.676
"The energized prayer of a righteous man
is very powerful."

cue-1748
01:56:06.156 --> 01:56:09.756
For Elijah, prayer was not just words, it
was power.

cue-1749
01:56:10.456 --> 01:56:13.816
It was supernatural and worked in
miraculous ways.

cue-1750
01:56:14.996 --> 01:56:19.676
He did not debate about natural laws, and
he never doubted God's power to act

cue-1751
01:56:19.676 --> 01:56:24.496
beyond them. He simply prayed. When he
prayed, the rain

cue-1752
01:56:24.496 --> 01:56:27.996
stopped. When he prayed again, the rain
came in abundance.

cue-1753
01:56:28.736 --> 01:56:32.496
When he prayed for the widow's dead child,
the child came back to life.

cue-1754
01:56:33.116 --> 01:56:35.956
When he prayed for fire from heaven, it
came down.

cue-1755
01:56:37.116 --> 01:56:40.456
Elijah did not argue about prayer, he
practiced it.

cue-1756
01:56:41.356 --> 01:56:43.936
The best way to understand prayer is to
pray.

cue-1757
01:56:44.916 --> 01:56:47.116
There have always been questions about
prayer.

cue-1758
01:56:47.796 --> 01:56:51.776
In the wilderness, people questioned
whether God could act beyond the known

cue-1759
01:56:51.776 --> 01:56:52.796
laws of the world.

cue-1760
01:56:53.836 --> 01:56:54.956
Can God do this?

cue-1761
01:56:55.776 --> 01:56:58.346
Faith answers, "Yes, He can."

cue-1762
01:56:59.396 --> 01:57:03.036
These are not days when we can easily say
anything is impossible.

cue-1763
01:57:03.896 --> 01:57:06.336
We are discovering new things all the
time.

cue-1764
01:57:07.096 --> 01:57:11.716
If people can now do what once seemed
impossible, who can say that anything is

cue-1765
01:57:11.716 --> 01:57:12.876
impossible for God?

cue-1766
01:57:13.996 --> 01:57:17.946
If human thoughts can be sent and heard
across great distances,

cue-1767
01:57:18.736 --> 01:57:21.276
who can limit the thoughts and purposes of
God?

cue-1768
01:57:22.536 --> 01:57:26.456
God, who made heaven and Earth, must be
greater than His creation.

cue-1769
01:57:27.116 --> 01:57:29.576
He cannot be limited by the laws He made.

cue-1770
01:57:30.786 --> 01:57:34.476
The prayer of faith connects a person's
request with God's power.

cue-1771
01:57:35.596 --> 01:57:40.596
Most people believe prayer can influence
the mind, shape character, and purify

cue-1772
01:57:40.596 --> 01:57:41.906
motives and desires,

cue-1773
01:57:42.776 --> 01:57:44.336
but prayer is more than that.

cue-1774
01:57:45.096 --> 01:57:46.276
Prayer is power.

cue-1775
01:57:46.976 --> 01:57:48.436
Prayer changes things.

cue-1776
01:57:49.296 --> 01:57:53.896
The Lord God of Elijah has complete and
unlimited power, and this power

cue-1777
01:57:53.896 --> 01:57:58.756
responds to believing prayer. Everyone who
truly prays has seen

cue-1778
01:57:58.756 --> 01:58:03.676
answers that can only be explained by God.
I hesitate to give

cue-1779
01:58:03.676 --> 01:58:06.516
examples, but in my own life, there are
many.

cue-1780
01:58:07.616 --> 01:58:12.276
Because of this, the words of Psalm 116
are often in my

cue-1781
01:58:12.276 --> 01:58:17.276
heart. "I love the Lord because He has
heard my voice and

cue-1782
01:58:17.276 --> 01:58:18.576
my pleas for mercy.

cue-1783
01:58:19.236 --> 01:58:23.676
Because He turned His ear to me, I will
call on Him as long as I live."

cue-1784
01:58:25.016 --> 01:58:28.756
There is one remarkable example I value
deeply because of how I heard it.

cue-1785
01:58:29.936 --> 01:58:34.656
In the city of Bristol, there are two
buildings that stand as reminders of

cue-1786
01:58:34.656 --> 01:58:35.446
answered prayer.

cue-1787
01:58:36.656 --> 01:58:41.056
One is the orphanage founded by George
Muller. The other I am not free to speak

cue-1788
01:58:41.056 --> 01:58:41.576
about here.

cue-1789
01:58:42.836 --> 01:58:47.576
Arthur Tappan Pearson, who was both my
friend and Muller's biographer, told me

cue-1790
01:58:47.576 --> 01:58:51.396
part of this story. He once stayed with
Muller at the orphanage.

cue-1791
01:58:52.276 --> 01:58:56.316
One night, after everyone had gone to bed,
Muller asked him to pray with him.

cue-1792
01:58:57.325 --> 01:59:01.896
He explained that there was no food at all
for breakfast the next morning. Pearson

cue-1793
01:59:01.896 --> 01:59:05.656
tried to object and reminded him that all
the stores were closed.

cue-1794
01:59:06.956 --> 01:59:08.296
Muller already knew that.

cue-1795
01:59:08.956 --> 01:59:13.575
He had prayed as he always did, and he
never told anyone his needs

cue-1796
01:59:13.576 --> 01:59:14.406
except God.

cue-1797
01:59:15.576 --> 01:59:16.476
So they prayed,

cue-1798
01:59:17.216 --> 01:59:19.976
Muller with strong faith and Pearson doing
his best.

cue-1799
01:59:21.116 --> 01:59:22.956
They went to bed and slept.

cue-1800
01:59:24.156 --> 01:59:28.896
In the morning, there was enough food
prepared to feed 2,000 children just as

cue-1801
01:59:28.896 --> 01:59:32.776
usual. Neither Muller nor Pearson knew how
the answer

cue-1802
01:59:32.776 --> 01:59:37.776
came. The rest of the story was told the
next morning to a man named

cue-1803
01:59:37.776 --> 01:59:38.776
Simon Short,

cue-1804
01:59:39.416 --> 01:59:42.306
who promised to keep it secret until the
giver had died.

cue-1805
01:59:43.376 --> 01:59:48.216
During the night, God had awakened him and
led him to send food to the orphanage.

cue-1806
01:59:49.076 --> 01:59:52.016
He knew nothing of the need or of the two
men praying,

cue-1807
01:59:52.676 --> 01:59:55.496
yet he sent enough supplies to feed them
for a month.

cue-1808
01:59:56.586 --> 02:00:01.456
This is what God is like, the same God who
answered Elijah, and even more,

cue-1809
02:00:01.456 --> 02:00:04.735
the God and Father of our Lord Jesus
Christ.

cue-1810
02:00:06.776 --> 02:00:08.496
The greatest force on Earth.

cue-1811
02:00:11.236 --> 02:00:16.236
Not every kind of prayer brings such
powerful results. It takes a true man or

cue-1812
02:00:16.236 --> 02:00:19.436
woman of prayer to pray like Elijah and
George Muller.

cue-1813
02:00:20.116 --> 02:00:24.796
It is the prayer of a righteous person
filled with God's power that has great

cue-1814
02:00:24.796 --> 02:00:25.216
effect.

cue-1815
02:00:26.396 --> 02:00:31.396
The widow recognized Elijah as a man of
God when he prayed, and her son came back

cue-1816
02:00:31.396 --> 02:00:31.886
to life.

cue-1817
02:00:33.176 --> 02:00:36.316
This is the highest proof and the final
test.

cue-1818
02:00:37.256 --> 02:00:41.076
Nothing would bring people back to God
more quickly than a church that truly

cue-1819
02:00:41.076 --> 02:00:42.916
prays and sees answers.

cue-1820
02:00:44.076 --> 02:00:47.806
The world will not believe in a faith that
has no supernatural power.

cue-1821
02:00:48.746 --> 02:00:52.886
A faith that is only intellectual, a
church focused only on social work,

cue-1822
02:00:53.516 --> 02:00:56.886
or a message reduced to moral teaching may
receive praise,

cue-1823
02:00:57.556 --> 02:01:01.816
but they do not deeply convince people or
lead them to true change.

cue-1824
02:01:03.056 --> 02:01:06.256
There is deep passion in prayer that truly
succeeds.

cue-1825
02:01:07.396 --> 02:01:10.636
Elijah was a man full of strong feeling
and intensity.

cue-1826
02:01:11.336 --> 02:01:13.936
Everything he did, he did with his whole
heart.

cue-1827
02:01:14.876 --> 02:01:18.836
God delights in people who are fully
committed. He cannot accept

cue-1828
02:01:18.836 --> 02:01:23.356
half-heartedness. He does not delay when
people seek Him with all their heart.

cue-1829
02:01:24.576 --> 02:01:29.336
As it is written in Book of Jeremiah
29:13-14, "When people

cue-1830
02:01:29.336 --> 02:01:32.616
search for God with all their heart, they
will find Him."

cue-1831
02:01:33.796 --> 02:01:37.316
When Elijah prayed, he was fully engaged
in his prayer.

cue-1832
02:01:38.156 --> 02:01:41.376
Is it not true that much praying today
lacks real prayer?

cue-1833
02:01:42.356 --> 02:01:47.190
A true man of prayer puts his whole self
into what he asks.We see

cue-1834
02:01:47.190 --> 02:01:51.980
this in Elijah when he prayed over the
dead child on Mount Carmel, and when he

cue-1835
02:01:51.980 --> 02:01:56.760
cried out to God for the people and for
God's honor. This same

cue-1836
02:01:56.760 --> 02:01:58.620
passion is seen throughout Scripture:

cue-1837
02:01:59.360 --> 02:02:03.920
Abraham pleading for Sodom, Jacob
wrestling through the night, Moses

cue-1838
02:02:03.920 --> 02:02:05.820
standing between God and the people,

cue-1839
02:02:06.500 --> 02:02:08.080
Hannah pouring out her sorrow,

cue-1840
02:02:08.760 --> 02:02:13.020
David broken with repentance, and even
Jesus praying with such

cue-1841
02:02:13.020 --> 02:02:15.680
intensity that it was like sweating blood.

cue-1842
02:02:16.940 --> 02:02:21.880
If we add examples from church history and
personal experience, the pattern is

cue-1843
02:02:21.880 --> 02:02:22.680
always the same.

cue-1844
02:02:23.320 --> 02:02:28.200
True prayer involves deep cost and strong
passion, and it brings

cue-1845
02:02:28.200 --> 02:02:32.980
results. It changes ordinary people into
people of power. It

cue-1846
02:02:32.980 --> 02:02:37.940
brings power, fire, rain, life. It brings
God near.

cue-1847
02:02:39.149 --> 02:02:42.620
There is no power like the power of prayer
that truly prevails.

cue-1848
02:02:44.380 --> 02:02:47.370
Recent letters have shared many stories of
answered prayer.

cue-1849
02:02:48.280 --> 02:02:52.680
I understand why some people question
them. Those who have not gone through

cue-1850
02:02:52.680 --> 02:02:56.320
deep, earnest prayer can often look for
other explanations.

cue-1851
02:02:57.340 --> 02:03:02.260
But for the one who has truly prayed, any
explanation only increases the

cue-1852
02:03:02.260 --> 02:03:03.420
wonder of the answer.

cue-1853
02:03:04.620 --> 02:03:09.480
In a real sense, he receives the answer in
his heart before it appears outwardly.

cue-1854
02:03:10.520 --> 02:03:11.720
Consider one example.

cue-1855
02:03:12.380 --> 02:03:15.140
A man told me about a serious problem in
his business.

cue-1856
02:03:15.850 --> 02:03:20.720
Like Jehoshaphat, he had no resources to
meet the need and did not know what to

cue-1857
02:03:20.720 --> 02:03:20.980
do.

cue-1858
02:03:22.060 --> 02:03:25.400
Still, he continued praying earnestly to
God.

cue-1859
02:03:26.500 --> 02:03:31.320
Then one day, a deep peace filled his
heart, and he knew that God had heard

cue-1860
02:03:31.320 --> 02:03:36.320
him. Nothing around him had changed, yet
he was certain of the answer.

cue-1861
02:03:37.540 --> 02:03:42.310
Later, in a completely unexpected way, and
through someone not well known to him,

cue-1862
02:03:42.310 --> 02:03:47.060
help came. The situation could be
explained in ordinary

cue-1863
02:03:47.060 --> 02:03:50.660
terms, but the answer to prayer was just
as real and

cue-1864
02:03:50.660 --> 02:03:55.480
certain. It seems to me that arguing about
prayer is useless.

cue-1865
02:03:56.620 --> 02:03:59.680
A challenge like that of Thomas Henry
Huxley leads nowhere.

cue-1866
02:04:00.529 --> 02:04:03.560
The proof that God answers prayer is found
in praying.

cue-1867
02:04:04.500 --> 02:04:09.080
Once, I responded to a man who challenged
me to prove that God answers prayer.

cue-1868
02:04:10.180 --> 02:04:11.860
I asked him to kneel and pray,

cue-1869
02:04:12.560 --> 02:04:17.360
but he refused. I still believe this is
the only true way to know,

cue-1870
02:04:17.960 --> 02:04:20.559
and it is both practical and certain.

cue-1871
02:04:21.600 --> 02:04:25.340
Another story, which I can share, comes
from T. A. Turney.

cue-1872
02:04:26.460 --> 02:04:30.040
As a boy, he attended a school where the
teacher was also his uncle.

cue-1873
02:04:30.780 --> 02:04:34.920
The teacher was strict and made students
discover answers for themselves.

cue-1874
02:04:35.969 --> 02:04:39.700
To avoid showing favoritism, he was even
harder on his nephew.

cue-1875
02:04:40.650 --> 02:04:45.600
The boy came to a point where he could not
solve a math problem. Day after day,

cue-1876
02:04:45.600 --> 02:04:48.980
he brought it to his teacher, only to be
told to try again.

cue-1877
02:04:50.140 --> 02:04:55.060
This continued for more than a week. One
night, the boy went to a church service

cue-1878
02:04:55.060 --> 02:04:56.760
and gave his life to God.

cue-1879
02:04:57.860 --> 02:05:01.760
As he knelt in prayer, he later asked God
to help him with the problem.

cue-1880
02:05:02.660 --> 02:05:07.460
That night, whether asleep or awake, he
saw the solution clearly worked

cue-1881
02:05:07.460 --> 02:05:07.700
out.

cue-1882
02:05:08.840 --> 02:05:10.660
He got up and wrote it down.

cue-1883
02:05:11.540 --> 02:05:13.760
The next morning, he showed it to his
teacher.

cue-1884
02:05:14.490 --> 02:05:18.000
The teacher looked at it and said,
"Correct. Who showed you?"

cue-1885
02:05:18.800 --> 02:05:20.560
"God," the boy replied.

cue-1886
02:05:22.660 --> 02:05:24.720
An energized intercessor.

cue-1887
02:05:27.500 --> 02:05:28.940
Have you heard of John Hyde?

cue-1888
02:05:29.720 --> 02:05:33.160
He came to be known as Praying Hyde by
those who knew him well.

cue-1889
02:05:34.190 --> 02:05:37.620
This began after he experienced a deep
spiritual renewal,

cue-1890
02:05:38.280 --> 02:05:40.900
often described as the baptism of the Holy
Spirit.

cue-1891
02:05:42.020 --> 02:05:46.200
From that time, his remarkable life of
prayer truly began.

cue-1892
02:05:47.160 --> 02:05:51.860
The recorded answers to his prayers are
only a small part of his story. He prayed

cue-1893
02:05:51.860 --> 02:05:54.520
the Indian Keswick movement into being.

cue-1894
02:05:54.720 --> 02:05:59.660
He prayed for thousands to come to faith
in God and for hundreds of workers to go

cue-1895
02:05:59.660 --> 02:06:01.300
out into God's harvest fields.

cue-1896
02:06:02.320 --> 02:06:06.940
More than all this, he grew into a deep
sharing in the intercession of our Lord.

cue-1897
02:06:08.109 --> 02:06:13.090
The secret of his prayer life was simple:
his whole life was devoted to prayer.

cue-1898
02:06:14.320 --> 02:06:19.200
In 1911, John Hyde was in England. He
attended a mission where J. Wilbur

cue-1899
02:06:19.200 --> 02:06:21.820
Chapman and Charles Alexander were
struggling.

cue-1900
02:06:22.640 --> 02:06:27.190
Hyde took the burden of the meetings upon
himself and prayed until there was a clear

cue-1901
02:06:27.190 --> 02:06:31.820
breakthrough. After a powerful meeting,
Dr. Chapman asked

cue-1902
02:06:31.820 --> 02:06:32.940
Hyde to pray for him.

cue-1903
02:06:34.140 --> 02:06:35.440
This is how he described it.

cue-1904
02:06:36.040 --> 02:06:39.560
He came into my room, locked the door, and
knelt down.

cue-1905
02:06:40.740 --> 02:06:42.260
For five minutes, he said nothing.

cue-1906
02:06:42.900 --> 02:06:44.630
I could hear both our hearts beating.

cue-1907
02:06:45.290 --> 02:06:49.120
Tears ran down my face, and I knew I was
in God's presence.

cue-1908
02:06:49.800 --> 02:06:50.850
Then he softly said,

cue-1909
02:06:51.730 --> 02:06:52.500
"Oh, God,"

cue-1910
02:06:53.600 --> 02:06:58.540
and again was silent for several minutes.
When he began to pray, he put his

cue-1911
02:06:58.540 --> 02:07:03.460
arm around me, and from deep within came
prayers for people that I had never heard

cue-1912
02:07:03.460 --> 02:07:03.880
before.

cue-1913
02:07:05.240 --> 02:07:06.580
When I rose from my knees,

cue-1914
02:07:07.200 --> 02:07:09.280
I understood what real prayer was.

cue-1915
02:07:10.520 --> 02:07:14.500
We had believed prayer was powerful, but
now we knew it in a new way.

cue-1916
02:07:16.540 --> 02:07:19.360
I know that stories like this can
discourage some people,

cue-1917
02:07:20.040 --> 02:07:24.919
even though they are meant to inspire. I
am not saying that we must become

cue-1918
02:07:24.920 --> 02:07:27.000
like these exceptional individuals,

cue-1919
02:07:28.040 --> 02:07:29.800
but I do rejoice in this truth.

cue-1920
02:07:30.580 --> 02:07:33.540
Whatever God gave to them is also
available to all.

cue-1921
02:07:36.560 --> 02:07:37.480
Chapter Twelve:

cue-1922
02:07:38.660 --> 02:07:40.420
Praying and the Commonplace.

cue-1923
02:07:43.500 --> 02:07:48.400
Moses and Elijah were not ordinary men.
They were so unique that, out of

cue-1924
02:07:48.400 --> 02:07:52.950
all the Old Testament saints, they were
chosen to speak with Jesus on the Mount of

cue-1925
02:07:52.950 --> 02:07:57.916
Transfiguration.One led under the old
covenant, and the other

cue-1926
02:07:57.916 --> 02:07:59.675
was its most powerful prophet.

cue-1927
02:08:00.796 --> 02:08:02.176
Their roles were special.

cue-1928
02:08:02.896 --> 02:08:07.136
God called them to tasks that required
close and constant fellowship with Him.

cue-1929
02:08:08.636 --> 02:08:11.336
Miracles were clearly seen in everything
they did.

cue-1930
02:08:11.946 --> 02:08:16.336
The staff of Moses and the cloak of Elijah
showed God's power at work.

cue-1931
02:08:17.276 --> 02:08:22.176
Their prayers brought about miracles. They
lived in the presence of God's unlimited

cue-1932
02:08:22.176 --> 02:08:22.556
power.

cue-1933
02:08:23.716 --> 02:08:26.736
Through their words, the heavens and the
earth were affected.

cue-1934
02:08:27.336 --> 02:08:32.216
Rivers and rain obeyed them. Life and
death were under their command. Oil

cue-1935
02:08:32.216 --> 02:08:33.736
and flour were multiplied.

cue-1936
02:08:34.576 --> 02:08:39.016
Even greater than these visible miracles
were the results of their prayers in

cue-1937
02:08:39.016 --> 02:08:41.256
receiving understanding and direction.

cue-1938
02:08:42.476 --> 02:08:47.256
God revealed His thoughts to them and
showed them His will. In answer to their

cue-1939
02:08:47.256 --> 02:08:52.136
prayers, they received wisdom beyond human
understanding. These

cue-1940
02:08:52.136 --> 02:08:55.946
works of the mind were greater than
miracles over physical things.

cue-1941
02:08:57.896 --> 02:09:00.276
Prayer and ordinary people.

cue-1942
02:09:01.996 --> 02:09:06.876
The powerful stories of answered prayer in
the Bible have deeply shaped how ordinary

cue-1943
02:09:06.876 --> 02:09:07.636
people think.

cue-1944
02:09:08.666 --> 02:09:11.656
They have set miracles as the normal way
prayer works.

cue-1945
02:09:12.536 --> 02:09:16.116
This is true in one sense because all
prayer is supernatural.

cue-1946
02:09:16.936 --> 02:09:21.656
Yet this idea can also discourage people.
Moses was unique,

cue-1947
02:09:21.656 --> 02:09:25.116
and although Elijah had human struggles
like we do,

cue-1948
02:09:25.736 --> 02:09:29.436
he was not an ordinary man, and his
mission was far from

cue-1949
02:09:29.436 --> 02:09:34.256
common. So what place does prayer have in
the lives of ordinary people?

cue-1950
02:09:35.116 --> 02:09:39.835
What about those who have no quiet time or
free moments, and whose days are filled

cue-1951
02:09:39.836 --> 02:09:42.156
with repetitive, everyday tasks?

cue-1952
02:09:43.216 --> 02:09:46.636
Is prayer only for special people in
unusual situations,

cue-1953
02:09:47.436 --> 02:09:52.136
or does it also belong in the lives of
those with simple abilities and ordinary

cue-1954
02:09:52.136 --> 02:09:52.846
routines?

cue-1955
02:09:54.076 --> 02:09:57.896
About the New Testament prophet who
followed Elijah, it is said that he

cue-1956
02:09:57.896 --> 02:10:02.096
performed no miracles. He was just as
devoted to

cue-1957
02:10:02.096 --> 02:10:06.676
prayer, but he did not multiply food,
raise the dead, or

cue-1958
02:10:06.676 --> 02:10:07.636
control nature.

cue-1959
02:10:08.836 --> 02:10:13.516
The only miracles seen in him were in his
character, his insight, and his

cue-1960
02:10:13.516 --> 02:10:13.976
message.

cue-1961
02:10:15.176 --> 02:10:19.496
This shows that God's power can work
through normal, everyday life.

cue-1962
02:10:20.716 --> 02:10:25.156
Ordinary people can pray about ordinary
things, and the answers may come as a

cue-1963
02:10:25.156 --> 02:10:29.896
clearer mind, a joyful and strong spirit,
steady faith, and a

cue-1964
02:10:29.896 --> 02:10:34.496
holy life. There may be no dramatic
events, but prayer

cue-1965
02:10:34.496 --> 02:10:37.976
lifts even the simplest life into the
realm of God's power,

cue-1966
02:10:38.936 --> 02:10:41.096
and that is the greatest miracle of all.

cue-1967
02:10:43.036 --> 02:10:44.416
Prayer and daily work.

cue-1968
02:10:47.196 --> 02:10:52.156
It is clear that we can't all be like
Elijah or Elisha, Abraham or Daniel,

cue-1969
02:10:52.156 --> 02:10:56.836
or even people like George Muller, Hudson
Taylor, Barnardo, or Praying Hyde.

cue-1970
02:10:57.756 --> 02:11:00.026
But that does not mean we can't be people
of prayer.

cue-1971
02:11:00.876 --> 02:11:05.425
In scripture, there are those who prayed,
yet no miracles are recorded about them.

cue-1972
02:11:06.205 --> 02:11:08.676
They lived and worked in ordinary
settings.

cue-1973
02:11:09.536 --> 02:11:14.116
Jacob and Moses were shepherds with long
periods of quiet where they could pray.

cue-1974
02:11:15.116 --> 02:11:18.536
Elijah, it seems, did little else but
pray.

cue-1975
02:11:20.126 --> 02:11:24.276
His life of miracles should be balanced
with the lives of others who worked under

cue-1976
02:11:24.276 --> 02:11:25.336
normal conditions.

cue-1977
02:11:26.396 --> 02:11:29.646
We expect preachers and prophets to devote
themselves to prayer,

cue-1978
02:11:30.276 --> 02:11:34.246
but what about those who work in
factories, offices, and stores?

cue-1979
02:11:35.416 --> 02:11:38.636
Nehemiah was just as much a man of prayer
as Elijah.

cue-1980
02:11:39.396 --> 02:11:42.676
He was a builder working to restore the
wall of Jerusalem.

cue-1981
02:11:43.516 --> 02:11:48.516
He performed no miracles, saw no visions,
and had no special message directly

cue-1982
02:11:48.516 --> 02:11:49.036
from heaven.

cue-1983
02:11:50.236 --> 02:11:53.916
He never claimed that God sent him, nor
did he ask others to say so.

cue-1984
02:11:54.756 --> 02:11:57.806
Instead, he saw a need and had an
opportunity,

cue-1985
02:11:58.536 --> 02:11:59.396
and that was enough.

cue-1986
02:12:00.636 --> 02:12:03.216
The broken state of the city filled him
with sorrow.

cue-1987
02:12:03.976 --> 02:12:08.876
There was important work to be done, and
no one seemed ready to do it. He

cue-1988
02:12:08.876 --> 02:12:11.246
felt deeply that he should take
responsibility,

cue-1989
02:12:12.335 --> 02:12:13.246
so he prayed.

cue-1990
02:12:13.996 --> 02:12:18.876
He prayed when he heard the bad news. He
prayed for the ruined city, for the

cue-1991
02:12:18.876 --> 02:12:23.866
suffering people, and for their shame. He
prayed until his heart was

cue-1992
02:12:23.866 --> 02:12:24.806
almost breaking.

cue-1993
02:12:25.676 --> 02:12:28.986
Nothing dramatic seemed to happen. No
angel appeared.

cue-1994
02:12:29.916 --> 02:12:31.636
God gave no visible sign.

cue-1995
02:12:32.716 --> 02:12:37.656
When Elijah prayed, outward things
changed. When Nehemiah prayed,

cue-1996
02:12:37.656 --> 02:12:39.216
it seemed like nothing happened.

cue-1997
02:12:40.176 --> 02:12:44.056
But something did happen. Something
changed within Nehemiah,

cue-1998
02:12:44.776 --> 02:12:48.816
and a changed person is a greater miracle
than changes in nature.

cue-1999
02:12:50.056 --> 02:12:51.556
His sorrow led him to prayer.

cue-2000
02:12:52.256 --> 02:12:56.256
Prayer formed a deep conviction.
Conviction gave him purpose.

cue-2001
02:12:56.876 --> 02:13:01.556
Purpose drove his energy. Energy led to
action. And so these two

cue-2002
02:13:01.556 --> 02:13:02.616
truths come together.

cue-2003
02:13:03.426 --> 02:13:05.776
"So I prayed, and so we built."

cue-2004
02:13:07.576 --> 02:13:12.096
Nehemiah's prayers did not produce sudden
or dramatic displays of supernatural

cue-2005
02:13:12.096 --> 02:13:12.396
power,

cue-2006
02:13:13.136 --> 02:13:16.996
yet they led to the rebuilding of the wall
and the restoration of the city.

cue-2007
02:13:18.116 --> 02:13:20.036
This was the work God had given him.

cue-2008
02:13:20.836 --> 02:13:22.616
Nehemiah prayed about his work.

cue-2009
02:13:23.526 --> 02:13:28.356
Prayer was not occasional for him. It was
his constant attitude and daily habit.

cue-2010
02:13:29.616 --> 02:13:33.116
Some people only pray in special or
desperate situations.

cue-2011
02:13:33.956 --> 02:13:37.096
We hear of those who pray when they are
completely overwhelmed.

cue-2012
02:13:37.936 --> 02:13:40.576
Many people only turn to prayer at such
times.

cue-2013
02:13:41.296 --> 02:13:44.016
Others pray only when they feel strong
emotions.

cue-2014
02:13:45.176 --> 02:13:47.096
But Nehemiah prayed continually

cue-2015
02:13:47.836 --> 02:13:50.146
through every step and about everything.

cue-2016
02:13:51.376 --> 02:13:54.816
Prayer was so natural to him that it
shaped his whole life

cue-2017
02:13:55.576 --> 02:13:58.856
until he truly became a man of prayer.

cue-2018
02:14:01.016 --> 02:14:05.886
The practical value of prayer.The habit of
prayer

cue-2019
02:14:05.886 --> 02:14:07.866
shapes how a person sees life.

cue-2020
02:14:08.946 --> 02:14:13.585
It begins with the belief that God is real
and rules over everything. It

cue-2021
02:14:13.586 --> 02:14:18.506
brings all things under His will, brings
every matter before Him, judges

cue-2022
02:14:18.506 --> 02:14:21.906
everything by His standards, and lives in
trust toward Him.

cue-2023
02:14:23.076 --> 02:14:26.266
Prayer is both the heart and the test of a
godly life.

cue-2024
02:14:27.416 --> 02:14:30.956
Who can fully measure how prayer affects
the mind and shapes character?

cue-2025
02:14:31.666 --> 02:14:35.406
Who can estimate its value in giving
wisdom and skill for daily life?

cue-2026
02:14:36.596 --> 02:14:41.306
The Book of Nehemiah shows this clearly.
It records what prayer did in the life of

cue-2027
02:14:41.306 --> 02:14:46.246
a man who performed no miracles, yet
rebuilt the wall in the face

cue-2028
02:14:46.246 --> 02:14:50.926
of great opposition. Through prayer,
Nehemiah gained the king's

cue-2029
02:14:50.926 --> 02:14:52.146
approval and support,

cue-2030
02:14:52.866 --> 02:14:54.746
as well as all the supplies he needed.

cue-2031
02:14:55.946 --> 02:15:00.046
Prayer gave him courage and good judgment
when facing critics and enemies.

cue-2032
02:15:01.106 --> 02:15:05.586
It helped him deal wisely with problems
among the workers, including matters of

cue-2033
02:15:05.586 --> 02:15:06.826
labor and wages.

cue-2034
02:15:08.006 --> 02:15:12.766
It protected him from deceitful officials
and gave him insight to resist the

cue-2035
02:15:12.766 --> 02:15:13.986
schemes of his enemies.

cue-2036
02:15:15.406 --> 02:15:19.266
When false accusations were made against
him, prayer became his

cue-2037
02:15:19.266 --> 02:15:23.825
refuge. It equipped him not only with
faith, but also with a steady

cue-2038
02:15:23.826 --> 02:15:24.286
spirit,

cue-2039
02:15:24.926 --> 02:15:29.926
even a sense of calm confidence as he
worked with both sword and tool

cue-2040
02:15:29.926 --> 02:15:30.506
in hand.

cue-2041
02:15:31.666 --> 02:15:36.326
He kept his life clean, his mind sharp,
and his courage strong,

cue-2042
02:15:36.326 --> 02:15:38.606
praying through every challenge.

cue-2043
02:15:40.006 --> 02:15:44.966
He was confident in God, confident in
God's character, God's Word, and

cue-2044
02:15:44.966 --> 02:15:45.756
God's covenant,

cue-2045
02:15:46.946 --> 02:15:51.686
so he prayed, and he trusted. He worked,
and he overcame.

cue-2046
02:15:53.906 --> 02:15:54.926
Whatever you ask.

cue-2047
02:15:57.806 --> 02:16:02.786
There is nothing we can't pray about, but
prayer is not effective if it is only a

cue-2048
02:16:02.786 --> 02:16:05.176
passing desire or careless wish.

cue-2049
02:16:06.386 --> 02:16:10.826
Nehemiah prayed about his work, but he
also made it his business to understand it

cue-2050
02:16:10.826 --> 02:16:15.186
well. His work succeeded because he gave
himself fully to it.

cue-2051
02:16:16.046 --> 02:16:20.866
It does no good to pray about work and
then neglect it or act foolishly in it

cue-2052
02:16:20.866 --> 02:16:23.526
through lack of courage, skill, or wisdom.

cue-2053
02:16:24.726 --> 02:16:27.956
Nehemiah prayed, but he also used good
judgment.

cue-2054
02:16:28.835 --> 02:16:33.626
He trusted God to provide, yet he made
sure to obtain the king's letters.

cue-2055
02:16:33.626 --> 02:16:38.506
He trusted God to protect, yet he
equipped the builders with

cue-2056
02:16:38.506 --> 02:16:41.646
both tools and weapons.

cue-2057
02:16:42.506 --> 02:16:47.406
Prayer gives clear vision in private,
understanding in action, wisdom in

cue-2058
02:16:47.406 --> 02:16:52.386
decisions, courage in testing, strength to
endure hardship, and

cue-2059
02:16:52.386 --> 02:16:54.696
a deep joy in following God's will.

cue-2060
02:16:55.956 --> 02:16:59.846
There was once a weaver who prayed over
his work as Nehemiah did.

cue-2061
02:17:00.946 --> 02:17:05.346
People came to say that every piece of
cloth he made was for the Lord Jesus

cue-2062
02:17:05.346 --> 02:17:05.806
Christ.

cue-2063
02:17:06.846 --> 02:17:11.835
He never became rich, but his work
succeeded, and his character was of

cue-2064
02:17:11.835 --> 02:17:16.686
great value. Every task and duty can be
made holy through God's

cue-2065
02:17:16.686 --> 02:17:17.806
Word and prayer.

cue-2066
02:17:19.006 --> 02:17:23.706
A life of prayer that shows no outward
miracles may, in fact, be the

cue-2067
02:17:23.706 --> 02:17:25.206
greatest miracle of all.

cue-2068
02:17:26.726 --> 02:17:30.366
The secret of life is found in the quiet
place where God waits.

cue-2069
02:17:31.406 --> 02:17:34.726
Even for those who cannot find outward
privacy,

cue-2070
02:17:34.786 --> 02:17:37.706
there is an inner place of the soul where
they can withdraw.

cue-2071
02:17:38.776 --> 02:17:43.726
The habit of private prayer is of great
and lasting value. There is nothing that

cue-2072
02:17:43.726 --> 02:17:45.716
should not be brought to God in prayer.

cue-2073
02:17:46.496 --> 02:17:51.346
Life can be lived before Him. Problems can
be worked through in His presence.

cue-2074
02:17:52.266 --> 02:17:57.246
Questions about both freedom and duty can
be settled there. God's guidance

cue-2075
02:17:57.246 --> 02:18:00.796
can be sought, and everything can be
placed under His judgment.

cue-2076
02:18:01.996 --> 02:18:05.326
This inner place becomes a sanctuary for
the soul.

cue-2077
02:18:07.406 --> 02:18:09.866
One morning, there was a beautiful sight,

cue-2078
02:18:10.586 --> 02:18:15.426
a rainbow rising over the hill. It stood
bright and full,

cue-2079
02:18:15.426 --> 02:18:20.106
then stretched until one end touched the
village and the other reached the

cue-2080
02:18:20.106 --> 02:18:20.446
river.

cue-2081
02:18:21.946 --> 02:18:25.926
Its colors were beyond description,
filling the whole scene with beauty.

cue-2082
02:18:27.006 --> 02:18:31.546
The old ruins looked like a palace, and
every small house seemed to shine.

cue-2083
02:18:33.026 --> 02:18:37.986
Fields and trees reflected the light, and
even the simplest objects appeared

cue-2084
02:18:37.986 --> 02:18:39.636
full of beauty and glory.

cue-2085
02:18:40.846 --> 02:18:45.066
In the same way, prayer makes ordinary
life holy and beautiful.

cue-2086
02:18:45.886 --> 02:18:50.886
It brings God's presence into everyday
things and fills even the simplest life

cue-2087
02:18:50.886 --> 02:18:52.246
with meaning and glory.

cue-2088
02:18:55.326 --> 02:18:56.306
Chapter thirteen:

cue-2089
02:18:56.906 --> 02:18:58.106
The prayer of faith.

cue-2090
02:19:00.946 --> 02:19:05.766
He who comes to God must believe that He
exists and that He rewards those who

cue-2091
02:19:05.766 --> 02:19:06.786
earnestly seek Him.

cue-2092
02:19:08.366 --> 02:19:10.006
Faith is necessary for prayer.

cue-2093
02:19:10.686 --> 02:19:14.546
Without it, it is hard to see how anyone
could truly pray.

cue-2094
02:19:15.216 --> 02:19:17.586
No one can pray without some measure of
faith.

cue-2095
02:19:18.566 --> 02:19:23.106
That is why the faith God requires is the
first condition in a person who

cue-2096
02:19:23.106 --> 02:19:23.606
prays.

cue-2097
02:19:24.706 --> 02:19:26.286
Atheists do not pray.

cue-2098
02:19:26.966 --> 02:19:29.046
God places great value on faith.

cue-2099
02:19:29.946 --> 02:19:34.896
He makes it the first requirement for
prayer, the only condition for salvation,

cue-2100
02:19:34.896 --> 02:19:39.246
the essential part of spiritual life, and
the foundation of all true power.

cue-2101
02:19:40.426 --> 02:19:44.846
It is a shallow understanding of faith
that mocks salvation by grace through

cue-2102
02:19:44.846 --> 02:19:45.766
faith alone.

cue-2103
02:19:47.086 --> 02:19:48.146
Faith is enough.

cue-2104
02:19:49.006 --> 02:19:53.826
It is all God asks and all Jesus asks.
"You believe in God,

cue-2105
02:19:53.826 --> 02:19:55.226
believe also in me."

cue-2106
02:19:56.506 --> 02:19:59.246
When the synagogue leader was told his
daughter had died,

cue-2107
02:19:59.846 --> 02:20:04.325
Jesus encouraged him saying, "Do not be
afraid. Only

cue-2108
02:20:04.326 --> 02:20:09.082
believe."And when the troubled father of a
possessed boy cried out in

cue-2109
02:20:09.082 --> 02:20:09.642
despair,

cue-2110
02:20:10.362 --> 02:20:14.582
Jesus assured him that all things are
possible for the one who believes.

cue-2111
02:20:15.842 --> 02:20:19.002
Without faith, it is impossible to please
God.

cue-2112
02:20:19.682 --> 02:20:24.522
Without faith, it is impossible to pray.
Without faith, there can be

cue-2113
02:20:24.522 --> 02:20:25.972
no fellowship with God.

cue-2114
02:20:26.682 --> 02:20:31.562
Without faith, a person can do nothing
with God, and God does nothing

cue-2115
02:20:31.562 --> 02:20:32.402
with that person.

cue-2116
02:20:33.182 --> 02:20:36.062
Even in human life, nothing works without
faith.

cue-2117
02:20:37.002 --> 02:20:41.922
Faith is the foundation, not only of
salvation, but also of everyday

cue-2118
02:20:41.922 --> 02:20:43.791
life and human society.

cue-2119
02:20:46.162 --> 02:20:47.102
The law of faith.

cue-2120
02:20:49.522 --> 02:20:54.262
The Apostle Paul explains the law of faith
in relation to grace, and James

cue-2121
02:20:54.262 --> 02:20:56.842
explains the same law in relation to
prayer.

cue-2122
02:20:57.902 --> 02:20:59.492
There is no conflict between them.

cue-2123
02:21:00.202 --> 02:21:00.682
For both,

cue-2124
02:21:01.302 --> 02:21:04.602
faith is more than simply agreeing with
something in the mind,

cue-2125
02:21:05.472 --> 02:21:08.102
no matter how sincere that agreement may
be.

cue-2126
02:21:09.282 --> 02:21:13.882
Faith is a moral and spiritual response
that commits the whole person to

cue-2127
02:21:13.882 --> 02:21:18.322
truth that is accepted and trusted. It is
more than belief.

cue-2128
02:21:19.242 --> 02:21:23.102
Even evil spirits believe and tremble, but
they do not

cue-2129
02:21:23.102 --> 02:21:25.782
trust. Faith is trust.

cue-2130
02:21:26.442 --> 02:21:29.582
It is not just an opinion, an idea, or a
guess.

cue-2131
02:21:30.202 --> 02:21:34.862
It is a way of seeing, a means of
confirming truth, a confident knowledge,

cue-2132
02:21:34.862 --> 02:21:37.042
and a guiding principle for life.

cue-2133
02:21:38.102 --> 02:21:42.702
True faith requires an honest mind, pure
motives, and faithful

cue-2134
02:21:42.702 --> 02:21:43.302
obedience.

cue-2135
02:21:44.422 --> 02:21:48.982
This kind of faith works according to
God's order. It brings justification to

cue-2136
02:21:48.982 --> 02:21:52.762
the sinner, holiness to the unholy, and
power in prayer.

cue-2137
02:21:54.102 --> 02:21:59.042
Jesus said that even faith as small as a
mustard seed can move mountains,

cue-2138
02:21:59.042 --> 02:22:00.532
that nothing will be impossible.

cue-2139
02:22:01.762 --> 02:22:06.212
Yet he also taught that such power is
connected with prayer and fasting.

cue-2140
02:22:07.042 --> 02:22:09.982
This teaching should be understood
alongside his words:

cue-2141
02:22:11.022 --> 02:22:12.142
"Have faith in God.

cue-2142
02:22:13.262 --> 02:22:17.882
Whoever speaks to a mountain and does not
doubt but believes it will happen will

cue-2143
02:22:17.882 --> 02:22:19.122
receive what he asks."

cue-2144
02:22:20.282 --> 02:22:25.082
Therefore, when we pray, we are to believe
that we have received what we ask for,

cue-2145
02:22:25.942 --> 02:22:27.042
and it will be given.

cue-2146
02:22:28.782 --> 02:22:30.562
The law of faith in prayer.

cue-2147
02:22:33.602 --> 02:22:33.822
One,

cue-2148
02:22:34.722 --> 02:22:36.961
ask, James one-five.

cue-2149
02:22:38.482 --> 02:22:42.722
James follows and explains the teaching of
Jesus, especially from the Sermon on the

cue-2150
02:22:42.722 --> 02:22:47.602
Mount. He begins simply, "Ask. If anyone
lacks, let him ask

cue-2151
02:22:47.602 --> 02:22:47.842
God."

cue-2152
02:22:48.742 --> 02:22:52.142
This invitation includes every kind of
need, not only wisdom.

cue-2153
02:22:52.982 --> 02:22:57.042
God gives freely to all who ask without
blaming or holding back.

cue-2154
02:22:58.062 --> 02:22:59.222
So the promise stands,

cue-2155
02:22:59.962 --> 02:23:01.722
ask and you will receive.

cue-2156
02:23:02.562 --> 02:23:04.422
Prayer has no narrow limits.

cue-2157
02:23:05.442 --> 02:23:09.622
Whatever is promised to whoever, giving
full freedom to those who pray.

cue-2158
02:23:10.502 --> 02:23:14.961
We are told not to be anxious about
anything, but to bring everything to God

cue-2159
02:23:14.962 --> 02:23:19.642
in prayer with thanksgiving. God already
knows our

cue-2160
02:23:19.642 --> 02:23:24.552
needs, but asking is not about informing
Him. It is about coming to Him in

cue-2161
02:23:24.552 --> 02:23:25.042
trust.

cue-2162
02:23:25.962 --> 02:23:29.702
God waits to be asked so that He may give
what we truly need.

cue-2163
02:23:31.662 --> 02:23:31.922
Two,

cue-2164
02:23:32.602 --> 02:23:35.582
ask in faith, James one-six.

cue-2165
02:23:36.842 --> 02:23:40.082
Faith is best understood by looking at its
opposite, doubt.

cue-2166
02:23:40.742 --> 02:23:43.362
Doubt makes a person divided and unstable.

cue-2167
02:23:44.122 --> 02:23:48.342
Like the sea, it is restless and easily
driven by winds and waves.

cue-2168
02:23:49.062 --> 02:23:52.922
Inner struggles disturb it, and outward
circumstances push it in different

cue-2169
02:23:52.922 --> 02:23:53.582
directions.

cue-2170
02:23:54.762 --> 02:23:58.362
Such a person receives nothing because
they are not fully committed.

cue-2171
02:23:59.482 --> 02:24:04.302
A divided mind leads to an unsteady life.
As it has been

cue-2172
02:24:04.302 --> 02:24:09.021
said, "Ships go east and ships go west,
whatever the winds that

cue-2173
02:24:09.022 --> 02:24:09.382
blow.

cue-2174
02:24:09.982 --> 02:24:14.002
The set of the sail and not the gale
settles the way we go."

cue-2175
02:24:16.602 --> 02:24:18.042
Faith sets the sails.

cue-2176
02:24:20.562 --> 02:24:20.822
Three,

cue-2177
02:24:21.702 --> 02:24:22.902
ask in the right way,

cue-2178
02:24:23.502 --> 02:24:24.602
James four-three.

cue-2179
02:24:25.452 --> 02:24:27.061
It is possible to ask wrongly.

cue-2180
02:24:27.681 --> 02:24:32.202
You ask and do not receive because you ask
with wrong motives to spend it on your

cue-2181
02:24:32.202 --> 02:24:33.022
own desires.

cue-2182
02:24:34.002 --> 02:24:37.742
God looks not only at what we ask for, but
also at why we ask.

cue-2183
02:24:38.502 --> 02:24:39.622
He examines the heart.

cue-2184
02:24:40.342 --> 02:24:42.262
There are conditions that hinder prayer.

cue-2185
02:24:42.942 --> 02:24:44.182
Sin blocks the way.

cue-2186
02:24:45.002 --> 02:24:48.042
If I hold on to sin in my heart, the Lord
will not hear me.

cue-2187
02:24:48.922 --> 02:24:50.742
Unbelief also blocks the way.

cue-2188
02:24:51.442 --> 02:24:53.852
A lack of faith keeps a person from
receiving.

cue-2189
02:24:54.722 --> 02:24:57.082
An unforgiving spirit is another barrier.

cue-2190
02:24:58.182 --> 02:25:02.602
If we refuse to forgive others, we close
the door on our own prayers.

cue-2191
02:25:03.802 --> 02:25:07.762
A divided and unstable mind also prevents
answers.

cue-2192
02:25:08.662 --> 02:25:13.002
A guilty conscience can hold us back, and
selfish motives can keep us from

cue-2193
02:25:13.002 --> 02:25:13.502
receiving.

cue-2194
02:25:14.682 --> 02:25:18.762
Faith works within those who pray so that
they may ask in the right way,

cue-2195
02:25:19.482 --> 02:25:23.082
with clean hearts, steady trust, and right
desires.

cue-2196
02:25:24.682 --> 02:25:24.982
Four,

cue-2197
02:25:25.782 --> 02:25:27.002
ask righteously,

cue-2198
02:25:27.822 --> 02:25:30.302
James five-thirteen to eighteen.

cue-2199
02:25:31.422 --> 02:25:34.382
Right praying depends on the character of
the one who prays.

cue-2200
02:25:35.302 --> 02:25:37.542
The person is, in a sense, the prayer.

cue-2201
02:25:38.202 --> 02:25:41.282
He is both the one who asks and the reason
for the asking.

cue-2202
02:25:42.482 --> 02:25:46.982
In scripture, many appealed to their
uprightness before God, and their prayers

cue-2203
02:25:46.982 --> 02:25:47.502
were heard.

cue-2204
02:25:48.562 --> 02:25:53.442
Cornelius is an example. His prayers and
acts of kindness were accepted by

cue-2205
02:25:53.442 --> 02:25:53.822
God.

cue-2206
02:25:54.902 --> 02:25:59.822
Peter then understood that God does not
show favoritism, but accepts anyone

cue-2207
02:25:59.822 --> 02:26:04.762
who fears Him and lives rightly. The
prayers of a righteous person have

cue-2208
02:26:04.762 --> 02:26:05.502
great power.

cue-2209
02:26:06.222 --> 02:26:09.982
Faith does not replace right living. It
does not cover sin.

cue-2210
02:26:10.682 --> 02:26:15.650
Only Christ's sacrifice can do that.But
faith does save from sin,

cue-2211
02:26:15.650 --> 02:26:19.710
gives victory over it, and makes a person
righteous before God.

cue-2212
02:26:20.890 --> 02:26:23.090
Because of this, there is no condemnation.

cue-2213
02:26:23.790 --> 02:26:26.100
Instead, there is confidence before God.

cue-2214
02:26:26.890 --> 02:26:28.480
This brings assurance in prayer.

cue-2215
02:26:29.150 --> 02:26:33.650
When we obey Him and do what pleases Him,
we can ask with boldness, knowing that He

cue-2216
02:26:33.650 --> 02:26:35.290
hears and answers.

cue-2217
02:26:36.910 --> 02:26:37.330
Five,

cue-2218
02:26:38.370 --> 02:26:39.350
ask earnestly.

cue-2219
02:26:40.210 --> 02:26:45.130
God promises that He will be found by
those who seek Him with all their heart.

cue-2220
02:26:46.229 --> 02:26:50.890
Elijah's prayers were powerful because
they were full of deep feeling and strong

cue-2221
02:26:50.890 --> 02:26:51.450
desire.

cue-2222
02:26:52.290 --> 02:26:57.250
Jesus taught through his parables that
prayer should be persistent, continuing

cue-2223
02:26:57.250 --> 02:26:58.550
even when it is difficult.

cue-2224
02:26:59.570 --> 02:27:02.890
His own prayers were marked by deep cries
and tears.

cue-2225
02:27:03.970 --> 02:27:07.930
It is this kind of wholehearted, earnest
prayer that prevails.

cue-2226
02:27:09.550 --> 02:27:09.780
Six,

cue-2227
02:27:10.650 --> 02:27:15.290
ask in the Spirit. Elijah's effective
prayer was not just emotional.

cue-2228
02:27:15.290 --> 02:27:18.030
It was guided and strengthened by the
Holy Spirit.

cue-2229
02:27:18.780 --> 02:27:22.270
True prayer is inspired, directed, and
empowered by the Spirit of

cue-2230
02:27:22.270 --> 02:27:24.290
God. Seven,

cue-2231
02:27:24.970 --> 02:27:26.090
ask in faith.

cue-2232
02:27:27.010 --> 02:27:30.890
We must pray with believing hearts
according to the law of faith.

cue-2233
02:27:31.810 --> 02:27:36.150
Jesus taught that when we pray, we should
believe we have received what we ask for.

cue-2234
02:27:37.310 --> 02:27:40.030
Scripture gives many examples of this kind
of faith.

cue-2235
02:27:40.830 --> 02:27:44.369
Hebrews 11 shows how people lived and
acted by faith.

cue-2236
02:27:45.180 --> 02:27:49.550
They trusted God's promises even when they
could not yet see the results.

cue-2237
02:27:50.770 --> 02:27:53.840
Like the man who believed Jesus' word and
went his way,

cue-2238
02:27:54.510 --> 02:27:56.150
they moved forward with confidence.

cue-2239
02:27:57.030 --> 02:28:01.770
Israel shouted before the walls of Jericho
fell when there was no visible sign of

cue-2240
02:28:01.770 --> 02:28:04.270
change, and their faith brought victory.

cue-2241
02:28:05.390 --> 02:28:09.930
Jehoshaphat's singers praised God before
the battle began, and their faith was

cue-2242
02:28:09.930 --> 02:28:10.970
stronger than an army.

cue-2243
02:28:11.810 --> 02:28:16.670
Elijah spoke God's promise and never-
during a famine, and her supply never ran

cue-2244
02:28:16.670 --> 02:28:16.930
out.

cue-2245
02:28:17.910 --> 02:28:21.370
The prayer of faith is powerful because it
depends on God's power.

cue-2246
02:28:22.450 --> 02:28:26.750
When we pray, we are to believe that we
have received, and it will be given.

cue-2247
02:28:27.650 --> 02:28:29.810
God never fails to honor true faith.

cue-2248
02:28:33.170 --> 02:28:34.020
Chapter 14:

cue-2249
02:28:34.790 --> 02:28:36.890
Praying One for Another.

cue-2250
02:28:39.170 --> 02:28:43.270
The people in the Bible who prayed were
often intercessors. They prayed for

cue-2251
02:28:43.270 --> 02:28:46.290
others. Abraham prayed for Sodom and
Gomorrah.

cue-2252
02:28:46.950 --> 02:28:49.790
Moses prayed for Israel when they turned
away from God.

cue-2253
02:28:50.830 --> 02:28:54.450
Samuel prayed through the night for Saul
and continually for the nation.

cue-2254
02:28:55.240 --> 02:28:59.930
David prayed for his people. Daniel prayed
for the deliverance of God's people from

cue-2255
02:28:59.930 --> 02:29:04.790
captivity. Jesus prayed for his disciples
and especially for Peter.

cue-2256
02:29:05.630 --> 02:29:10.590
Paul lived out his teaching that prayers,
intercessions, and thanksgivings should

cue-2257
02:29:10.590 --> 02:29:15.450
be made for all people. At one point, it
is said that God was

cue-2258
02:29:15.450 --> 02:29:18.030
surprised that no one was praying for
others.

cue-2259
02:29:18.730 --> 02:29:22.590
He saw that there was no one to stand in
the gap and intercede.

cue-2260
02:29:23.450 --> 02:29:28.010
God's mercy in delivering people is often
connected to those who are willing to

cue-2261
02:29:28.010 --> 02:29:30.000
carry the burdens of others in prayer.

cue-2262
02:29:31.210 --> 02:29:35.790
God looked for someone to stand before Him
on behalf of the land but

cue-2263
02:29:35.790 --> 02:29:37.090
found no one.

cue-2264
02:29:38.490 --> 02:29:43.150
This shows that the normal purpose of
prayer is not only for ourselves, but to

cue-2265
02:29:43.150 --> 02:29:46.270
intercede, to pray to God for others.

cue-2266
02:29:48.430 --> 02:29:49.750
The mystery of intercession.

cue-2267
02:29:51.730 --> 02:29:56.590
The mystery of praying for others is one
of the deepest and most beautiful parts of

cue-2268
02:29:56.590 --> 02:29:56.910
prayer.

cue-2269
02:29:58.150 --> 02:30:01.050
If we do not fully understand how to pray
for ourselves,

cue-2270
02:30:01.670 --> 02:30:03.490
how can we know how to pray for others?

cue-2271
02:30:04.439 --> 02:30:06.930
We only partly understand our own needs,

cue-2272
02:30:07.550 --> 02:30:12.370
so how can we fully understand the needs
of someone else? Who are we to

cue-2273
02:30:12.370 --> 02:30:15.830
decide what another person truly needs
before God?

cue-2274
02:30:17.010 --> 02:30:20.790
God alone knows, and His knowledge and
love can be trusted.

cue-2275
02:30:21.830 --> 02:30:24.270
Yet prayer is not meant to be done alone.

cue-2276
02:30:24.910 --> 02:30:27.530
It is personal, but not separate from
others.

cue-2277
02:30:28.390 --> 02:30:33.240
Life is connected and dependent on one
another, as it says in Romans 14:7,

cue-2278
02:30:34.019 --> 02:30:35.519
"None of us lives to himself."

cue-2279
02:30:36.390 --> 02:30:39.000
Prayer can't remain only about our own
needs.

cue-2280
02:30:39.730 --> 02:30:44.430
Even when we pray privately, we are still
affected by the people in our homes,

cue-2281
02:30:44.430 --> 02:30:46.030
churches, and the world.

cue-2282
02:30:47.210 --> 02:30:48.810
The principle of prayer is this:

cue-2283
02:30:49.630 --> 02:30:53.830
Each person stands alone before God and is
responsible to Him,

cue-2284
02:30:54.650 --> 02:30:56.870
just as each will give an account of
himself.

cue-2285
02:30:58.070 --> 02:31:02.650
Each person carries his own burden, yet at
the same time carries the

cue-2286
02:31:02.650 --> 02:31:03.590
burdens of others.

cue-2287
02:31:04.780 --> 02:31:06.450
There is always a burden to bear.

cue-2288
02:31:07.150 --> 02:31:10.550
Praying for others means taking their
needs upon ourselves.

cue-2289
02:31:11.770 --> 02:31:16.610
The Savior interceded because He carried
the sins of others, as shown in Isaiah

cue-2290
02:31:16.610 --> 02:31:17.490
53:12.

cue-2291
02:31:18.710 --> 02:31:20.570
This is true of all prayer for others.

cue-2292
02:31:21.290 --> 02:31:25.980
Moses made the troubles of Israel his own
in his prayers, see

cue-2293
02:31:25.980 --> 02:31:27.390
Exodus and Numbers.

cue-2294
02:31:28.350 --> 02:31:32.710
Isaiah included himself among those with
unclean lips.

cue-2295
02:31:34.270 --> 02:31:36.480
Daniel confessed the sins of his nation.

cue-2296
02:31:37.160 --> 02:31:41.710
The father of the suffering boy and the
mother of the troubled daughter each made

cue-2297
02:31:41.710 --> 02:31:46.490
their child's need their own personal
plea. This has always been

cue-2298
02:31:46.490 --> 02:31:48.079
true in the history of the church.

cue-2299
02:31:48.830 --> 02:31:53.670
William Carey carried the burden of India,
Hudson Taylor of China, and David

cue-2300
02:31:53.670 --> 02:31:58.630
Livingstone of Africa. In the same way,
everyone carries the burden of

cue-2301
02:31:58.630 --> 02:32:00.170
those for whom they pray.

cue-2302
02:32:02.090 --> 02:32:03.910
The intercession in Heaven.

cue-2303
02:32:05.650 --> 02:32:10.610
Prayer is central in Heaven. This is where
the mystery of praying for others begins

cue-2304
02:32:10.610 --> 02:32:15.510
to be understood. It is sharing in the
work of our great High Priest at God's

cue-2305
02:32:15.510 --> 02:32:20.034
right hand.As Hebrews seven twenty-five
says,

cue-2306
02:32:20.634 --> 02:32:22.514
"He always lives to intercede."

cue-2307
02:32:23.414 --> 02:32:27.434
It is a mystery that Jesus needed to pray
while He lived on earth.

cue-2308
02:32:28.074 --> 02:32:32.214
It is an even greater mystery that He
continues to intercede in heaven.

cue-2309
02:32:33.414 --> 02:32:38.253
This is beyond our full understanding. We
cannot fully explain why or

cue-2310
02:32:38.254 --> 02:32:43.134
how, but because He lives to intercede, He
is able to completely

cue-2311
02:32:43.134 --> 02:32:45.934
save those who come to God through Him.

cue-2312
02:32:47.194 --> 02:32:49.874
What is revealed to us is clear and
certain.

cue-2313
02:32:50.914 --> 02:32:55.914
The risen Christ is both priest and king
at God's right hand.

cue-2314
02:32:55.914 --> 02:32:59.104
As high priest, He represents people
before God.

cue-2315
02:32:59.994 --> 02:33:04.654
As king, He represents God to people. He
entered God's

cue-2316
02:33:04.654 --> 02:33:08.254
presence by offering Himself as the
sacrifice for sin.

cue-2317
02:33:09.234 --> 02:33:13.914
Through His own blood, He became the one
mediator between God and humanity,

cue-2318
02:33:13.914 --> 02:33:17.424
and the advocate who speaks to the Father
on our behalf.

cue-2319
02:33:18.304 --> 02:33:20.294
He continues to intercede for us.

cue-2320
02:33:21.134 --> 02:33:25.614
Our prayers are accepted and made
effective through Him and His finished

cue-2321
02:33:25.614 --> 02:33:25.914
work.

cue-2322
02:33:27.074 --> 02:33:31.554
He takes the prayers offered on earth and
joins them with the power of heaven,

cue-2323
02:33:31.554 --> 02:33:34.154
making them pleasing to God through His
name.

cue-2324
02:33:35.384 --> 02:33:39.074
This is what has been revealed to us, and
we should not go beyond it,

cue-2325
02:33:39.754 --> 02:33:43.654
but it shows that prayer exists in heaven
as well as on earth.

cue-2326
02:33:44.894 --> 02:33:49.894
In the shared life of God's people, prayer
continues, and there is no reason

cue-2327
02:33:49.894 --> 02:33:54.614
to think that those who are redeemed are
left out of this work of intercession.

cue-2328
02:33:56.814 --> 02:33:58.304
The intercession of the Spirit.

cue-2329
02:34:00.934 --> 02:34:02.814
There are two kinds of intercession.

cue-2330
02:34:03.424 --> 02:34:07.594
The high priest intercedes for us in
heaven, and the Holy Spirit intercedes

cue-2331
02:34:07.594 --> 02:34:09.574
within the temple of the devoted soul.

cue-2332
02:34:10.484 --> 02:34:13.034
The Spirit also helps our weaknesses,

cue-2333
02:34:13.714 --> 02:34:18.714
for we do not know what we should pray for
as we ought, but the Spirit Himself

cue-2334
02:34:18.714 --> 02:34:22.514
intercedes for us with groanings too deep
for words.

cue-2335
02:34:23.694 --> 02:34:28.413
And He who searches hearts knows the mind
of the Spirit because the Spirit

cue-2336
02:34:28.414 --> 02:34:33.414
intercedes for the saints according to the
will of God. These

cue-2337
02:34:33.414 --> 02:34:38.194
two intercessions are so united in purpose
and so perfectly in

cue-2338
02:34:38.194 --> 02:34:40.494
harmony that they are truly one.

cue-2339
02:34:41.694 --> 02:34:46.034
What is prayed by the intercessor on earth
is also prayed by the intercessor in

cue-2340
02:34:46.034 --> 02:34:50.754
heaven. The Spirit takes the things of
Christ and shows them to us.

cue-2341
02:34:51.914 --> 02:34:55.494
He takes the deep things of God and makes
them known to us.

cue-2342
02:34:56.674 --> 02:35:01.214
He knows the purpose of God and intercedes
according to the divine will.

cue-2343
02:35:02.334 --> 02:35:02.994
In this way,

cue-2344
02:35:03.614 --> 02:35:04.794
He works in us both

cue-2345
02:35:05.394 --> 02:35:08.554
the desire and the power to do what
pleases God.

cue-2346
02:35:09.634 --> 02:35:12.934
The groaning that cannot be spoken belongs
to our weak humanity,

cue-2347
02:35:13.534 --> 02:35:18.034
but the wordless groaning of the Spirit
within us is fully expressed through the

cue-2348
02:35:18.034 --> 02:35:23.024
priestly ministry of Christ in heaven.
Intercession through

cue-2349
02:35:23.024 --> 02:35:26.274
the Spirit requires a temple filled with
the Spirit.

cue-2350
02:35:27.144 --> 02:35:31.424
He can only make spiritual things clear to
those who are spiritually minded

cue-2351
02:35:32.094 --> 02:35:35.994
because the carnal mind can't understand
the mind of the Spirit.

cue-2352
02:35:37.184 --> 02:35:41.254
He can't intercede in the heart of a will
that has not been yielded to

cue-2353
02:35:41.254 --> 02:35:46.214
God. The pure in heart see God. The heart
must be open to

cue-2354
02:35:46.214 --> 02:35:48.774
light and obedient to the heavenly
vision.

cue-2355
02:35:49.894 --> 02:35:53.494
A person must be a saint to share in the
ministry of intercession.

cue-2356
02:35:54.594 --> 02:35:59.154
There are many kinds of service that do
not require deep spirituality to succeed.

cue-2357
02:35:59.914 --> 02:36:04.914
Preaching may become an art with no power
of the Spirit. Outward church ministry

cue-2358
02:36:04.914 --> 02:36:08.504
may be carried on by the abilities of
office and routine alone.

cue-2359
02:36:09.814 --> 02:36:13.934
Social service may produce good reports
without any warmth of spiritual life.

cue-2360
02:36:14.974 --> 02:36:19.774
Church music may be of such a kind that it
does not require the burden and pain of

cue-2361
02:36:19.774 --> 02:36:20.434
intercession.

cue-2362
02:36:21.464 --> 02:36:23.554
The man of prayer must be a man of God.

cue-2363
02:36:25.554 --> 02:36:27.594
The intercession of the secret place.

cue-2364
02:36:29.774 --> 02:36:32.494
We are called to share in this twofold
intercession.

cue-2365
02:36:33.114 --> 02:36:37.654
The words used to describe it show that it
requires sacrifice, hard labor, and

cue-2366
02:36:37.654 --> 02:36:42.174
steady earnestness. Few things cost more.
Paul speaks of

cue-2367
02:36:42.174 --> 02:36:44.854
travail, striving, and laboring in prayer.

cue-2368
02:36:45.754 --> 02:36:49.474
Victorious intercession always carries
deep burden and suffering.

cue-2369
02:36:50.474 --> 02:36:55.434
The reason is not that God is unwilling,
because when He inspires prayer,

cue-2370
02:36:55.434 --> 02:36:57.374
it is because He intends to answer.

cue-2371
02:36:58.724 --> 02:37:03.354
The struggle comes from many enemies in
the human will and also from spiritual

cue-2372
02:37:03.354 --> 02:37:04.574
powers and forces.

cue-2373
02:37:05.434 --> 02:37:10.014
God waits to bless, which means He is
always ready and always willing.

cue-2374
02:37:11.174 --> 02:37:15.494
Daniel's prayer was delayed for three
weeks because of a hidden conflict in the

cue-2375
02:37:15.494 --> 02:37:16.494
spiritual realm.

cue-2376
02:37:17.234 --> 02:37:17.874
Paul says,

cue-2377
02:37:18.614 --> 02:37:23.434
"Our wrestling is not against flesh and
blood, but against the principalities,

cue-2378
02:37:23.434 --> 02:37:28.074
against the powers, against the world
rulers of this darkness, against the

cue-2379
02:37:28.074 --> 02:37:32.874
spiritual hosts of wickedness in the
heavenly places."

cue-2380
02:37:32.874 --> 02:37:33.674
Jesus said,

cue-2381
02:37:34.344 --> 02:37:39.254
"Satan hath desired to have you that he
may sift you as wheat, but I have

cue-2382
02:37:39.254 --> 02:37:40.014
prayed for thee."

cue-2383
02:37:40.914 --> 02:37:43.134
For whom and for what should we pray?

cue-2384
02:37:44.114 --> 02:37:48.164
The general answer is for everyone and for
everything.

cue-2385
02:37:48.814 --> 02:37:53.724
But the truer answer is according to the
intercession of the Spirit and according

cue-2386
02:37:53.724 --> 02:37:54.734
to the will of God.

cue-2387
02:37:55.954 --> 02:38:00.794
Some people have a special claim on our
prayers, our families, our friends,

cue-2388
02:38:00.794 --> 02:38:04.394
our fellow believers, our ministers, and
fellow workers,

cue-2389
02:38:05.294 --> 02:38:10.153
those we work beside, those over us, and
all those we know to be in

cue-2390
02:38:10.154 --> 02:38:10.514
need.

cue-2391
02:38:11.774 --> 02:38:16.554
Intercessory prayer requires intelligence,
understanding, watchfulness,

cue-2392
02:38:16.554 --> 02:38:19.754
sympathy, earnestness, and sacrifice.

cue-2393
02:38:20.794 --> 02:38:25.546
It often also requires patient endurance
and faith.Sometimes the

cue-2394
02:38:25.546 --> 02:38:28.866
answer comes at once, and sometimes it is
delayed.

cue-2395
02:38:30.016 --> 02:38:34.046
The one truth on which faith rests is that
the answer does come.

cue-2396
02:38:34.866 --> 02:38:39.746
The Spirit who gives assurance knows every
circumstance, and His assurances are

cue-2397
02:38:39.746 --> 02:38:43.306
always yes and amen in Christ Jesus.

cue-2398
02:38:44.566 --> 02:38:49.126
I have tried more to describe the holy
place of my own faith than to give rules

cue-2399
02:38:49.126 --> 02:38:50.286
or list examples.

cue-2400
02:38:51.446 --> 02:38:55.786
This subject fills all Scripture, and its
reach has no limits.

cue-2401
02:38:56.666 --> 02:39:00.906
Its mysteries cannot be fully searched
out, but its certainties never

cue-2402
02:39:00.906 --> 02:39:05.326
fail. Its blessings cannot be measured and
are beyond price.

cue-2403
02:39:06.146 --> 02:39:10.606
Who can tell how much has entered into a
person's life through the prayers of

cue-2404
02:39:10.606 --> 02:39:10.946
others?

cue-2405
02:39:12.146 --> 02:39:17.126
Who can measure the work done by those
whose ministry is to labor in prayer for

cue-2406
02:39:17.126 --> 02:39:17.566
others?

cue-2407
02:39:19.166 --> 02:39:21.406
God's great need is for intercessors.

cue-2408
02:39:22.266 --> 02:39:27.006
Ye that are the Lord's remembrances, take
ye no rest, and give him no rest

cue-2409
02:39:27.006 --> 02:39:31.666
till he establish, and till he make
Jerusalem a praise in the earth.

cue-2410
02:39:33.486 --> 02:39:36.486
He still saves through those who sigh and
cry.

cue-2411
02:39:39.826 --> 02:39:40.746
Chapter fifteen:

cue-2412
02:39:41.546 --> 02:39:43.406
Praying for divine healing.

cue-2413
02:39:45.226 --> 02:39:48.046
The subject of divine healing is always on
my mind.

cue-2414
02:39:48.686 --> 02:39:53.526
Weaknesses and sicknesses in the body have
kept it before me as a constant question

cue-2415
02:39:53.526 --> 02:39:54.286
in my faith.

cue-2416
02:39:55.286 --> 02:40:00.286
In pastoral work, it can't be avoided.
Sick people look with hope to the words of

cue-2417
02:40:00.286 --> 02:40:03.666
the Apostle James about the prayer that
heals the sick,

cue-2418
02:40:04.286 --> 02:40:05.706
and they ask for guidance.

cue-2419
02:40:06.466 --> 02:40:08.486
Some are healed through the prayer of
faith.

cue-2420
02:40:09.146 --> 02:40:11.006
If one is healed, why not another?

cue-2421
02:40:11.606 --> 02:40:13.526
If some are healed, why not all?

cue-2422
02:40:14.706 --> 02:40:19.246
I have searched the scriptures over and
over from beginning to end so that I might

cue-2423
02:40:19.246 --> 02:40:20.426
understand the truth.

cue-2424
02:40:21.526 --> 02:40:24.146
I have not found this subject easy to
answer.

cue-2425
02:40:26.026 --> 02:40:27.766
The problem of divine healing.

cue-2426
02:40:30.526 --> 02:40:33.386
There is such a thing as healing through
the prayer of faith.

cue-2427
02:40:34.026 --> 02:40:37.386
Many trustworthy and godly people bear
witness to this truth.

cue-2428
02:40:38.106 --> 02:40:42.826
It also seems that some are given the gift
of healing, and when they lay hands on

cue-2429
02:40:42.826 --> 02:40:44.646
the sick, the sick recover.

cue-2430
02:40:45.946 --> 02:40:48.686
I myself have been healed through the
prayer of faith.

cue-2431
02:40:49.906 --> 02:40:54.046
In my ministry, God has also used me in
the healing of the sick.

cue-2432
02:40:55.126 --> 02:41:00.066
But I have never prayed for healing except
when the sick strongly asked for it,

cue-2433
02:41:00.066 --> 02:41:02.486
and I felt a clear leading from the Spirit
of God.

cue-2434
02:41:03.586 --> 02:41:06.666
In other cases, I have been completely
helpless.

cue-2435
02:41:07.846 --> 02:41:11.916
There have been people for whom I would
gladly have given my right hand if I could

cue-2436
02:41:11.916 --> 02:41:13.306
have prayed them back to health,

cue-2437
02:41:14.186 --> 02:41:17.346
but I had to watch them suffer and die.

cue-2438
02:41:18.126 --> 02:41:22.626
Some have suffered deep mental anguish
because they sought healing and did not

cue-2439
02:41:22.626 --> 02:41:23.246
receive it.

cue-2440
02:41:24.306 --> 02:41:25.466
That has been my problem.

cue-2441
02:41:26.446 --> 02:41:30.506
When I was still a young minister, one of
the church workers became seriously

cue-2442
02:41:30.506 --> 02:41:35.126
ill. We claimed the promises of God, and
some of the finest

cue-2443
02:41:35.126 --> 02:41:39.446
Christians I have ever known prayed
earnestly and in faith for his recovery.

cue-2444
02:41:40.426 --> 02:41:42.546
We would not believe that faith could
fail,

cue-2445
02:41:43.286 --> 02:41:45.246
but he died while we were still praying.

cue-2446
02:41:46.186 --> 02:41:47.946
The shock to our faith was very great.

cue-2447
02:41:49.586 --> 02:41:52.486
One of my own sisters was an invalid for
many years.

cue-2448
02:41:53.426 --> 02:41:57.475
Well-meaning but mistaken believers
troubled her with the same kind of

cue-2449
02:41:57.475 --> 02:42:00.606
arguments that Job's comforters used
against him.

cue-2450
02:42:01.906 --> 02:42:06.246
Together we searched the scriptures and
sought the Lord, pleading with him to heal

cue-2451
02:42:06.246 --> 02:42:06.426
her.

cue-2452
02:42:07.426 --> 02:42:11.666
The Lord answered her in a vision and gave
her peace, but not healing.

cue-2453
02:42:12.886 --> 02:42:17.226
I could give many more examples on both
sides, and perhaps others have been

cue-2454
02:42:17.226 --> 02:42:18.906
troubled by the same questions.

cue-2455
02:42:21.426 --> 02:42:23.006
Witnesses to divine healing.

cue-2456
02:42:25.446 --> 02:42:28.746
There are many people who testify that the
Lord is our healer.

cue-2457
02:42:29.546 --> 02:42:33.486
A few weeks ago, I was near Bishop
Auckland, where Pastor Jeffries had held a

cue-2458
02:42:33.486 --> 02:42:34.926
mission some months earlier.

cue-2459
02:42:36.006 --> 02:42:40.646
As we were leaving a house we had visited,
one woman in our group said to her sister

cue-2460
02:42:40.646 --> 02:42:45.586
that she was sorry she had not brought
some special tablets for her. The sister

cue-2461
02:42:45.586 --> 02:42:50.546
had suffered severe headaches for years,
and this was a new remedy she intended to

cue-2462
02:42:50.546 --> 02:42:50.946
try.

cue-2463
02:42:52.326 --> 02:42:53.406
She answered cheerfully,

cue-2464
02:42:54.036 --> 02:42:58.736
"You need not bring them. I do not need
them anymore. The Lord healed me,

cue-2465
02:42:58.736 --> 02:43:01.746
and I have not had even the slightest
pain since."

cue-2466
02:43:02.986 --> 02:43:05.816
Her husband and children confirmed her
words by saying,

cue-2467
02:43:06.516 --> 02:43:07.746
"She is a different woman."

cue-2468
02:43:09.586 --> 02:43:14.246
There are many testimonies like this. The
most remarkable case of divine healing I

cue-2469
02:43:14.246 --> 02:43:16.906
have known happened at the Southport
Convention.

cue-2470
02:43:17.966 --> 02:43:21.196
The Reverend W. H. Tindall was president
of the convention.

cue-2471
02:43:22.226 --> 02:43:26.446
Because of the strain of much speaking, he
had developed a disease of the throat.

cue-2472
02:43:27.626 --> 02:43:31.966
For more than a year, he had not spoken
above a whisper, and even that caused

cue-2473
02:43:31.966 --> 02:43:32.306
pain.

cue-2474
02:43:33.526 --> 02:43:35.716
Specialists gave no hope of recovery.

cue-2475
02:43:36.426 --> 02:43:39.846
At all the meetings, he was a sorrowful
and silent figure.

cue-2476
02:43:40.526 --> 02:43:42.486
People prayed for him continually.

cue-2477
02:43:43.566 --> 02:43:48.026
At the speaker's prayer meeting on Friday
morning, there was an unusual strength and

cue-2478
02:43:48.026 --> 02:43:48.986
unity of faith.

cue-2479
02:43:50.026 --> 02:43:54.106
No one could pray for anything except the
recovery of Mr. Tindall's voice.

cue-2480
02:43:55.466 --> 02:44:00.266
Faith grew bold, forgot what seemed
impossible, and claimed the promise.

cue-2481
02:44:01.846 --> 02:44:04.866
Dr. Ebenezer E. Jenkins was leading the
meeting.

cue-2482
02:44:05.946 --> 02:44:09.956
When the rest of us rose from our knees,
Mr. Tindall remained kneeling.

cue-2483
02:44:10.946 --> 02:44:12.016
Dr. Jenkins said,

cue-2484
02:44:12.756 --> 02:44:16.126
"This is the most remarkable prayer
meeting I have ever known."

cue-2485
02:44:17.366 --> 02:44:22.126
Then he placed his hand on the president's
head and declared, in the name of the

cue-2486
02:44:22.126 --> 02:44:27.116
Lord, that before the convention ended, we
would hear Mr. Tindall speak in

cue-2487
02:44:27.116 --> 02:44:32.019
the tent.That night, Mr. Tyndall spoke in
the tent for fifteen minutes

cue-2488
02:44:32.019 --> 02:44:36.750
and was heard by twelve hundred people.
He continued to preach

cue-2489
02:44:36.750 --> 02:44:39.370
without losing his voice for the rest of
his life.

cue-2490
02:44:40.530 --> 02:44:45.450
I was there and saw and heard it myself,
and there are still living witnesses who

cue-2491
02:44:45.450 --> 02:44:46.950
can confirm what I say.

cue-2492
02:44:48.630 --> 02:44:53.170
The experience of E. Stanley Jones,
recorded in The Christ of the Indian

cue-2493
02:44:53.170 --> 02:44:57.540
Road, is another striking example of God's
will and power to heal.

cue-2494
02:44:58.710 --> 02:45:03.390
Just before the greatest missionary
opportunity of his life, he found himself

cue-2495
02:45:03.390 --> 02:45:05.990
spiritually weak and physically worn out.

cue-2496
02:45:07.190 --> 02:45:07.550
He wrote,

cue-2497
02:45:08.350 --> 02:45:10.710
I saw that unless I got help from
somewhere,

cue-2498
02:45:11.450 --> 02:45:15.850
I would have to give up my missionary
career, go back to America, and work on a

cue-2499
02:45:15.850 --> 02:45:17.610
farm to try to regain my health.

cue-2500
02:45:18.490 --> 02:45:20.510
It was one of the darkest hours.

cue-2501
02:45:21.630 --> 02:45:23.710
At that time, he was in a meeting at
Lucknow.

cue-2502
02:45:24.450 --> 02:45:27.660
While he was praying, and not especially
thinking about himself,

cue-2503
02:45:28.300 --> 02:45:29.810
he seemed to hear a voice say,

cue-2504
02:45:30.690 --> 02:45:33.570
Are you yourself ready for this work to
which I have called you?

cue-2505
02:45:34.850 --> 02:45:35.610
He replied,

cue-2506
02:45:36.350 --> 02:45:40.410
No, Lord, I am finished. I have come to
the end of my strength.

cue-2507
02:45:41.750 --> 02:45:42.690
The voice answered,

cue-2508
02:45:43.550 --> 02:45:48.030
If you will hand that over to me and stop
worrying about it, I will take care of it.

cue-2509
02:45:48.030 --> 02:45:50.390
He answered at once,

cue-2510
02:45:51.170 --> 02:45:54.110
Lord, I make that agreement here and now.

cue-2511
02:45:55.470 --> 02:45:59.790
Then a great peace filled his heart and
spread through his whole being.

cue-2512
02:46:01.030 --> 02:46:02.470
He knew the answer had come.

cue-2513
02:46:03.190 --> 02:46:05.170
Abundant life had taken hold of him.

cue-2514
02:46:05.950 --> 02:46:09.130
For days afterward, he hardly seemed aware
of having a body.

cue-2515
02:46:09.840 --> 02:46:12.330
He worked through each day and far into
the night,

cue-2516
02:46:12.950 --> 02:46:17.930
and when bedtime came, he wondered why he
should go to bed at all, because he felt

cue-2517
02:46:17.930 --> 02:46:18.930
no tiredness.

cue-2518
02:46:20.110 --> 02:46:24.910
He seemed filled with life, peace, rest,
and with Christ himself.

cue-2519
02:46:26.470 --> 02:46:29.820
Nine of the most demanding years of his
life passed after that,

cue-2520
02:46:30.520 --> 02:46:32.410
and the old trouble never returned.

cue-2521
02:46:33.610 --> 02:46:36.350
He said he had never before enjoyed such
health.

cue-2522
02:46:37.390 --> 02:46:42.230
It was as if he had found a new source of
life for body, mind, and spirit.

cue-2523
02:46:43.330 --> 02:46:47.910
Life had been lifted to a permanently
higher level, and he had done nothing but

cue-2524
02:46:47.910 --> 02:46:49.109
receive it.

cue-2525
02:46:49.690 --> 02:46:52.650
The Reverend Andrew Murray had a very
similar experience.

cue-2526
02:46:53.390 --> 02:46:58.190
After he was healed, he traveled widely
through Europe, America, and South Africa

cue-2527
02:46:58.190 --> 02:47:02.550
for several years, preaching and speaking
every day with great power.

cue-2528
02:47:03.730 --> 02:47:08.070
Yet later in life, when he became ill
again, he said to his daughter with great

cue-2529
02:47:08.070 --> 02:47:08.520
tenderness,

cue-2530
02:47:09.490 --> 02:47:10.110
My child,

cue-2531
02:47:10.850 --> 02:47:15.710
I would so much like to hold evangelistic
meetings, but God does not see fit to

cue-2532
02:47:15.710 --> 02:47:16.150
heal me.

cue-2533
02:47:18.610 --> 02:47:19.770
What does Scripture say?

cue-2534
02:47:21.830 --> 02:47:25.390
The teaching of Scripture is the final
authority on this subject,

cue-2535
02:47:26.030 --> 02:47:28.570
as it is on every matter of faith and
life.

cue-2536
02:47:29.810 --> 02:47:34.590
For me, the Bible has the last word. I
accept what it teaches, whether I fully

cue-2537
02:47:34.590 --> 02:47:35.710
understand it or not.

cue-2538
02:47:36.610 --> 02:47:37.490
Faith can wait.

cue-2539
02:47:38.510 --> 02:47:43.410
It may be humbling to endure the pity of
those who speak confidently from science,

cue-2540
02:47:43.410 --> 02:47:45.699
philosophy, learning, or psychology,

cue-2541
02:47:46.490 --> 02:47:51.449
but Christ's yoke is easy when faith is
sure and humility is willing to

cue-2542
02:47:51.450 --> 02:47:56.110
wait for God's time. When evolution and
revelation seem to

cue-2543
02:47:56.110 --> 02:47:59.010
disagree, faith rests on revelation.

cue-2544
02:47:59.950 --> 02:48:04.350
Yet the greater difficulty is not the
opposition of science or scholarship, but

cue-2545
02:48:04.350 --> 02:48:06.850
the disagreements among believers
themselves.

cue-2546
02:48:07.730 --> 02:48:09.150
Interpretations differ,

cue-2547
02:48:09.750 --> 02:48:13.690
but instead of joining every argument, we
should seek to know the truth for

cue-2548
02:48:13.690 --> 02:48:16.030
ourselves, as far as we are able.

cue-2549
02:48:17.850 --> 02:48:21.610
There is no doubt that Scripture teaches
that the Lord is our healer.

cue-2550
02:48:22.250 --> 02:48:24.910
This is one of the names by which he
reveals himself.

cue-2551
02:48:26.090 --> 02:48:30.889
It is also clear that our Lord and Savior
treated healing as an essential part of

cue-2552
02:48:30.890 --> 02:48:31.540
his ministry.

cue-2553
02:48:32.630 --> 02:48:37.490
He was a physician who healed all kinds of
diseases without medicine. He

cue-2554
02:48:37.490 --> 02:48:39.770
sent his apostles out to heal the sick.

cue-2555
02:48:40.790 --> 02:48:44.890
The gift of healing was, and still is, one
of the gifts of the

cue-2556
02:48:44.890 --> 02:48:48.549
Spirit. Healing was part of the ministry
of the apostles.

cue-2557
02:48:49.549 --> 02:48:52.130
This gift has never been taken away from
the church.

cue-2558
02:48:52.810 --> 02:48:55.990
In every age, there have been witnesses to
its power.

cue-2559
02:48:57.070 --> 02:49:00.790
The promise in the Epistle of James still
stands for all time.

cue-2560
02:49:01.730 --> 02:49:05.890
The prayer of faith shall save the sick,
and the Lord shall raise him up,

cue-2561
02:49:06.570 --> 02:49:09.590
and if he have committed sins, they shall
be forgiven him.

cue-2562
02:49:10.830 --> 02:49:13.270
The Bible connects sickness with Satan.

cue-2563
02:49:13.950 --> 02:49:18.170
God did not create man to be sick.
Sickness entered with sin.

cue-2564
02:49:19.110 --> 02:49:22.010
Jesus said that some sicknesses came from
the devil.

cue-2565
02:49:22.610 --> 02:49:26.710
He said of one woman that Satan had bound
her for eighteen years.

cue-2566
02:49:27.910 --> 02:49:29.830
In Acts 10.38, we read that

cue-2567
02:49:30.550 --> 02:49:34.850
Jesus went about doing good and healing
all who were oppressed of the devil.

cue-2568
02:49:36.130 --> 02:49:40.630
At the same time, Jesus rebuked those who
said that sickness and

cue-2569
02:49:40.630 --> 02:49:43.170
suffering always come from personal sin.

cue-2570
02:49:44.310 --> 02:49:44.770
He said,

cue-2571
02:49:45.410 --> 02:49:49.750
Neither hath this man sinned nor his
parents that he should be born

cue-2572
02:49:49.810 --> 02:49:50.430
blind.

cue-2573
02:49:51.580 --> 02:49:55.630
Sickness and sin are connected in the work
of redemption and healing.

cue-2574
02:49:56.790 --> 02:50:01.210
Matthew sees the healing ministry of our
Lord as the fulfillment of Isaiah's

cue-2575
02:50:01.210 --> 02:50:01.710
prophecy.

cue-2576
02:50:02.770 --> 02:50:07.630
He cast out the spirits with his word and
healed all that were sick, that it

cue-2577
02:50:07.630 --> 02:50:12.470
might be fulfilled which was spoken by
Esaias the prophet, saying, Himself

cue-2578
02:50:12.470 --> 02:50:15.630
took our infirmities and bare our
sicknesses.

cue-2579
02:50:16.850 --> 02:50:21.650
He bore our sicknesses as he bore our
sins, because both were part of the

cue-2580
02:50:21.650 --> 02:50:22.430
same burden.

cue-2581
02:50:23.600 --> 02:50:28.290
This does not mean that sickness itself
was transferred to him, for as far as we

cue-2582
02:50:28.290 --> 02:50:33.262
know, he was never sick.Rather, in deep
sympathy and at great

cue-2583
02:50:33.262 --> 02:50:38.142
cost to himself in body and mind, he
lifted the burden and carried it

cue-2584
02:50:38.142 --> 02:50:43.072
away. The sinless Christ bore our sins,
and the one who was never

cue-2585
02:50:43.072 --> 02:50:44.862
sick bore our sicknesses.

cue-2586
02:50:45.942 --> 02:50:50.522
When he healed the paralyzed man who was
lowered through the roof, he first dealt

cue-2587
02:50:50.522 --> 02:50:51.262
with his sin.

cue-2588
02:50:52.262 --> 02:50:55.922
To others whom he healed, he said that
they should sin no

cue-2589
02:50:55.922 --> 02:51:00.522
more. The passage in James also connects
healing with

cue-2590
02:51:00.522 --> 02:51:01.162
forgiveness.

cue-2591
02:51:01.962 --> 02:51:06.602
Paul also writes in First Corinthians
eleven thirty-one to thirty-two of

cue-2592
02:51:06.602 --> 02:51:10.602
sickness and even death coming from
spiritual wrongdoing.

cue-2593
02:51:11.722 --> 02:51:15.622
Yet there is also sickness in which there
is no personal sin.

cue-2594
02:51:16.682 --> 02:51:21.502
It may be true in a broad theological
sense that all sickness entered through

cue-2595
02:51:21.502 --> 02:51:21.842
sin,

cue-2596
02:51:22.562 --> 02:51:27.382
but in actual experience, there is a kind
of sickness that belongs to grace.

cue-2597
02:51:28.222 --> 02:51:30.102
Scripture must explain scripture.

cue-2598
02:51:30.722 --> 02:51:34.722
Job's suffering was of grace. It was for
the glory of God.

cue-2599
02:51:35.582 --> 02:51:38.602
Paul's thorn in the flesh was not caused
by sin.

cue-2600
02:51:39.322 --> 02:51:43.242
Satan used it, but God allowed it for the
glory of his grace.

cue-2601
02:51:44.102 --> 02:51:48.702
Paul healed others, yet accepted his own
suffering as part of the

cue-2602
02:51:48.702 --> 02:51:49.852
sufferings of Christ.

cue-2603
02:51:50.982 --> 02:51:53.382
Epaphroditus was healed by the Lord.

cue-2604
02:51:54.342 --> 02:51:57.662
Trophimus, however, Paul had to leave sick
at Miletus.

cue-2605
02:51:58.762 --> 02:52:02.012
For Timothy's stomach troubles, Paul
advised a little wine.

cue-2606
02:52:03.262 --> 02:52:07.802
And in his travels, Paul was accompanied
by Luke, the beloved physician.

cue-2607
02:52:10.002 --> 02:52:11.332
I believe in divine healing.

cue-2608
02:52:13.502 --> 02:52:18.252
I believe in the healing power that comes
through faith. Even apart from religion,

cue-2609
02:52:18.252 --> 02:52:21.462
there is often health for the person who
lives by faith.

cue-2610
02:52:22.442 --> 02:52:27.422
Much sickness has its roots in the mind as
well as in the body. But divine healing

cue-2611
02:52:27.422 --> 02:52:29.652
is more than healing through faith alone.

cue-2612
02:52:30.612 --> 02:52:33.622
It is not the same as hypnotism or
auto-suggestion.

cue-2613
02:52:34.532 --> 02:52:38.622
The Lord himself is the healer, and faith
is placed in him.

cue-2614
02:52:39.522 --> 02:52:41.802
The foundation of my faith is in him.

cue-2615
02:52:42.682 --> 02:52:47.582
I trust his word, the redeeming work of
Christ, and the sanctifying power of his

cue-2616
02:52:47.582 --> 02:52:51.222
Spirit, who gives life even to our mortal
bodies.

cue-2617
02:52:52.392 --> 02:52:54.962
The chief concern is to know the will of
God.

cue-2618
02:52:56.062 --> 02:53:00.442
Sickness may sometimes be a loving
correction for disobedience, and through

cue-2619
02:53:00.442 --> 02:53:05.042
faith the cause may be removed, the sin
forgiven, and health restored.

cue-2620
02:53:06.242 --> 02:53:10.322
But I am also bound to believe that
sickness may sometimes be within the will

cue-2621
02:53:10.322 --> 02:53:15.322
of God for discipline, for the glory of
his grace, and for service

cue-2622
02:53:15.322 --> 02:53:15.902
to Christ.

cue-2623
02:53:17.102 --> 02:53:21.742
I am certain that divine healing is real
and that the gift of healing still

cue-2624
02:53:21.742 --> 02:53:22.902
remains in the church,

cue-2625
02:53:23.862 --> 02:53:25.462
waiting for the prayer of faith.

cue-2626
02:53:26.582 --> 02:53:30.942
I am certain that many people are sick who
should never have become sick and who

cue-2627
02:53:30.942 --> 02:53:32.412
could even now be healed.

cue-2628
02:53:33.552 --> 02:53:38.082
I am certain that no life is so full of
health and light as the life of

cue-2629
02:53:38.082 --> 02:53:39.722
joyful and obedient faith.

cue-2630
02:53:40.902 --> 02:53:45.322
I am certain that I believe with all my
heart and mind in divine healing, even

cue-2631
02:53:45.322 --> 02:53:48.222
though I myself am often unwell.

cue-2632
02:53:51.182 --> 02:53:54.542
Chapter sixteen: The problem of unanswered
prayer.

cue-2633
02:53:57.342 --> 02:54:01.002
It has been many years since I first wrote
about unanswered prayer.

cue-2634
02:54:01.982 --> 02:54:06.962
The problem became very real to me when a
man we were praying for so earnestly and

cue-2635
02:54:06.962 --> 02:54:09.522
confidently died while we were still
praying.

cue-2636
02:54:10.672 --> 02:54:11.982
The shock was overwhelming.

cue-2637
02:54:12.622 --> 02:54:14.862
It had never entered our minds that he
might die.

cue-2638
02:54:15.982 --> 02:54:20.102
We had claimed the promise. We were
completely sure of God's Word.

cue-2639
02:54:21.382 --> 02:54:24.362
I do not think my faith has ever been
tested more severely.

cue-2640
02:54:25.462 --> 02:54:30.402
So we went back to the Word, and God gave
me a message that has brought comfort to

cue-2641
02:54:30.402 --> 02:54:31.032
many people.

cue-2642
02:54:32.262 --> 02:54:36.482
Through all the years since, it has
remained a strong support for my faith.

cue-2643
02:54:37.442 --> 02:54:40.922
Many years have passed, but the truth
still stands.

cue-2644
02:54:41.802 --> 02:54:43.802
Even if I must repeat myself somewhat,

cue-2645
02:54:44.582 --> 02:54:47.062
I want to pass this message on to others.

cue-2646
02:54:49.162 --> 02:54:49.701
The problem.

cue-2647
02:54:52.162 --> 02:54:56.702
There can be no doubt that God answers
prayer. Scripture speaks very clearly

cue-2648
02:54:56.702 --> 02:54:59.122
about this. Nothing could be more certain.

cue-2649
02:55:00.042 --> 02:55:05.042
All people are commanded to pray at all
times, in all places, and for all

cue-2650
02:55:05.042 --> 02:55:05.942
kinds of needs.

cue-2651
02:55:06.712 --> 02:55:09.642
The Bible gives many assurances that
prayer is heard.

cue-2652
02:55:10.292 --> 02:55:14.962
The promises are plain, and Scripture is
full of examples and encouragement.

cue-2653
02:55:16.122 --> 02:55:19.662
Christ himself said, "Everyone that asketh
receiveth."

cue-2654
02:55:20.492 --> 02:55:24.662
The promise is not limited by place, by
time, or by subject.

cue-2655
02:55:25.642 --> 02:55:30.322
Everything that concerns us matters to God
and is a proper subject for prayer.

cue-2656
02:55:31.522 --> 02:55:36.401
God does not separate our needs into
sacred and secular or spiritual and

cue-2657
02:55:36.402 --> 02:55:36.922
material.

cue-2658
02:55:37.842 --> 02:55:42.482
The one who taught us to pray for the
forgiveness of our sins also taught us to

cue-2659
02:55:42.482 --> 02:55:45.422
say, "Give us this day our daily bread."

cue-2660
02:55:46.402 --> 02:55:51.062
Yet as we study this subject, it becomes
clear that there are conditions and

cue-2661
02:55:51.062 --> 02:55:51.462
limits.

cue-2662
02:55:52.382 --> 02:55:57.262
Prayer has its laws. The promises that
seem unlimited are surrounded

cue-2663
02:55:57.262 --> 02:55:58.582
by certain conditions.

cue-2664
02:55:59.842 --> 02:56:04.082
We are commanded to pray for all people,
yet there were some for whom the prophet

cue-2665
02:56:04.082 --> 02:56:08.982
was told not to pray. It is possible to
ask and not

cue-2666
02:56:08.982 --> 02:56:09.582
receive.

cue-2667
02:56:10.272 --> 02:56:15.102
Prayers without sincerity and faith cannot
be accepted. This is

cue-2668
02:56:15.102 --> 02:56:18.862
plain enough. God looks at the heart, and
so do we.

cue-2669
02:56:19.562 --> 02:56:22.822
No one grants requests when these simple
qualities are missing.

cue-2670
02:56:23.702 --> 02:56:27.802
That sincerity must belong both to the
prayer and to the person praying.

cue-2671
02:56:28.982 --> 02:56:30.722
Fine words are not prayer.

cue-2672
02:56:31.362 --> 02:56:35.762
Are all sincere, earnest, believing
prayers offered by godly

cue-2673
02:56:35.762 --> 02:56:39.954
people answered as they ask?Experience
says no.

cue-2674
02:56:40.714 --> 02:56:45.244
I have seen a grieving mother cling to the
body of her child, refusing to believe

cue-2675
02:56:45.244 --> 02:56:46.334
the child was dead.

cue-2676
02:56:47.394 --> 02:56:52.354
She had prayed. God had promised. She had
believed. He always heard

cue-2677
02:56:52.354 --> 02:56:52.854
prayer.

cue-2678
02:56:53.634 --> 02:56:55.454
How then could her child die?

cue-2679
02:56:56.754 --> 02:57:01.614
When at last the truth forced itself on
her troubled mind, her sorrow grew even

cue-2680
02:57:01.614 --> 02:57:06.293
deeper at the thought that God had not
heard her. There are many such

cue-2681
02:57:06.294 --> 02:57:11.274
moments of desperate faith. Is God angry,
as in the case of David,

cue-2682
02:57:11.274 --> 02:57:13.594
even when there seems to be no such cause?

cue-2683
02:57:14.674 --> 02:57:16.374
Could it be that He is indifferent?

cue-2684
02:57:17.014 --> 02:57:18.684
Could it be that He does not know?

cue-2685
02:57:19.354 --> 02:57:20.264
Has He forgotten?

cue-2686
02:57:21.374 --> 02:57:24.894
With questions like these in mind, I
turned to my Bible,

cue-2687
02:57:25.594 --> 02:57:28.794
and there I found the answer in three
representative cases.

cue-2688
02:57:29.694 --> 02:57:33.294
Deuteronomy three, verses twenty-three
through twenty-five,

cue-2689
02:57:34.354 --> 02:57:37.294
where Moses prayed that he might go over
into Canaan.

cue-2690
02:57:38.034 --> 02:57:39.894
First Kings nineteen, verse four,

cue-2691
02:57:40.594 --> 02:57:42.893
where Elijah prayed that he might die.

cue-2692
02:57:43.854 --> 02:57:47.413
Second Corinthians twelve, verses eight
through nine,

cue-2693
02:57:47.414 --> 02:57:50.674
where Paul prayed that his affliction
might be removed.

cue-2694
02:57:51.764 --> 02:57:56.114
These three men hold an important place in
Scripture, and yet each of them was

cue-2695
02:57:56.114 --> 02:58:01.054
denied his request. Their prayers are
representative cases,

cue-2696
02:58:01.054 --> 02:58:03.594
and together they cover the whole problem.

cue-2697
02:58:04.734 --> 02:58:06.314
Let us look at them one by one.

cue-2698
02:58:08.334 --> 02:58:09.454
The prayer of Moses.

cue-2699
02:58:12.034 --> 02:58:15.094
Moses prayed that he might be allowed to
finish his work.

cue-2700
02:58:15.794 --> 02:58:17.734
He had taken it up at God's command.

cue-2701
02:58:18.394 --> 02:58:23.334
For forty years he had cared for and led a
complaining and ungrateful people through

cue-2702
02:58:23.334 --> 02:58:24.014
the wilderness.

cue-2703
02:58:24.894 --> 02:58:26.694
Now the promised land was in sight.

cue-2704
02:58:27.714 --> 02:58:31.974
What could be more natural than for him to
long to see his life's work brought to

cue-2705
02:58:31.974 --> 02:58:32.594
completion?

cue-2706
02:58:33.694 --> 02:58:37.894
And from every human point of view, he
seemed impossible to replace.

cue-2707
02:58:38.794 --> 02:58:42.214
He would appear to be needed in Canaan
even more than in the wilderness.

cue-2708
02:58:43.094 --> 02:58:44.774
Enemies still had to be driven out.

cue-2709
02:58:45.424 --> 02:58:49.714
The nation's order had to be established,
and the people had to be settled in the

cue-2710
02:58:49.714 --> 02:58:50.114
land.

cue-2711
02:58:51.334 --> 02:58:56.054
If he left them now, it seemed as though
the work of forty years might fall apart.

cue-2712
02:58:57.594 --> 02:58:59.923
Internal conflict might ruin the nation.

cue-2713
02:59:01.174 --> 02:59:06.154
It is no wonder then that he prayed that
he might cross over. Yet in spite

cue-2714
02:59:06.154 --> 02:59:10.614
of the people's need, in spite of his
faithful record, and in spite of his

cue-2715
02:59:10.614 --> 02:59:11.474
earnest prayer,

cue-2716
02:59:12.434 --> 02:59:13.274
he died.

cue-2717
02:59:14.274 --> 02:59:19.254
He died with his work unfinished. He died
when he seemed to be needed

cue-2718
02:59:19.254 --> 02:59:19.674
most.

cue-2719
02:59:20.564 --> 02:59:23.694
He died with the hope of many years
finally within sight.

cue-2720
02:59:24.674 --> 02:59:29.274
Is it not often like this? A person may
accept his life's work as a calling from

cue-2721
02:59:29.274 --> 02:59:29.674
God.

cue-2722
02:59:30.604 --> 02:59:35.534
He gives to it all he has, mind and body,
time and strength,

cue-2723
02:59:36.314 --> 02:59:39.894
often at great cost to his own comfort and
personal hopes.

cue-2724
02:59:41.054 --> 02:59:45.394
He prays for his work, asking God to
prosper it and bless him in it.

cue-2725
02:59:46.194 --> 02:59:46.854
That is right.

cue-2726
02:59:47.454 --> 02:59:51.794
No one should be engaged in work that he
cannot bring before God in prayer.

cue-2727
02:59:52.654 --> 02:59:56.794
God does not place a person in work for
empty or unworthy purposes.

cue-2728
02:59:57.394 --> 03:00:00.174
He intends work to have meaning and value.

cue-2729
03:00:01.054 --> 03:00:04.794
And yet, how often it seems that the
prayers of good people fail.

cue-2730
03:00:05.634 --> 03:00:07.774
Plans they have prayed over fall apart.

cue-2731
03:00:08.434 --> 03:00:12.854
Competitors succeed. Trouble overtakes
them. Illness weakens them.

cue-2732
03:00:12.854 --> 03:00:16.714
Death comes, and the labor of many years
is left

cue-2733
03:00:16.714 --> 03:00:21.414
unfinished. At such times, death can seem
almost cruel.

cue-2734
03:00:22.074 --> 03:00:27.034
It strikes just as the hand is reaching
for the reward. It takes the parent

cue-2735
03:00:27.034 --> 03:00:30.374
or wise guide when they seem needed most.

cue-2736
03:00:30.794 --> 03:00:33.354
It passes by the weak and takes the
strong.

cue-2737
03:00:34.254 --> 03:00:38.394
It removes the one carrying the burden and
leaves the burden behind.

cue-2738
03:00:39.614 --> 03:00:44.354
We plead to remain a little longer, just a
little longer, only until this work is

cue-2739
03:00:44.354 --> 03:00:48.994
finished, only until the children are
grown, only until the business is settled.

cue-2740
03:00:48.994 --> 03:00:53.374
But the answer may still be, "Get thee up
into the top of

cue-2741
03:00:53.374 --> 03:00:55.114
Pisgah and die."

cue-2742
03:00:57.114 --> 03:01:00.904
David wanted to build a house for God. His
heart was set on it.

cue-2743
03:01:01.594 --> 03:01:06.394
God even praised him for desiring to do
it, yet he would not allow him to do it.

cue-2744
03:01:07.634 --> 03:01:12.554
In the same way, many hearts are set on
some work for God with deep longing and

cue-2745
03:01:12.554 --> 03:01:12.874
prayer.

cue-2746
03:01:13.694 --> 03:01:15.934
Yet that work is withheld from them.

cue-2747
03:01:17.194 --> 03:01:21.114
The man whom Jesus had wonderfully saved
begged that he might go with him,

cue-2748
03:01:21.814 --> 03:01:24.194
but Jesus sent him home instead.

cue-2749
03:01:26.434 --> 03:01:27.654
Juniper tree prayers.

cue-2750
03:01:30.174 --> 03:01:32.394
Elijah was a mighty man of prayer.

cue-2751
03:01:33.414 --> 03:01:36.054
God answered all his prayers except one,

cue-2752
03:01:36.774 --> 03:01:38.334
the prayer that he might die.

cue-2753
03:01:39.234 --> 03:01:43.674
He prayed this while sitting under the
juniper tree, worn down by mental and

cue-2754
03:01:43.674 --> 03:01:44.694
physical exhaustion.

cue-2755
03:01:45.834 --> 03:01:47.894
The day before had been a great victory.

cue-2756
03:01:48.574 --> 03:01:53.474
He had stood alone as God's servant,
strong, bold, and triumphant.

cue-2757
03:01:54.554 --> 03:01:57.044
But the next day was the day after the
battle.

cue-2758
03:01:57.734 --> 03:01:58.964
At the threat of one woman,

cue-2759
03:01:59.614 --> 03:02:02.314
he fled. His nerves were shattered.

cue-2760
03:02:03.234 --> 03:02:06.384
Fear, discouragement, and despair took
hold of him.

cue-2761
03:02:07.234 --> 03:02:11.574
In the bitterness and confusion of
depression, he prayed that he might die.

cue-2762
03:02:12.794 --> 03:02:16.434
That condition is still with us, and
perhaps more common than ever.

cue-2763
03:02:17.514 --> 03:02:20.634
There are not enough juniper trees for all
who would sit beneath them.

cue-2764
03:02:21.454 --> 03:02:26.294
Some gloomy Christians seem almost to have
built their homes there. A

cue-2765
03:02:26.294 --> 03:02:30.604
nervous breakdown is not only physical, it
is often spiritual as well,

cue-2766
03:02:31.254 --> 03:02:32.654
though usually it is both.

cue-2767
03:02:33.684 --> 03:02:36.174
Faith has no place for hopeless despair.

cue-2768
03:02:37.614 --> 03:02:42.114
How merciful it is that God does not
always grant our words exactly as we speak

cue-2769
03:02:42.114 --> 03:02:47.050
them.Few things dishonor God more than
the complaining hopelessness

cue-2770
03:02:47.050 --> 03:02:51.139
of his people. Juniper trees make poor
places of worship.

cue-2771
03:02:52.580 --> 03:02:57.510
The apostle's thorn in the flesh does not
need much discussion here because we have

cue-2772
03:02:57.510 --> 03:02:59.750
already spoken of prayer and suffering.

cue-2773
03:03:00.740 --> 03:03:05.650
The thorn was a bodily affliction, and
because Paul saw it as a hindrance, he

cue-2774
03:03:05.650 --> 03:03:07.490
prayed that it might be taken away.

cue-2775
03:03:08.530 --> 03:03:13.110
But it was not removed, even though he
pleaded with the Lord three times.

cue-2776
03:03:14.310 --> 03:03:18.850
He had to learn that affliction may be a
messenger from God as well as something

cue-2777
03:03:18.850 --> 03:03:19.890
Satan uses.

cue-2778
03:03:21.850 --> 03:03:23.650
The answer to unanswered prayers.

cue-2779
03:03:26.270 --> 03:03:30.190
None of these prayers went unanswered.
They were not granted, but they were

cue-2780
03:03:30.190 --> 03:03:32.430
answered, and the answer was no.

cue-2781
03:03:33.430 --> 03:03:36.010
No is just as much an answer as yes.

cue-2782
03:03:36.910 --> 03:03:41.490
When a request is refused, it is answered
just as truly as when it is granted.

cue-2783
03:03:42.670 --> 03:03:47.649
Sometimes refusal is the only answer that
love, wisdom, and truth can

cue-2784
03:03:47.649 --> 03:03:47.950
give.

cue-2785
03:03:49.180 --> 03:03:54.160
A child may cry for a razor, and grown
people may cry for things just as

cue-2786
03:03:54.160 --> 03:03:57.190
unsuitable, dangerous, or unwise.

cue-2787
03:03:58.430 --> 03:04:02.730
Many people have lived long enough to
thank God that he refused their desperate

cue-2788
03:04:02.730 --> 03:04:04.530
prayers at some particular time

cue-2789
03:04:05.210 --> 03:04:08.310
or for something that then seemed
absolutely necessary.

cue-2790
03:04:09.410 --> 03:04:11.550
God never refuses without a reason.

cue-2791
03:04:12.150 --> 03:04:17.030
He knows the past, and there may be things
in it that explain why a request

cue-2792
03:04:17.030 --> 03:04:18.210
can't now be granted.

cue-2793
03:04:19.210 --> 03:04:22.750
Sin may be forgiven, yet its effects may
still remain.

cue-2794
03:04:23.750 --> 03:04:26.290
Moses and David were both examples of
this.

cue-2795
03:04:26.950 --> 03:04:31.190
Some vessels are spoiled on the potter's
wheel, and though another vessel may be

cue-2796
03:04:31.190 --> 03:04:34.130
made, the first one cannot be restored.

cue-2797
03:04:34.970 --> 03:04:39.070
Diseases may be healed, but a lost limb
cannot be given back.

cue-2798
03:04:40.080 --> 03:04:42.470
The Lord knows the future as well as the
past.

cue-2799
03:04:43.110 --> 03:04:46.130
What seems good for the moment may put the
future in danger.

cue-2800
03:04:46.750 --> 03:04:50.670
A craving for a single meal may cost a
person his inheritance.

cue-2801
03:04:51.910 --> 03:04:54.449
Esau got the answer he wanted at mealtime.

cue-2802
03:04:55.490 --> 03:05:00.350
Jacob received his answer at daybreak. God
added fifteen years to Hezekiah's

cue-2803
03:05:00.350 --> 03:05:05.030
life, but in the end, it might have been
better if he had gone when the

cue-2804
03:05:05.030 --> 03:05:06.350
Lord first called him.

cue-2805
03:05:08.110 --> 03:05:10.230
The greater includes the lesser.

cue-2806
03:05:12.670 --> 03:05:17.030
Delay is not denial, and it is always
worth waiting for God's time.

cue-2807
03:05:18.510 --> 03:05:23.470
Moses did enter Canaan, and Elijah went to
heaven by a far more glorious

cue-2808
03:05:23.470 --> 03:05:26.270
way than the one he imagined under the
juniper tree.

cue-2809
03:05:27.450 --> 03:05:31.870
No prayer of faith that is truly inspired
by God is ever finally

cue-2810
03:05:31.870 --> 03:05:36.250
refused. God's no is never his last word.

cue-2811
03:05:37.050 --> 03:05:42.010
If a prayer seems unanswered, it is only
because the answer is hidden for a time in

cue-2812
03:05:42.010 --> 03:05:44.830
a greater glory that will be seen later.

cue-2813
03:05:45.570 --> 03:05:50.429
God may refuse one path because he knows a
better one. He brought Moses into

cue-2814
03:05:50.430 --> 03:05:53.000
Canaan by a better way and in better
company.

cue-2815
03:05:54.040 --> 03:05:58.970
I have known others who also had to go by
way of heaven to receive the answer

cue-2816
03:05:58.970 --> 03:05:59.810
to their prayers.

cue-2817
03:06:01.010 --> 03:06:05.690
God took Elijah to heaven in a much more
wonderful way than death in the ordinary

cue-2818
03:06:05.690 --> 03:06:06.090
course.

cue-2819
03:06:07.270 --> 03:06:11.930
Elijah wanted to die, but God gave his
weary servant sleep and

cue-2820
03:06:11.930 --> 03:06:15.310
rest and then sent him away to the hills
for renewal.

cue-2821
03:06:16.380 --> 03:06:21.280
That is often God's remedy for exhausted
nerves, fresh air, a new vision,

cue-2822
03:06:21.280 --> 03:06:22.770
and a greater task.

cue-2823
03:06:23.710 --> 03:06:25.850
Paul had no use for juniper trees.

cue-2824
03:06:26.550 --> 03:06:27.630
To him, God said,

cue-2825
03:06:28.250 --> 03:06:33.030
"My grace is sufficient for thee," and
taught him to rejoice even in suffering

cue-2826
03:06:33.030 --> 03:06:33.790
and hardship.

cue-2827
03:06:34.910 --> 03:06:38.060
In the experience that first tested our
faith so deeply,

cue-2828
03:06:38.710 --> 03:06:40.770
God sent help out of the darkness.

cue-2829
03:06:41.950 --> 03:06:45.149
Through the tears of a broken heart, light
came.

cue-2830
03:06:45.750 --> 03:06:50.690
When the memorial card was prepared, it
carried these words, which corrected our

cue-2831
03:06:50.690 --> 03:06:51.269
unbelief.

cue-2832
03:06:52.230 --> 03:06:57.230
He asked life of thee, and thou gavest it
him, even length of days forever and

cue-2833
03:06:57.230 --> 03:06:57.510
ever.

cue-2834
03:06:58.370 --> 03:07:02.809
So one day in glory, we shall see that our
prayers were answered according to the

cue-2835
03:07:02.809 --> 03:07:07.790
infinite wisdom and eternal love of God
our Father, who teaches us

cue-2836
03:07:07.790 --> 03:07:08.290
to pray.

cue-2837
03:07:10.610 --> 03:07:13.430
E. B. Browning wrote the following:
Unanswered yet.

cue-2838
03:07:14.390 --> 03:07:18.530
The prayers your lips have pleaded in
agony of heart these many years.

cue-2839
03:07:19.850 --> 03:07:21.030
Does faith begin to fail?

cue-2840
03:07:21.970 --> 03:07:22.980
Is hope departing?

cue-2841
03:07:23.890 --> 03:07:26.390
And think you all in vain those falling
tears?

cue-2842
03:07:27.830 --> 03:07:30.150
Say not the Father hath not heard your
prayer.

cue-2843
03:07:30.830 --> 03:07:33.110
You shall have your desire, sometime,

cue-2844
03:07:33.770 --> 03:07:34.170
somewhere.

cue-2845
03:07:35.050 --> 03:07:35.950
Unanswered yet?

cue-2846
03:07:36.770 --> 03:07:41.330
Though when you first presented this one
petition at the Father's throne, it seemed

cue-2847
03:07:41.330 --> 03:07:45.950
you could not wait the time of asking, so
urgent was the heart to make it known.

cue-2848
03:07:46.920 --> 03:07:48.600
Though years have passed since then,

cue-2849
03:07:49.270 --> 03:07:50.070
do not despair.

cue-2850
03:07:50.790 --> 03:07:51.810
The Lord will answer you,

cue-2851
03:07:52.410 --> 03:07:52.920
sometime,

cue-2852
03:07:53.630 --> 03:07:56.090
somewhere. Unanswered yet.

cue-2853
03:07:56.890 --> 03:08:01.230
Nay, do not say ungranted. Perhaps your
work is not wholly done.

cue-2854
03:08:02.230 --> 03:08:06.710
The work began when first your prayer was
uttered, and God will finish what he has

cue-2855
03:08:06.710 --> 03:08:07.150
begun.

cue-2856
03:08:08.610 --> 03:08:13.090
If you will keep the incense burning
there, his glory you shall see,

cue-2857
03:08:13.090 --> 03:08:14.670
sometime, somewhere.

cue-2858
03:08:15.670 --> 03:08:16.580
Unanswered yet.

cue-2859
03:08:17.370 --> 03:08:22.190
Faith cannot be unanswered. Her feet are
firmly planted on the rock. Amid the

cue-2860
03:08:22.190 --> 03:08:27.150
wildest storms she stands undaunted, nor
quails before the loudest thunder

cue-2861
03:08:27.150 --> 03:08:27.450
shock.

cue-2862
03:08:28.570 --> 03:08:33.280
She knows omnipotence has heard her
prayer, and cries, "It shall be done,

cue-2863
03:08:33.280 --> 03:08:35.270
sometime, somewhere."

cue-2864
03:08:37.930 --> 03:08:41.350
You have finished listening to The Path of
Prayer by Samuel Chadwick.

